<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="MRK" stage="Final" version="B">
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Ma'u</p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Lii Hag'a D'ara J'ara Lua Yesus<bt>*Gospel (Good Story) about Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Pedèu nga do hure do b'uke ri<bt>according to what has been written by</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Ma'u<bt>Markus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Na d'ee ke, lii hag'a d'ara. Lii ped'èi j'ara lua Ana Deo.<bt>This is a good story. It is the story/report/narration about God's Child.</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne lua pale ta &lt;Ana Deo&gt; ad'o do era pa Alkitab do rai uru he hag'e.<bt>The words &lt;God's child&gt; are not in some some of the oldest Bible writings.</bt></note>Ne ngara Noo, Yesus Kristus, do pej'èu'e rai uru ri Deo. Mi nahee ne kepue lii ped'èi ène:<bt>His name is/was Yesus Kristus, whom God had already designated/appointed from long ago. This is the beginning of His story:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèngi = berkat ; pej'uj'e ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèngi = berkat ; pej'uj'e = ditunjuk ; petone = tunjuk khusus untuk itu (kuno, kurang populer, kurang diketahui) ; lua pale = sebutan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lii ped'iri nane do peke ke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Lii ped'iri nane do peke ke rai uru rai telora ri Yesaya mone ub'a Deo miha. Mihe ne lii ped'iri ne:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Johani, mone peherani dèu, pemoko ruj'ara tuu Yesus<bt>Johani, the.one.who.habitually *baptizes people, opens the way/path for Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 3:1-12; Luka 3:1-18; Johani 1:19-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Uru ngad'o j'èga dae Yesus, pepue uru ri Deo he dèu, ne ngara noo Johani. Johani pe'ure ta la pemoko ruj'ara tuu lua dèka Yesus. Rai uru rai telora, do pake ke ri Deo, he dèu, ne ngara noo Yesaya, ta mone ub'a unu Noo. Do b'uke ke ri noo, mihe ane:<bt>Yesus had not yet begun His work, God had ordered (to do s.t.) a person, his name was Johani. Johani had to go ahead to prepare the way for Yesus' coming. Long before, God had already used a person named Yesaya as His *prophet/spokesperson. He wrote, saying:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="uru ngad'o = sebelum ; j'èga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">uru ngad'o = sebelum ; j'èga = kerja, tugas ; pepue = disuruh, diutus ; ped'ae = sampaikan ; Rai tare = dari awal (creation) ; Rai uru rai telora = long ago in history ; unu = milik</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ta ped'ae ke ri Johani nengaa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ta ped'ae ke ri Johani nengaa ne do èla pe b'uke ri Yesaya mone ub'a Deo, mihe ane:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;D'èno nga woie! Pejue ri Yaa ne dèu Yaa, la pemoke ruj'ara natuu Èu.<bt>&lt;&lt;Listen carefully! I am ordering/commanding a person of Mine, to prepare the way for You.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pejue &lt; pejuu ; pemoke &lt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pejue &lt; pejuu ; pemoke &lt; pemoko</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Noo hine do ta kako la era do kehii-kejid'o, j'e lango ri noo:<bt>That person will go to an empty-uninhabited (doublet) place, and shout saying:</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hine = nanti ; pad'a ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hine = nanti ; pad'a = padang, lapangan ; kehii-kejid'o = sunyi-sepi ; lango = sampaikan suara keras (ada pesan) ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Hari-hari dèu pemoke nga woie ruj'ara, mij'e ta hapo lua dèka Muri.<bt>&lt;All people prepare to make good/fix the way/path, to receive the Lord/Master's coming![+Hon.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pemira ruj'ara tuu ta hème Noo.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Make flat the path to greet Him.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pemira = bekin rata"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Pemira = bekin rata</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-6" />Johani do tima ta pale ri dèu he, mone peherani dèu. Ne era pee noo, pa era do kehii-kejid'o. Ne b'ara pake noo ngati rèu b'ada unta. Dari wake noo ngati kuri b'ada. Ne nga'a-nginu noo, keb'ara nga donahu oni. [Muri mada Johani, hela'u nga Elia uru he.]<bt>People usually called Johani, one.who.habitually *baptizes people. He lived in a empty (doublet) place. His clothes were from camel's (loan:onta) fur. His belt was from animal skin. His food-drink (doublet), grasshoppers (picture HK00054C) and wild honey. (This way of life of Johani, was like Elia long ago.) [EXEG: High-level book-level theme from 1:1 (Jesus is the Christ; Elijah will come before the Christ comes) that was obvious to a reasonaly informed Jewish audience, but is not accessible or retrieveable by Timor audiences.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kuri wake = ikat pinggang (dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Kuri wake = ikat pinggang (dari kulit) ; dari wake = normal term for belt ; keb'ara = belalang (picture HK00054C) dimakan orang Sabu ; donahu oni = gula madu ; oni = tawon, lebah ; donahu = gula</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Duae-duae 1:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Pa awe na ène, dèu ti kota Yerusalem, nga ti propensi Yudea harièle, dèka la pe'abu nga Johani la era pee noo. Ne dèka roo d'èi ta la ngède Johani, nga d'èi ta d'èno ne lii aj'a noo. Ta lii ke Johani, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Kelolo mola we ne hala-ludèumuu, j'e hani ri muu ne muri mada muu dod'o mèd'èipa Deo, mij'e lonye pemèu ri Deo ne lub'u-hèro nga menyilu muu harièle. J'e herani muu, ta he èhi rutada ta do èla ke muu pe pe'ie nga Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, people from Yerusalem city (loan: kota), and from all of Yudea province (loan:propensi), came to meet with Johani at his living place. They came because they wanted to see Johani, and wanted to hear his teaching. Johani told them, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must *confess and leave behind all your *wrongs1 (doublet), and stop your way of living that is not pleasing to God, in.order.that *God *forgive1 (wipe clean) all your *wrongs2 (Idiom: salty mud and sour--entrenched (doublet)). Then you-pl must get *baptized (method neutral), as a sign that you are already again RECIP-good (=in a good relationship) with the God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'abu = temui ; hala-ludu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'abu = temui ; hala-ludu = kesalahan, penyimpangan, dosa ; mola = lurus ; kelolo mola = mengaku dgn tulus dari hati sendiri ; pehuba = ampuni (anak melanggar kata-kata orang tua, baru anak minta pehuba; orang yg mencuri ami pehuba ; orang yg bersina mij'e pehuba = supaya diampuni (NOTE: does not require a change of heart) ; lub'u-hèro = lumpur-asin (kiasan bagi dosa, cukup populer) KT ; menyilu = asam. ; KT sala is sometimes seen as kotoran yang -- lonye pemèu = cuci bersih ; pebèlu ne hala-ludu = (orang) lupa buang orang pung sala ; propensi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pantes: not necessarily every last person,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">pantes: not necessarily every last person, but lots, by a hyperbole common in Greek. Could be "plenny plenny," but "all" is OK.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00296C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Johani, mone peherani dèu<bt>Johani, the habitual baptizer of people</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Nadèu do kelolo ne hala-ludèuroo, peherani ri Johani pa loko Yarden.<bt>Whoever *confessed their *sins1 (doublet), Johani *baptised them in the Yarden stream/river.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Pedae lema ri noo, &lt;&lt;B'ole pengee yaa ri muu ta do nga kuaha. Do ta dèka leto ngati yaa he dèu do rihi mone ae kuaha ngati yaa. J'èma led'o yaa ta dèu pejuu Noo.<bt>He told them saying like.this, &lt;&lt;You should not think that I am a person with power/authority. Later there is a person who is more important with power/authority than me going to come. Even to just be his *slave (person who is habitually ordered about), I'm not fitting/appropriate. [NOTE: 1st sent explicated (not added) to avoid ambiguity in last sentence that John is refusing to become his servant.]</bt><note reference="1:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do asli, do b'uke mi nad'ee, &lt;&lt;ta peru'u èni j'e boke ne dari helapa Noo, j'èma led'o ma yaa.&gt;&gt; Ne pedèb'o d'ee, pengee ri Johani, dèu rai patima he. Ad'o Johani do j'èma ta jad'èi dèu pejuu ri Yesus.<bt>The original Greek language Bible it is written saying, &lt;&lt;to just bow.down myself in.order.to undo his sandal strap, it's not fitting/appropriate for me.&gt;&gt; It's meaning is Johani's thinking was he was just a little/common person (social status). He wasn't fitting/worthy to became Yesus' *slave.</bt></note><v n="8" />Peherani muu ri yaa, ri èi we, tapulara nengaa ne do ta tao ri Noo hine, rihi ri ko ngaa do tao ri yaa. Noo ke do ta wie ne Hengaa Megala Deo la d'ara ade muu.&gt;&gt;<bt>I'm only *baptizing you with water, but what He will do is more/greater than what I do. He is the one who will give *God's *Holy Spirit (=Spirit/Soul of brightness/light--already entrenched in society) to fill your livers.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gaa led'o = tidak pantas ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gaa led'o = tidak pantas ; ènu = hamba, budak ; peru'u = tunduk, bow, stoop ; dari = tali ; dèu rai patima he = masyarakat biasa ;; 8: higa = ; megala = berkilat-kilat (suci, tidak ada noda), jernih, clear, clear sky with noo clouds = megala liru, megala rai = malam sudah lewat, bisa lihat dengan terang, ; Hengaa Megala Deo = already fixed in society as KT,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Collocation of &quot;baptize&quot; and &quot;Spirit&quot; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Collocation of "baptize" and "Spirit" is opaque; spelled out here.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus peherani ri Johani<bt>Johani *baptizes Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 3:13-17; Luka 3:21-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Pa d'ara awe do na ène, ta dèka ke Yesus ti rae Nasare pa propensi Galilea la pe'abu nga Johani. Ta peherani ke Noo ri Johani pa loko Yarden.<bt>At that time, Yesus came from the Nasare village in the province of Galilea in.order.to meet Johani. Then Johani *baptized Him in the Yarden river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed by a comma after "time"</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Mi nahère Yesus ne mèhu èni ti d'ara èi nee, ta ngède ke ne liru-bèla ta boka èni. Ta puru ke ne Hengaa Deo la Yesus, mi koro j'awa.<bt>As the moment Yesus came out of the water, the sky (doublet) was seen opened (by itself). Then the God's *Spirit descended to Yesus, like a dove.</bt><v n="11" />J'e rènge ne lii pedai Deo ti liru-bèla, mihe ane,<bt>Then was heard *God's voice from the sky, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèla = luas ; koro j'awa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">bèla = luas ; koro j'awa = ada yg puti, abu-abu, hitam, makan jagung, beras, kacang ijo, sprti makanan ayam ; wue = menyerupai; 11: penau nga na ène = bersamaan dgn itu ; liru-bèla = sky (doublet)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Èu ke d'ee, Ana d'èi Yaa.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-sg here, [are] My dear Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Èu ke ne do pemengèlu d'ara Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>You are the one who makes Me happy.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pemengèlu d'ara = memberikan sukacita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pemengèlu d'ara = memberikan sukacita</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Ped'iri Pe'era Liru nga Rai-wawa 22:2, Lii Wue-Waje 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateo 3:17, 12:18, Ma'u 9:7, Luka 3:22</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01656b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm">Johani èla peherani Yesus<bt>Johani has finished baptising Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus hèko ri Kètu wango pa era do kehii-kejid'o<bt>*Satan (=evil spirits Head) *tests Yesus in a lonely place</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 4:1-11; Luka 4:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta èla pe mi nahère, ta pereda ke pa Yesus ri Hengaa Deo, ta kako la era do kehii-kejid'o.<bt>After that, the *God's *Spirit ordered Yesus to go to an empty place (doublet).</bt><v n="13" />Pee Noo pa nii èpa nguru lod'o ne tui, hela'u nga b'ada èdèuhe. Pa era na ène, dèka ne Kètu wango la hèko Noo mij'e ta pedèue noo, tapulara nara d'o. Dèka ne dèu pejuu Deo ti liru-bèla la pemoke Noo.<bt>Yesus stayed in that place forty days, together with wild animals. There, *Satan came to tempt/test Him to follow/obey him, but he didn't accomplish.his.purpose. Then *angels (God's servants from heaven) came to arrange/take.care.of/prepare Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tui = lamanya ; kika ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tui = lamanya ; kika = leluhur orang Sabu ; naju = pesuruh (kuno, kurang dikenal) ; malaika = commonly used, says concept of spirit of baby who died in infancy not known on Sabu (but UNS's say it is, and it is called malaika and kika); dèu can't be used for non-human creatures ; hewewe = membimbing ke arah yg lebih baik ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: da Devil &quot;Wild animals&quot; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Satanaa: da Devil "Wild animals" is part of the setting for Pidgin, so moved to connect with "boonies".<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>Implicit "come" to get them on site. Not "take care Jesus," because the reference is clear from the cast of characters and the semantics. In this case the pronoun works.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus kako la Galilea la peke ne ruj'ara do d'èi Deo<bt>Yesus goes to Galilea to tell (people) the ways of God's will/ways that please God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 4:12-17; Luka 4:14-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta èla Johani, mone peherani dèu, pe pemaho la èmu b'èdo, ta kako ke Yesus la propensi Galilea, la pedae pe peke ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo pa nii.<bt>After they had put Johani, the habitual baptizer of people, into prison, Yesus went to the province of Galilea, to speak telling (people) the Good News from God there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Tukang Sarani&quot; from the first section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">"Tukang Sarani" from the first section.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ta pedai ke Noo, mihe ane,<bt>He told (them), saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peke = tell, Obj tunggal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peke = tell, Obj tunggal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu! D'ai ke ne awe pa Deo!<bt>&lt;&lt;You people listen! God's time has arrived!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Na d'ee, toi ke ri harièle dèu ta Deo ne do pereda!<bt>Now, all people will know that God rules/governs!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pengède = memperlihatkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pengède = memperlihatkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ri mi nahère ke, hani ko ne hala-ludèumuu!<bt>Therefore you must stop your wrongs (doublet)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nga muri mada dod'o mèd'i pa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nga muri mada dod'o mèd'i pa Deo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">J'e pedèue ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then follow/obey the Good News of God.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="1:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 3:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pedoa mone j'ala ta pedèue Noo<bt>Yesus calls/summons fishermen1 to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 4:18-22; Luka 5:1-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Pa d'ara he lod'o, ta nèru ke Yesus oro ngidi èi lobo Galilea. Ta ngède ke ri Noo he dèu, ne ngara noo Himo, nga ari noo Anderia. Hari do d'ue roo, pa d'ara j'ala nadèuu. Na nee ke, ne j'èga roo helod'o-helod'o.<bt>One day, Yesus went along the edge of lake Galilea. He saw a person, named Simo, with his younger.sibling, Anderia. The two of them were (busy/momentarily) cast-netting fish. That was their daily work.</bt><v n="17" />Moko ke Yesus ta pedoa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama ee! Mai we ma pedèue Yaa. Do tima ke muu ta kale nadèuu. Na d'ee ta pejad'èi muu ri Yaa ta la kale dèu ta pedèue Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus called/summoned them, saying, &lt;&lt;Father, ee [vocative for any male, of any age, can be more than one]! Come.here and follow Me [+imperative]. You-pl customarily hunt fish. Now I'm going to make you become people. hunt people to follow/obey Me.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="18" />Ta rèngi mi nahère, ta hani d'ènge ke ne j'ala roo, j'e la pedèue Noo.<bt>After hearing that, they immediately stopped their cast-netting to follow Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="petari rai = mula-mula ; mone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">petari rai = mula-mula ; mone j'ala = penjala ikan ; mone pèku = orang pukat ; oro = menyusur pante ; hab'a = usaha, mencari ; pa d'ara = sementara, busy doing ; j'ala = jala; 17: ngalai = sobat (used for saksi at a wedding), orang sederajat ; hianga = neutral as to status, friend ; Ama ee = sapaan hormat bagi sapa sa, ada maksud sst, can be used for summoning 2 people at once ;; 18: nalu dahi = perlengkapan nelayan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01682b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Nèru hudi ngati ène, ta ngèdi ke ri Noo, ana ri Sabadeu. Mone a'a, ne J'ako. Johani, mone ari. Hari do d'ue roo pa d'ara pemoko ne pèku pa d'ara kowa roo.<bt>After that, Yesus walked a little bit more, then He saw Sabadeu's children. The elder.male's name was Jako. Johani was the younger male. The two of them were busy arranging/fixing/preparing their drag-net in their boat.</bt><v n="20" />Ta pedoa ke roo d'ue ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama ee! Mai we muu ma pedèue Yaa.&gt;&gt; Ta kèd'èid'ènge ke roo, hani ama roo nga harièle dèu do j'èga hela'u nga roo pa d'ara kowa nee. Roo d'ue la pedèue Yesus.<bt>Yesus called/summoned them two, saying, &lt;&lt;Father, ee! Come here and follow Me.&gt;&gt; So the two of them stood up immediately, leaving behind their father and all their working people on the boat. And they followed Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pèku = pukat ; pemoko ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pèku = pukat ; pemoko = mempersiapkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus hud'èiwango ti he dèu pa kota Kapernaum<bt>Yesus expels *evil spirit(s) from a person in Kapernaum city</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 4:31-37)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ta d'ai ke Yesus nga do èpa dèu do pedèue Noo he la kota Kapernaum. Pa lod'o heb'aj'a do Jahudi,<bt>Then Yesus with those four people who followed Him, arrived at Kapernaum city. On the *Sabbath (Jahudi people's (collective) worshipping day),</bt><note reference="1:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne lod'o heb'aj'a, lod'o pengaha ihi, ki ad'o lod'o pengaha j'èga unu do Jahudi he, do tima lema ta pale ta &lt;Lod'o Sabat&gt;.<bt>Jahudi people's worshipping day, rest day, or day of stopping work, they call &lt;Sabat Day&gt;.</bt></note>ta maho ke Yesus la èmu heb'aj'a nee, j'e wie ne lii aj'a pa ène.<bt>then Yesus entered the *synagogue (=worship-service house) and taught there.</bt><v n="22" />Madalae tèra harièle ne dèu do d'èno lii aj'a Noo, ri do toi woie rowi Noo ne ihi lii aj'a Noo. Ne lii aj'a Noo do wala ngati lii aj'a guru agama Jahudi he.<bt>Hearing His teaching, all the people were *amazed, cuz He truly knew/understood the contents of His teaching. His teaching was different than the Jahudi people's religious teachers. [CHECK: I'm not sure manner (how he taught) comes through.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mud'i hèku = kebetulan ; pengaha"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mud'i hèku = kebetulan ; pengaha ihi = istirahat; 22: teleo = jelas, terang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ri d'ai wo ie teleo do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ri d'ai wo ie teleo do toi ri Noo nga petuu ne ihi lii aj'a do pedae ri Noo. Ne lii aj'a Noo do wala ngati lii aj'a guru-guru Jahudi he.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 7:28-29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Pa awe do na ène, era he dèu do maho ri wango. Ta maho le ke noo, la d'ara èmu heb'aj'a nee, j'e pekaa ne wango do pa d'ara noo, mihe ane,<bt>At that time, there was a person who was entered (=normal way of speaking about demon possession) by an *evil spirit. He also entered into the synagogue, and.then that evil spirit inside that person shouted, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en: &quot;take ova&quot; and &quot;let go&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">en: "take ova" and "let go" is the culturally appropriate way to talk about a person being under the control of an outside power. "In" and "go out" or "throw out" doesn't make a lot of sense. At least two of the translators have had first hand experience with this kind of situation.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />&lt;&lt;Wo! Yesus, do Nasare! Ta ma ngaa ke j'ii ri Èu? Ta ma pe'apa j'ii ri Èu? Tade Èu ri j'ii. Ta Èu ke ne do dèka pedèuu nga lii jaji Deo. Èu d'ee, Dèu do d'o i'a tao hala-ludèu&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Wo! Yesus, the Nasare person! What (business) do you-sg have with us-exc! Have You come to destroy us-exc? We-exc know/recognise You. You here have come according to God's promise. You here, the Person who doesn't *sin (doublet).&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ta j'ege ke noo ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Petèmo ne ub'a èu! Mèhu èni ti d'ara dèu do na d'ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke angrily to him, saying, &lt;&lt;Shut your mouth! Get out of that person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ege = hardik, masparak ; petèmo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'ege = hardik, masparak ; petèmo = tutup</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ta ked'èji ke ne dèu na ène, ri kuaha wango do era pa d'ara ngi'u noo. Ta mèhu èni ne wango nee, nga pekaa do mèdèu<bt>Then the power of that *evil spirit made that person's body to convulse. And then he came out of that person with a very loud shout.</bt><v n="27" />Harièle ne dèu do pa d'ara èmu heb'aj'a ne ta hengodo ke. J'e pedai roo he dèu nga he dèu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Lai ngaa na d'ee? Pereda ri Noo wango ta mèhu èni, ta pedèuu we. Lii aj'a do wiu? Tèra-tèra ne kuaha Dokepai d'ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people in that *synagogue were *amazed2 (open-mouthed). And they all spoke.to.each.other, saying, &lt;&lt;What's this? He commands *evil spirits to go out, and they follow/obey (Him). Is this a new teaching, or (what)? This Old Man's (term of respect-age not relevant) power/authority, is really exceptional!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ked'èji = kejang, convulse (like penyakit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ked'èji = kejang, convulse (like penyakit ayan); 27: tèra-tèra = sungguh-sungguh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Several people have remarked on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Several people have remarked on the inadequacy of just "?" and "!" for Pidgin. The combination "?!" is what they suggest for something that sounds like a question but which is really a surprised exclamation. kat' exousian: could go either with "teaching" or with "tell". This kind of sits on the fence.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta j'ari ke dèu he, ta pedai he dèu nga he dèu, menyèla la harièle rae-kowa pa propensi Galilea.<bt>Then the people began to RECIP-tell.story all over the place from person to person, spreading to all the villages in Galilea province.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menyèla = tersebar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">menyèla = tersebar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie ina matu Petu, nga ae riko dèu do hewala<bt>Yesus *heals Petu's mother-in-law and many other people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 8:14-17; Luka 4:38-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta mèhu èni ke roo ngati èmu heb'aja nee, j'e hare Yesus la èmu Himo nga Anderia. Mi nahère lema J'ako nga Johani do penau hela'u nga roo.<bt>As they were coming out of the *synagogue, then Yesus went to Simo and Anderia's house. J'ako and Johani went with them.</bt><v n="30" />Ne ina matu ri Himo do bèj'i ta emo. Ta d'ai roo ne maho la d'ara èmu nee, ta pika ke dèu pa Yesus ta, &lt;&lt;Nèi do emo j'e rena weka nee.&gt;&gt;<bt>Simo's mother-in-law was laying down with fever. Thus when they arrived entered that house, then someone told Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;Elder.mother (term of respect) has a fever.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ina matu = WM ; riko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ina matu = WM ; riko = lagi ~ rike ;; 30: nèi = sementara, ada ; rena weka = mamatua</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta maho ke Yesus la pehod'e rena weka nee. Ta pèro ri Noo ne wolaèba rena weka nee, j'e pekèd'e. Ta ie d'ènge ke ne emo noo. J'e kèd'èila pemoko nga'a-nginu natuu roo.<bt>Then Yesus went into the old lady's room. He held her hand, then2 stood her up. Then her fever immediately disappeared. Then2 elder.mother stood up, to go serve/arrange/take.care of their food-drink.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pekèd'e = kasi bangun, stood up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pekèd'e = kasi bangun, stood up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="She couldn't cook because it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">She couldn't cook because it was Sabbath.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ta jèna ne lod'o, dèka ke ne dèu lowe he nga ègu dèu do pèd'a, nga do maho ri wango. Ami roo ta la pe'ie ri Yesus.<bt>When the sun was sinking, people came bringing their sick people, and who were adversely affected by *evil spirits. They brought them for Yesus to heal.</bt><v n="33" />Harièle dèu pa d'ara rae na ène, dèka la peteni pa hed'apa èmu do na ène.<bt>All the humans in that city [hyperbole], came crowding around the front of that house.</bt><v n="34" />Ae kera'a pèd'a ne dèu he, pe'ie harièle ri Yesus. Ae ne wango do hud'èiri Noo ti d'ara dèu he. Lara ri Yesus ne wango he ta b'ole pedai lii, ri do tade ke Noo ri roo.<bt>Those people had various sorts of sicknesses, but Yesus *healed them. And he expelled ever so many *evil spirits from people's insides. Yesus forbade those *evil spirits to talk, because they knew Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="herae-hekowa ; pe'ude = collect (things)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">herae-hekowa ; pe'ude = collect (things) ; peteni = collect (people) ; heti'i = tempat cucuran air</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pelebe Lii Ha'ga D'ara ngati Deo la kota-kota do wala<bt>Yesus spread.tells the *gospel from God2 to other cities</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 4:42-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Pa d'ara perèmo mèu rai, ta kèd'èike Yesus ti èmu do na ène. Kako Noo la era do kehii la heb'aj'a, la pedai lii nga Deo.<bt>The next morning almost daylight, Yesus got.up and left that house. He went to a lonely place to *pray1, to RECIP-talk with God.</bt><v n="36" />D'ai ne keb'èdi Himo nga ihianga noo, pe'ee d'oke Yesus. Ta la kale ke ri roo Yesus.<bt>When Simo and his companions woke.up, Yesus was no longer there. So they went to look for Yesus [CHECK: pronominalise?].</bt><v n="37" />Ta d'ai roo ne pehapo nga Yesus, ta lii ke roo, &lt;&lt;Wo Ama. Ae ne dèu do la kale Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they found Him, then they said, &lt;&lt;Wo, Father. Many people are looking for you (father).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="last sent V S O"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">last sent V S O</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ta lii ke Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ie lema. Tapulara rihi ie dii ta pekèd'èila rae-rae do wala do pe'umu pa d'ee. Ne d'èi Yaa, la pedae leko pa roo ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo. Ri ne dèka Yaa tuu lai na d'ee ke.&gt;&gt;<bt>He said, saying, &lt;&lt;That's also good. But it's better for us-inc to go first to other villages, that are close by here. I want to tell them the *Gospel (Good News from God) too. Cuz that is the reason for My coming.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leko = ?? juga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">leko = ?? juga</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ta kako ke Yesus pehero hari hewue propensi Galilea, j'e pedae ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo pa d'ara harièle èmu heb'aj'a roo. Hud'èilema ri Noo ne wango ngati dèu he.<bt>Then He went walking all.around that Galilea province and told the *Gospel from at all their various *synagogues. And He also expelled *evil spirits from people.</bt><note reference="1:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 4:23, 9:35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie he dèu do pèd'a kusta<bt>Yesus *heals a person with leprosy sickness (loan)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 8:1-4; Luka 5:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Pa awe na ène, ta dèka ke he dèu do pèd'a kusta nga Yesus. Ta d'ai noo la hed'apa Yesus ta lèku rutuu ke noo, j'e ami, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Muri yae! Ruba kowe ne d'ara Èu, ta pe'ie ne pèd'a yaa! Mij'i dod'o b'ege d'ara loro ne dèu he nga yaa. Kido d'èi tèra, Muri nga yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there was a person with leprosy, who came to Yesus. Then he knelt (folded knees) to request help, saying, &lt;&lt;Master! [=conventionalised title elevating the addressee in status] Help/Pity/Mercy me now! You can make this illness of mine disappear/be healed! So.that people no longer are grossed.out/avoid me. As long as you/Master want to.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pèd'a nadato = (not known), belom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pèd'a nadato = (not known), belom ada di Sabu, kalo kana di tangan, jari jato, dll ; yae &lt; yaa + e ; kido = kalau ; b'ege = ?? jijik</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease patient, but someone suffering from a skin disease that made him ritually unfit for worship. But with so many people here having relatives who were (or are) in the Kalaupapa leper colony, "lepa" has instant recognition, and a strong emotional reaction as serious. Ideas of "ritually impure" are not, on the other hand, common in the culture. katharisai: "cleanse" in the ritual sense, "make me so I can worship with the rest again"<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ta meloro ke ne ade Yesus nga noo. Ta j'ole ri Yesus ne wolaèba Noo j'e b'uje ne dèu na ène, j'e lii Noo, &lt;&lt;Ne d'èi Yaa, ie we èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then, Yesus love/pity (toward) that person. Then He stretched out his hand to touch him, and said, &lt;&lt;I want to; you be well/healed!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meloro = kasian"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">meloro = kasian</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Pa d'ara awe do na ène, ele d'ènge ne pèd'a noo. B'ale ne ngi'u noo mi patima.<bt>Unexpectedly/immediately, his disease disappeared. His body returned to normal/wholenss.</bt><v n="43" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa noo, ta b'ale la èmu nga jaji made-made pa noo, mihe ane,<bt>Then Yesus told him to go.home, and reminded/warned him firmly,saying,</bt><v n="44" />&lt;&lt;Henge pe woie! Ie ke èu. B'ole la ped'èii pa nadèu we! Petobe we ri èu ne lua petèka Musa rai uru he. Kako uru la pengèdi èni pa kètu agama, mij'e ta pereha ri noo ne ngi'u èu, ta do ie tèra ke, we ad'o. J'e èba èu ne b'ara j'ola ta he èhi rutada terima kasi, mij'e toi ri dèu do lowe he ta do ie tèra ke èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Remember this really well! You are now healed, but you may not tell anyone! You must follow Musa's command from long ago. Go first/now to show yourself to the *priest (=head of religion), in.order.that he examine your body, to see if you are really well/healed or not. Then you must give an *offering as a sign of thanks, in.order.that all/many people know that you are truly healed.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ole (Dimu) ~ j'ole (Seba) ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'ole (Dimu) ~ j'ole (Seba) = sorong; 44: for Jingitiu the priest is called /mone ama rai/</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very abrupt with the man, and practically pushed him out the door. Two senses of "now": admonition with "no foget", and time with "stay good." No clash.<span class="Italic">(44)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kètu Agama nga Lua Petèka Agama 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Tapulara, ta d'ai noo ne mèhu èni, ta kako ke noo la ped'èii pa mii-pa mii. Pelai ti mi nahère, ae tèra ne dèu do la kale ta pe'abu nga Yesus, tade dod'o wae ke Yesus ta pengèdi èni pa roo pa d'ara rae. Ta la pee ke Noo pa era-era do kehii. Maji lema ta mi nahère, pee ma ne dèu he ta pejila nga Yesus ti harièle keb'ihu rai.<bt>But that person went out, and he narrated all.around everywhere/wherever. Then, many people searched to meet with Yesus, to-point-that He couldn't show himself to them. So He just stayed in lonely places. But from everywhere/all directions, people kept flowing coming continually, wanting to meet with Yesus..</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pejila = ?? datang terus-menerus ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pejila = ?? datang terus-menerus ; keb'ihu rai = ?? penjuru;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie he dèu do red'o<bt>Yesus heals a paralyzed person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 9:1-8; Luka 5:17-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Ta ludèupèri lod'o, ta b'ale rike Yesus la Kapernaum. Ta menyèla ke ne lii pa rai na ène, ta nèi ke Noo pa èmu.<bt>After passing several days, Yesus then went again to Kapernaum. And was (impersonal construction) told everywhere that He was already at the house.</bt><v n="2" />Ta dèka ke ne dèu do rihi ae ti mii-mii. Bèra huke-huke ne d'ara èmu ne hape la tele. Ta pika ke ri Yesus pa roo ne lua do d'èi Deo.<bt>And many people came from everywhere. They crowded around until they were crowded-tight in the house. To the point that in.front of the door also was already crowded-tight. After that, Yesus told them, God's will. [NOTE: "about God's will" is a very broad way of saying "talk about the things of God"]</bt></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\thruRoof.jpg" rtfFormat="textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Pa d'ara nga pedai lii ko Yesus, ta dèka ke do èpa dèu nga meree he dèu do red'o ta èbe nga Yesus.<bt>While He was still talking, there were four people came carrying a paralysed person to take him to Yesus.</bt><v n="4" />Ri do bèra huke-huke ke ne dèu, d'ai d'o ke roo ta ègo ne dèu ne nga Yesus. Ta ha'e ke roo la dèni èmu, j'e lebo ne dèni èmu pemira nga Yesus. Ta boo ne dèni èmu nee, ped'ule ke ri roo ne do red'o ne pa d'ara dèpi merèi noo.<bt>Because there were already too many people, they could not bring that person to Yesus. Then they went up to the top/roof of the house, and tore.apart the roof right/exactly above Yesus. When the roof was open, they lowered him on his mat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krabatton: The mat was the sick"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">krabatton: The mat was the sick man's, not a mat that happened to be in front of Jesus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne dèpi merèi noo do tao ngati b'ara do rui.<bt>His mat was made from strong material.</bt></note><v n="5" />Ta ngède ri Yesus ne j'èga roo, ta toi ke ta do parahaj'a tèra roo pa Noo. Ta lii ke Yesus pa do red'o nee, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ana Yaa ee! Èla ke ri Yaa pe pehuba ne hala-ludèuèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw what they were doing (lit. their work), He knew they really *believed in Him. Then Yesus told that paralysed person, saying, &lt;&lt;My child [=affection]! I have already *forgiven2 your *sins (doublet)!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Pa ène era lema do mejèd'èido pèri dèu guru agama Jahudi. Ta d'ai ri roo ne rènge ne lii pedai Yesus, mèd'èid'o pa d'ara ade roo.<bt>In that place were also sitting several Yahudi religious teachers. When they heard what Yesus had said, they felt not satisfied/happy inside their hearts (livers).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;in their hearts&quot; would be overkill"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">"in their hearts" would be overkill for Pidgin, though it's sayable</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ta pedai ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ani tèra Noo ta pedai mi nahii! Deo we miha do nara ta pehuba hala-ludèudèu. Lii pedai Noo d'ee, ta paha èni Noo ta hela'u nga Deo. Èla ke ri Noo pekare Deo!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then they said.to.each.other saying, &lt;&lt;He is very bold talking like that! It is only just God, who can *forgive2 people(s) *sin (doublet). What He has said, just makes himself the same with God. He has slandered/blasphemed God!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paha èni = ?? menonjolkan diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">paha èni = ?? menonjolkan diri</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01689b.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Tapulara toi ri Yesus nengaa ne do pa d'ara pengee roo. Ta lii ke Noo pa roo, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ke muu ne pengee mi nahère?<bt>But Yesus already knew what was inside their thinking. Then He told them, &lt;&lt;Why do you-pl think like that?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneumati: could say &quot;inside his spirit&quot;,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">pneumati: could say "inside his spirit", but it isn't as meaningful as "inside". Same thing for "inside yoa heart".</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Na mii do rihi memud'e pedèue pengee muu? Ki pali Yaa, pa do red'o na ène, &lt;Èla ke ri Yaa pe pehuba ne hala-ludèuèu, &gt; toi d'o ri muu ta do tajad'èi we ad'o. Tapulara ki pali Yaa, &lt;Kèd'èiwe! Lule ne dèpi èu, j'e b'ale.&gt; Ki kèd'èid'ènge noo, toi tèra ke ri muu, ta Yaa do nga kuaha nga higa ta pehuba hala-ludèudèu. Ri Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Which is easier according to your thinking? If I say to this paralysed person saying, &lt;I have already *forgiven2 your-sg *sin(s) (doublet),&gt; you-pl don't know if that happens, or not. But if I say, &lt;Get.up [imperative]! Roll up your mat to go.home!&gt; If he gets up immediately, only.then will you-pl truly know that I has *power/authority and *right to *forgive2 people's *sins (doublet). Cuz I here, am the *True Human.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CALON: dèu mola-mira (lurus, tidak cacat)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">CALON: dèu mola-mira (lurus, tidak cacat) ; dèu tèra-tèra (truly = ambig.) ; melaa ihiwue = pure gold (not mixed) ; dèu rai-wawa kuaha (but also used for market tricksters) ; dèu rai-wawa do keteme ; dèu rai-wawa ihi ; dèu rai-wawa do petuu-petuu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Na mii do rihi memud'e ne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Na mii do rihi memud'e ne tada muu Na mi do rihi memud'e ne pali, pehed'apa nga dèu do red'o nane, &lt;Ne lub'u hèrro èu èla ke pe pehuba&gt;, we lii ta &lt;kèdd'i we j'e lule ne dèpi èu j'e kako/b'ale?&gt; Mij'i ta ketèra pa muu ta Yaa ke ne Ana Dèu rai-wawa donga kuaha ta pehuba lub'u hèro dèu.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(9)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta lii ke Yesus pa dèu do red'o nee, mihe ane,<bt>After that also, Yesus told that paralysed person, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="compare Matthew 9:5-6."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">compare Matthew 9:5-6.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />&lt;&lt;D'èno ee! Ie ke èu! Kèd'èiwe, lule ne dèpi èu, j'e b'ale.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-sg listen é! Now you are *healed! Get.up, roll.up your mat, then go.home [+imperative].&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta rènge ri noo ne lii Yesus, ta kèd'èid'ènge ke noo. Èbe ne dèpi noo, j'e pekèd'e. Ngède ri namada hari-hari dèu do era pa ène. Ta madalae ke roo harièle. J'e lii, &lt;&lt;Wee! Ngèdi ded'o di ta pehapo nga lai do mi nahee. Tèra-tèra ne kuaha Deo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, he immediately got.up. And he picked.up his mat and left. All the people there saw with their very own eyeballs. And they all were amazed (open-mouthed). Then saying, &lt;&lt;Wee! [+positive amazement]! Only now have we-ex ever seen anything like this. Truly this is the power of God!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mada = ?? mata"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mada = ?? mata</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pedoe Lewi ta pedèue Noo<bt>Yesus calls/summons Lewi to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 9:9-13; Luka 5:27-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta b'ale rike Yesus la ngidi èi lobo Galilea. Ae ne dèu do dèka la pe'abu nga Noo, j'e pepeke ri Noo ne lua d'èi Deo pa roo.<bt>And so after that, Yesus went again to the edge of Galilea lake. Many people came to meet Him, and He told them God's will.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00309C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Mone hèmi doi b'ea<bt>A person collecting taxes</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Pa ène, era he dèu ne ngara noo Lewi, ana ri Alpeu. Noo, do j'èga pa era ma'i b'ea unu do pereda Roma. Pa d'ara nga nèru Yesus j'ara ène, ta ngède ke ri Noo Lewi. Ta lii ke Yesus pa noo, &lt;&lt;Ama ee! Mai ma pedèue Yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that place, there was a person named Lewi, Alpeu's child. He worked at a place for paying tax to the Roma government. Just as Yesus walked by there, He saw Lewi. And Yesus said to him, &lt;&lt;Child, ee! Come and follow Me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta rènge ne lii pedoa Yesus, ta kèd'èid'ènge ke Lewi, j'e pedèue Noo.<bt>Hearing Yesus summons, then Lewi got.up and followed Him straightaway.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Èla pe na ène, Yesus he mejèd'èita nga'a pa èmu Lewi, hela'u nga ihianga Lewi do mone hèmi doi b'ea he. Pedèuu petèka pengee do Jahudi, ae kera'a dèu do muri mada pa d'ara apa, do mejèd'èita nga'a hela'u nga Yesus. Ae ti telora roo do mejèd'èita nga'a hela'u, do d'èi ta d'èno ne lii pedai Yesus.<bt>So after that, Yesus (collective) were sitting eating at Lewi's house, together with Lewi's friends who habitually collected tax. There were also other people whom the Yahudi people considered people living in evil ways, who were sitting eating with Yesus. From those people who sat eating, there were many who liked to listen to Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pa d'ara awe nga mejèd'i ta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Pa d'ara awe nga mejèd'i ta nga'a Yesus he pa èmu Lewi, ae lema ne ihianga Lewi do mone hèmi b'ea he do dèka la nga'a hela'u nga roo. Pedutu petèka pengee do Jahudi, mone hèmi b'ea he dèu do muri mada do apa, do nga'a kuka unu dèu. Pa telora roo do mejèd'i ta nga'a he, ae ne do mengèlu d'ara ta d'èno ne lii pedai Yesus.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the eyes of the pharisaical. Even in Galilee of the Gentiles, people who associated with non-Jews were considered second class Jews. It isn't a matter of them actually sinning or being bad people; they were just religious outcasts as the religious leaders defined it. Verse 16 mentions them too, and 17 mentions the outcasts. eekolouthoun: they were tagging along (not "plenny peopo" but a crowd of the wrong kind of people who were curious about Jesus and wanted to see more).<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Pa awe na ène, era do pèri dèu guru agama ti kejie Parisi he, do ngède Yesus mejèd'èita nga'a hela'u nga mone hèmi doi b'ea, nga dèu do muri mada pa d'ara apa he. Ta keb'ali ke roo pa ana aj'a Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa Guru muu ne nga'a hela'u nga mone hèmi doi b'ea he, nga dèu do muri mada pa d'ara apa he?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there were several religion teachers from the Parisi party/group, able to see Yesus sitting eating with those who habitually collect tax, and those people who were living in evil ways. Then they asked Yesus' *disciples/students/taught underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Why is your-pl Teacher eating with those people who habitually collect tax, and with those people living in evil ways?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;odda kine peopo jalike dem&quot; in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">"odda kine peopo jalike dem" in Matthew. "Bad name jalike dem" may be better, since it is judgmental and reflects the Pharisees' viewpoint. It also leads into Verse 17 better, which the neutral term used in Matthew doesn't do. Matthew has "fo da odda kine peopo" in 9:13. Change?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Do rènge ri Yesus ne lii keb'ali roo, ta b'ale ke ri Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Dèu do pèd'a do paraluu dote, tapulara dèu do kehèdèu ad'o do paraluu. Ne dèka Yaa ta ma hewewe ne dèu do muri mada pa d'ara apa he. Ad'o dèka ta ma hewewe dèu do pengee ne muri mada noo ta do petuu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus heard their question. and He responded, saying, &lt;&lt;Sick people truly need a doctor, but well/healed people don't need. I came to take.care.of/arrange those people living in evil ways. I did not come to take.care.of/arrange people who already think their way of life is right/correct.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ad'o ma pemane nga dèu do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ad'o ma pemane nga dèu do mola do mira/mèu??, tapulara nga dèu do do muri mada pa d'ara lub'u hèro nga menyilu (do apa do ked'aha he.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii aj'a Yesus wala ngati lii aj'a do Parisi he<bt>Yesus' teachings are different from the Parisi people's teachings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 9:14-17; Luka 5:33-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Pa d'ara he wari, dèu ti kejie agama Parisi pa d'ara puasa. Ngèdi ri roo, ana aj'a Johani, mone peherani dèu, do puasa lema. Tapulara ngèdi d'o ri roo ne ana aj'a Yesus he ta do puasa mi roo le. Ta kako ke roo la pe'abu nga Yesus, j'e keb'ali, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama. J'ii he pa d'ara puasa. Mi nahère lema, ana aj'a Johani he. Ta ngaa ke ne ana aj'a Èu ku dod'o puasa?&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, people from the religious Parisi group were *fasting (loan). They saw the *disciples of Johani the One.who.habitually Baptizes were also fasting. But they didn't see Yesus' *disciples fasting like them. Then they came to meet with Yesus and asked saying, &lt;&lt;Father. We-ex are fasting. Johani's people also are fasting. Why aren't Your *disciples fasting?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puasa ; laj'u èni = mogok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">puasa ; laj'u èni = mogok makan (mara sang bini, atau masalah lain) ; le = short for lema</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Toi ri muu, ki era rame peloko nga'a, do pedoa he puasa d'o, tapulara nga'a tade b'èhu. Kiri mone peloko nga'a ne do era ko, nga'a-nginu mengèlu d'ara hela'u roo harièle.<bt>And Yesus replied, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl know, that if there's a marriage feast, the guests don't fast, but they eat until.satisfied/full. If the groom is still there at the feast, of course they all eat together having.a.good.time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="momone do peloko nga'a = groom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">momone do peloko nga'a = groom (Dimu) ; mone peloko nga'a = groom (Seba)</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ki jad'èi he ne lai, ne mone peloko nga'a nee, mahido ri dèu, j'e èbe perai, pa awe na ène ke, ne ihianga noo ne hedèu pengee, j'e'itu puasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>If later at some time, it happens that other people arrest/kidnap that groom and take him away, at that time his friends will feel in.a.state.of.difficulty, only.then will they will fast.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ta wie rike ri Yesus he èhi ne lii pehèku, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ule d'o dèu do kelapu b'ara do mèje ri b'èla do wiu. Ki d'ai ne b'ahe, kepud'u ne b'èla do wiu nee, juu mehiu ne b'ara na ène.<bt>Then Yesus gave another *parable (example), saying, &lt;&lt;People don't patch and sew new cloth on old shirt. Cuz when it's washed, that new cloth will shrink and.so make that old shirt torn even more.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ask a woman if this makes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Ask a woman if this makes sense.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Mi nahère lema, b'ule d'o dèu do hali dèu la d'ara haba wo mèje. Tatu ta boo ne haba nee, j'e huti harièle ne dèu la rai. Hèku, dèu do wiu, do tatu ta hali pa d'ara haba do wiu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Similarly, people don't fill new palmwine in a fragile/decayed leaf.pail.for.collecting.palmwine. Cuz that pail will certainly break, and that palmwine seep.out wasted. So therefore, new palmwine must be poured into a pail that is new.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne do b'uke pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani, lii ta b'ole ihi èi ago do wiu pa d'ara haku do tao ti kuri b'ada do dèu, mij'e ta dod'o mehèri j'e mehèka.<bt>Original Greek language Bible writes don't fill grape juice that is new/fresh in an animal skin bag that is old, so.that it doesn't break and.so tears.</bt></note>(Mi nahère ke, lii aj'a Yesus do wowiu, b'ole pekiwo nga lii aj'a do dèu do unu do Parisi).<bt>(Like that Yesus taught them saying his new teaching, shouldn't be mixed with the Parisi people's old teaching.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="haku = saku ; èi ago"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">haku = saku ; èi ago =air anggur ; mehèri = tarobek panjang ; mehèka = pecah ; hali = ?? po'a</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana aj'a Yesus he g'ètu are-gandèu pa lod'o pengaha ihi<bt>Yesus' *disciples pick wheat-grain on the *Sabbath2 (stop work day)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 12:1-8; Luka 6:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Pa d'ara he wari, pa lod'o heb'aj'a do Jahudi, ta lake ke Yesus j'ara ngidi maa gandèu. Ta g'ètu hidèuke ne wuri gandèu ri ana aj'a Noo, j'e nga'a.<bt>One time, on the *Sabbath1 (Yahudi people's worship day), Yesus was walking on the path through/by the wheat-grain fields. And His *disciples were breaking.off wheat and eating it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wuri = ?? grainhead"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wuri = ?? grainhead</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 23:25</note><v n="24" />Do ngèdi ne tao roo ri do Parisi he, moko ta lii ke roo pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ne ana aj'a Èu ne pèga lua petèka pa d'ara agama dii? Roo he, do g'ètu are-gandèu pa lod'o pengaha ihi. Ad'o muu do j'èma ta tao mi nahère!&gt;&gt;<bt>The Parisi people saw it, then they told Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;Why are Your-sg disciples violating our-inc religious regulations? They are breaking.off wheat grain on the *Sabbath2 (work stop day). You-pl may not do like that!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="g'ètu = ketu ; hidu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">g'ètu = ketu ; hidu = copot ;; 24:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00099C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Are-gandèu<bt>Gandum grain</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi na mii, we? Hewina d'oke muu nengaa ne do tao ri Dau? Pa awe na ène, Abyata ne do jad'èi Kètu Mone Ae agama. Ta d'ai Dau nga harièle dèu lere noo, hèpo èle ri menganga. Ta maho ke roo la d'ara Leo Heb'aj'a pa Deo, la èbe ne roti do èla pe petale ri kètu agama he tuu Deo, j'e nga'e ri roo. Ne petuu he, roti na ène, nga'e ri kètu agama he we, ie d'o ta nga'e ri dèu do hewala. Maji lema ta nga'e ri Dau he, b'ule d'o he dèu he do lii ta do hala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;So how is it, ve? You-pl don't remember that story about Dau? At that time, Abyata was the *high priest (Top Head of the religious leaders). Dau and all his follower's stomachs were strumming (with hunger like a musical instrument) with hunger. Then they entered into *God's *tabernacle (Worship Tent), in.order.to take that bread that the *priests had already given to Lord, then they ate it. In fact, it was only just the priests who were allowed to eat that bread, but other people were not allowed to eat it. Then Dau mob ate it, but there was not one person who *accused/condemned them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kètu mone ae pa d'ara agama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kètu mone ae pa d'ara agama = KT high priest ; Leo Heb'aj'a pa Deo = KT tabernacle ; ie d'o = tidak baik, tidak boleh</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nga harièle dèu do lere noo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nga harièle dèu do lere noo</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The point is not just that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">The point is not just that David and his ate the special bread, but that the action is not condemned by Scripture even though it broke the letter of the law.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Semue 21:1-6; Kètu Agama nga Lua Petèka Agama 24:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ta lii rike Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole bèlo ri muu, ne pe'era ri Deo ne lod'o pengaha ihi natuu ta wie ne mèngi pa dii, dèu rai-wawa. Tao d'o dii dèu rai-wawa ri Deo, tuu ta ma pedèue lua petèka-kewèhu lod'o pengaha ihi we.<bt>And Yesus told them again saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl shouldn't forget that God made the *Sabbath2 (work stop day) to give a *blessing, to us-inc humans. But He didn't make us-inc humans in.order.to only just follow the regulations (doublet) of the *Sabbath2.</bt><v n="28" />Yaa ke na d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu. Yaa ke na d'ee, do nga higa ta lii pa dèu ta j'èga, ki ad'o b'ole j'èga, pa lod'o pengaha ihi.&gt;&gt;<bt>I here, am the *Ideal/Prototype Human. I am the one who has the right to say humans may work or may not work on the *Sabbath2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèngi = berkat, untung ; lua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèngi = berkat, untung ; lua kewèhu = syarat, yg disimpulkan ; tuu ta ma = cuma , hanya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is talking about himself. Is this clear? "Lord" is a relation to people, not to a time period. The relation to the day has to be spelled out more, because "Boss" does not collocate that way.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie dèu pa lod'o pengaha ihi<bt>Yesus heals a person on the *Sabbath2 (work stop day)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 12:9-14; Luka 6:6-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Èla pe na ène, ta maho rike Yesus la d'ara èmu heb'aj'a. Pa ène, ta ngède ke ri Noo, he dèu do made ne kae-nga'a helaa.<bt>After that, Yesus entered again into the *synagogue (worship house). There He saw a person whose arm on one side was dead (not functional).</bt><v n="2" />Pa ène lema, era do pèri dèu do kale lai ta pehale Yesus. Ta pehod'e hudi-hudi ke Noo ri roo, ngee-ngee ta pe'ie ri Noo ne dèu do pèd'a na ène pa lod'o pengaha ihi nee.<bt>There, there were also several people who kept looking for a way to *accuse/condemn Yesus. Therefore they continually scrutinized him, because they wanted to know if He would heal that person exactly on the *Sabbath2 or not.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="helaa = sebatang, selengan; 2: ngee-ngee"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">helaa = sebatang, selengan; 2: ngee-ngee = jangan sampai ; pehod'e = ?? maloi ; hudi-hudi = ?? sedikit2</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ta pedoe ke ri Yesus ne dèu do made ne kae-nga'a helaa nee, j'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mai ma titu ma hed'apa d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus called that person who had the dead arm on one side, saying, &lt;&lt;Come.here so you-sg to stand in front here.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="titu = berdiri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">titu = berdiri</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa roo harièle, ane Noo, &lt;&lt;Ki pedèuu lua petèka agama dii, nengaa leke do ie ta tao pa lod'o pengaha ihi? Tao ie, we tao apa? Ta pe'ie dèu dii, we ta pemade dèu?&gt;&gt; B'ule d'o he dèu he do boka ub'a.<bt>And He asked all those people, saying, &lt;&lt;If following our-inc religious regulations, what may we-inc do just on the *Sabbath? [May] we-inc do good, or do evil? [May] we heal people or, murder people?&gt;&gt; But they were all just quiet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leke = ?? saja"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">leke = ?? saja</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Pèd'a ne ade Yesus, heleo roo do rihi pekeb'ue lua petèka agama, nga dèu do made ne kae-nga'a helaa. Ta bubu d'ara ke Yesus, j'e kewèle ela heleo roo hari-hari. Ta lii ke Noo pa dèu do pèd'a nee, &lt;&lt;Pemole ne kae-nga'a èu do made ne!&gt;&gt; Ta pemole ke ne kae noo, ta ie d'ènge ke.<bt>So then Yesus' liver was in a very difficult state, because they were more valuing their regulations, than that person whose arm one side was dead. So he got.angry and.so glared all around at them. And then He told that sick person saying, &lt;&lt;Stick out your-sg arm (imperative)!&gt;&gt; He stuck out his arm, and it was immediately well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch out the paralyzed fingers, or just extending the hand and arm.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ta mèhu èni ke harièle ne do Parisi he ti d'ara èmu heb'aj'a nee. Ta la pelii ke roo nga dèu ti paratei Herode, ta kale ruj'ara ta pemade Yesus.<bt>After that, those Parisi people went outside leaving that worship house. And they plotted with people from the (political) party of Herode, to find a way to kill Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kewèle = pe'e mata; 6: pelii"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kewèle = pe'e mata; 6: pelii = sekongkol</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Healing itself was not the issue;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Healing itself was not the issue; details of the Law were. This is implicit in the Greek, but not accessible in Pidgin. The "Herodians" were a political group. Herod was a very unpopular king, but some people backed him because he was generally a winner.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ae ne dèu do pèd'a do pe'ie ri Yesus pa ngidi èi lobo<bt>Yesus heals many people at the edge of the lake</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7-8" />Pa d'ara hewari, ta lari èni ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo la ngidi èi lobo Galilea. Pelai ta do toi ke, ri dèu lowe nengaa ne do èla petao ri Noo, ri mi nahère ae ne dèu do dèka ngati harièle rae-kowa, la pedèue Noo. Era do dèka ti propensi Galilea, propensi Yudea, nga ti propensi Idèuea. Era lema had'e do dèka ngati kota Yerusalem, kota Sidon, nga ti kota Tirus. Era lema do wala, do dèka ti bara dimu loko Yarden. Harièle roo dèka ta la pe'abu nga Noo.<bt>One time, Yesus and His *disciples retreated/moved to lake Galilea's edge. But, because so many people had already heard what he had done, that is why many people came from various villages to follow Him. They came from Galilea province, Yudea province, and Idumea province. There were other people who also came from Yerusalem city, Sidon city, and Tirus city. And there were also other people who came from the east side of the Yarden river. They all were seeking to RECIP-meet with Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eekoloutheesen: not necessarily &quot;followed by boat.&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">eekoloutheesen: not necessarily "followed by boat." The place all these people ended up was "by the lake," however they got there</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Pelai ta rihi ae ne dèu, ta lii ke Noo pa ana aj'a Noo, ta pemoke hewue kowa natuu Noo. Ne d'èi Noo ta pedai lii ti ra kowa, mij'e ta rèngi roo, lema mij'e ta ngèd'e Noo ri harièle dèu.<bt>Because there were so many people, to-point-that Yesus told His *disciples to prepare a boat for Him. He wanted to talk.back.and.forth from the boat, so they all could hear, and also see Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lari = pindah ; bara dimu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lari = pindah ; bara dimu = sebelah timur, arah timur.; 9: ra &lt; d'ara ; pelèg'a èni = bekin longgar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mij'e ta nara Noo ta mejèd'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mij'e ta nara Noo ta mejèd'i pelèg'a èni ne</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Do uru, ae dèu pèd'a do pe'ie ri Noo. Ri mi nahère ke, ae ne dèu pèd'a do dèka la perub'i ta tade d'ae ta b'uje Noo.<bt>Before, He had healed many sick people. That is why now all the sick people came pushing.their.way.forward wanting to touch Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion; it's not a perfect, so "befo time" is probably wrong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ma'u 4:1, Luka 5:1-3</note><v n="11" />Ta ngède Yesus ri dèu do maho ri wango he, ta dèka ke roo la mejura pa hed'apa Yesus. J'e pekaa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Tèra-tèra Èu ke, ne Ana Deo nee!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the people whom the evil spirits had entered saw Yesus, they came and prostrated themselves in front of Yesus. And then they shouted saying, &lt;&lt;You here are indeed God's Child!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Tapulara ta lara made ke ri Noo pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ole pedai muu nga dèu, ta nadèu Yaa na d'ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>But he strongly forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell people who I am!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lèba = palang, halangi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lèba = palang, halangi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pid'èido henguru do d'ue ta jad'èi ana aj'a Noo<bt>Yesus chooses twelve people to be his *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 10:1-4; Luka 6:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ta èla pe na ène, ta ha'e ke Yesus la hewue lede. Ta pedoa ri Noo do pèri dèu do mèd'èipa Noo. Ta dèka ke roo nga Noo.<bt>And then Yesus went up a mountain. He called several people who fit/matched Him. And they came to/with Him.</bt><v n="14" />Ta pid'èike ri Noo, do henguru do d'ue. J'e lii Noo pa roo, &lt;&lt;Ne pid'èimuu, mij'e ta pedèue loro-loro Yaa. Ta pejuu muu ri Yaa, ta la pepeke ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo pa hari-hari dèu.<bt>Then he designated/chose twelve people. He said to them, &lt;&lt;I choose you-pl to follow Me continually. I also want to order you to go tell God's Good News to all people.</bt><v n="15" />Ta wie ri Yaa pa muu ne kuaha, ta hud'èiwango ti d'ara dèu he.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I will give *power to you-pl, to expel *evil spirits from people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16-19" />Ne do henguru do d'ue he, ne ngara roo nahee:<bt>Those twelve people's names are like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Himo (do pehune ne ngara ri Yesus, ta Petu),<bt>Simon (who Yesus also gave the name Petu),</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehune ne ngara = kasi nama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehune ne ngara = kasi nama</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">J'ako,<bt>J'ako,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Johani, (J'ako nga ari noo Johani, hela'u ta ana ri Sebedeu. Ne ngara roo d'ue do pehune ri Yesus, &lt;Boanerge&gt;, pa d'ara lii rai dii &lt;mi d'oro&gt;.)<bt>Johani, (J'ako and his younger-sibling Johani, are both Sabadeu's children. Yesus gave a name to the two of them &lt;Boanerge&gt; its meaning &lt;like thunder&gt;.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lua pej'ara = arti , makna"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lua pej'ara = arti , makna ; wue had'a = sifat ; kedèru = bunyi besar ; lii j'ege = masparak ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="violent disposition, bombastic, calling down fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">violent disposition, bombastic, calling down fire on people (which fortunately God didn't send)</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16-19a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne do b'uke pa Alkitab lii rai Yunani, &lt;ana ri d'oro&gt;, ne hela'u mi, &lt;wue had'a mi d'oro&gt;. Pa d'ara pengee dèu do mèu d'ara he, ne lii pedai J'ako nga Johani do mi kedèru d'oro he. Ki ad'o, ne lii j'ege roo mi lii kedèru d'oro he.<bt>The Greek writing says &lt;thunder's child&gt;, and its meaning &lt;characteristic like thunder&gt;. Several smart people think that this J'ako and Johani their voices were loud like thunder. Or they liked to talk-angrily like thunder.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Anderia,<bt>Anderia,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pelipu,<bt>Pelipu,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bartolomeo,<bt>Bartolemeo,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mateo,<bt>Mateo,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Toma,<bt>Toma,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">J'ako (ana ri Alpiu),<bt>J'ako (Alpiu's child),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tadiu,<bt>Tadiu,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Himo (ti paratei Selot),<bt>Simo (from the Selot (political) party),</bt><note reference="3:16-19b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Partei Selot kale ruj'ara mij'e ta golo èni ti kuaha pereda Roma. Ngara roo do wala ta &lt;Patriot&gt;.<bt>This Selot party sought a way for them to be free/independent from Roma's government. And they also called them &lt;Patriot&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nga Juda Iskario (do mone pewie Yesus).<bt>and Juda Iskario (the one who *betrayed (sold away) Yesus).</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Guru agama pehale Yesus nga lii ta Yesus do hèmi kuaha ngati kètu wango<bt>The religious teachers *accuse Yesus saying it's *Satan who has given *power to Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 12:22-32; Luka 11:14-23, 12:10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ta èla pe na ène, ta puru ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo ti lede nee. J'e b'ale la d'ara èmu. Ta dèka rike ne dèu do rihi ae la pewore Noo, tade dod'o b'ule Yesus he nga awe kehoo ta nga'a.<bt>After that, Yesus and his *disciples went.down again from that mountain. And they returned to the house. Many people came crowding-around Him again, until Yesus (collective) no longer had time to eat.</bt><v n="21" />Ta toi ri roo mi nahère, ta lii ke roo, &lt;&lt;Heleo ko ri muu Yesus. Toi tala d'oke ne ngi'u Noo.&gt;&gt; Ta rèngi ri tuèhu Noo ta do mi nahère, ta dèka ke roo la èbe Noo.<bt>Seeing that, people said, &lt;&lt;Look at Yesus. He's forgotten to take care of himself.&gt;&gt; His family heard people talking like that, so they came wanting to take/escort Him away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'owe (Dimu) ~ pewore (Seba) ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'owe (Dimu) ~ pewore (Seba) = kerumuni; 21: tuèhu = saudara-saudara, keluarga, kerabat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether it was Jesus' family saying he was nuts, or if it was other people were saying it. It doesn't sound, however, as if it were the other people, who were quite enthusiastic about him. It was probably his family who were shamed by his being so prominent. There are other indications the family were upset, as in John when Jesus' brothers did not believe in him.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Pa ène, era lema guru agama do dèka ti Yerusalem, la pedai nga dèu pa ène, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;We! Muu he b'ole pedèue Yesus. Ne i'a Noo hud'èiwango, ri èla penara kuaha ti kètu wango, do tima ta pale ta Balsebuu.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time religious teachers from Yerusalem came to tell people there, saying, &lt;&lt;We! You-pl don't go following (=do what He says) Yesus. He can cast out evil spirits, because He gets power/authority from *Satan, whom people usually call Balsebuu.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 9:34, 10:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ta rèngi ri Yesus ne lii pedai roo, ta pedoa ke roo hari-hari, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Maho d'o la d'ara pengee dèu! Mi namii ne jad'èi kètu wango ne hud'e ngi'u noo miha!<bt>Yesus heard that, and He called all those people to say, &lt;&lt;That doesn't make sense! How can *Satan be able to expel his own self!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parabolee: here Jesus is not telling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">parabolee: here Jesus is not telling stories, but using concise examples to make a point. Stick with the intent to teach, not the means used to do it. "Satan" doesn't fly as a name. After discussion it always comes back to "Devil."<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Kiri pa d'ara hewue rai pereda, dèu rai do pana ta pemuhu, mi namii rai pereda na ène ne nara ta kako nga woie!<bt>If in a kingdom, its citizens are hot/angry to war/ be enemies with each.other, how can that kingdom keep going!</bt><v n="25" />Mi nahère lema pa d'ara hewue èmu, kiri harièle dèu pa d'ara èmu ne petadi ta pehala, mi namii d'ara èmu na ène ne nara ta titu nga woie.<bt>And similarly if the people of a household are all fighting and accusing each other, how can they still stand well!</bt><v n="26" />Mi nahère lema ke wango, kiri pemuhu roo nga roo, tatu ta menyèla kebali-bali!<bt>It's like that also, if evil spirits are RECIP-enemies with each other, surely they will break up and be destroyed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mi namii ne jad'i = indicate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Mi namii ne jad'i = indicate rhetorical question ;; 24: pemuhu = petadi = bermusuh ;; 25: peluku = baku rabe; 26: tatu -tentu ; kebali-bali = ancor-ancor, pica-pica ; petuku = fight (Seba)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction of the Devil, but the demise of his organization.<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>"going" is not the future auxiliary "goin", but the main verb "go gains" 'oppose' in the progressive.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Kiri era dèu do la boka èmu he dèu do rui, uj'e uru ko ne dèu na ène. Èla pe mi nahère, memud'e ke noo ne èba b'ara dèu nee.<bt>If a person comes to rob things from a strong person's house, he must first tie.up completely that person. Only after that can he easily rob/take that person's things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boka = bongkar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">boka = bongkar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="alla: alternative way of thinking about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">alla: alternative way of thinking about it. The rhetorical question has to be set up so the answer is clear, so the "no good" is needed to provide the context.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Hèku pedai Yesus mi nahère, nga lua pedèb'o ta pika mij'e ta toi ri roo Yesus ta do rihi kuaha nga kètu wango he, do tima ri roo ta pale, &lt;Balsebuu&gt;.<bt>In that way, Yesus told that He was stronger than *Satan, who they (impersonal) usually call &lt;Balsebuu&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta pika d'ènge Yaa pa muu: Deo do moko ke ta lonye ne hala-ludèudèu. Ki lua pe'apa ngara dèu he, Deo do ta pehuba ko ma ne hala-ludèuroo.<bt>So I'm telling you-pl directly: God is prepared to *forgive2 people's sins (doublet). And if a person speaks evil about other people, God still can *forgive1 their sins.</bt><v n="29" />Tapulara ki era dèu do b'ani ta pedai woapa j'ara lua Hengaa Megala Deo, nara d'o ta pehuba ri Deo ne hala noo, hape la lod'o namii-mii.&gt;&gt;<bt>But if there is a person who dares to speak evil about that *Holy Spirit of God's, God will not forgive1 that sin of his, even until forever!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lonye = cuci ; lua pe'apa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lonye = cuci ; lua pe'apa ngara dèu = fitnah orang; 29: kare menihe = fitnah (also widely used) ; hape la lod'o namii-mii sampai selama-lamanya ; pe'ape &lt; pe'apa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Harièle hala ludu, nga lii kara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Harièle hala ludu, nga lii kara menihi do ngèdi ta pali roo ana dèu rai-wawa, do ta pehuba ri Deo.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 12:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ne pedai Yesus mi nahère, ri èla ke roo pelii ta Yesus do èla pemaho ri wango.<bt>Yesus said that, because they had already said that Yesus had been afflicted by *evil spirit(s)</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dèu do j'ège ne lua do d'èi Deo, roo tèra ke ne tuèhu Yesus<bt>The people who obey God's will, they are Yesus' true family</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 12:46-50; Luka 8:19-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta dèka ke ina ri Yesus nga ari Noo he la èmu na ène, ta la pe'abu nga Noo. Ta titu ke roo pa tele, j'e pejuu dèu la pedoe Noo.<bt>After that, Yesus' mother and His younger.siblings came to that house, to meet with Him. There they just stood outside the house and.so told/ordered someone to go call Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ina ri Yesus ?? (why ri?)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ina ri Yesus ?? (why ri?) to contrast with construction ina Maria, implying Yesus is a woman</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Pa awe na ène, Yesus do mejèd'èipedai lii nga dèu lowe he. Ta la pika ke ne dèu pa Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama ee. Ina Èu nga ari Èu he, hei pa tele nee. Ne dèka roo ta ma pehapo nga Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus was sitting talking.back.and.forth with many people. Then the person told Him, saying, &lt;&lt;Father, ee! Your mother and younger.siblings are outside. They want to meet with Father.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hei = ada (yonder)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hei = ada (yonder)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Tapulara ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Nadèu ke, ne ina Yaa nga tuèhu Yaa do petuu ne?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied, saying, &lt;&lt;Who is My real mother and My kin/family?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ta heleo ke ri Noo ne dèu do mejèd'èipehero Noo, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Muu ke harièle nahee, ne ina nga tuèhu Yaa do petuu.<bt>Then He looked at those people who were sitting all.around Him. And spoke, &lt;&lt;You-pl all here, are My real kin/family.</bt><v n="35" />Nadèu we ne do j'ège ne lua do d'èi Deo, roo tèra ke ne tuèhu Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz whoever does according to God's will, they are My true family.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus wie lii pehèku j'ara wini do bui la ae kera'a wurai<bt>Yesus tells a *parable (example) about seed in various.kinds.of soil</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 13:1-9; Luka 8:4-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Pa d'ara hewari, ta kako rike Yesus la èi lobo Galilea. Ta dèka rike ne dèu do rihi ae la peworle Noo. Ta ha'e ke Noo la d'ara hewue kowa do penawo pa ène, j'e wie ri Noo lii aj'a pa roo. Harièle ne dèu do pa kolo lede d'èno ne lii aj'a Noo.<bt>One time, Yesus went again to lake Galilea. And very many people came crowding.around Him. So He went.up on top of a boat that was harboured/anchored there, in.order.to teach them. All those people on the land could hear His teaching.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wini = bibit ; liba ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wini = bibit ; liba = hambur ; worai ~ wurai = tana ; penawo = balabu ; pa kolo lede = (idiom) 1) mountain peak, 2) on land (as opposed to water)</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 5:1-3</note><v n="2" />Ae ne lii aj'a do wie ri Noo pa d'ara lii pehèku, mihe ane,<bt>Then He taught lots.and.lots to them using *parables (examples) saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />&lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu nga woie! Era he dèu do kako la liba wini pa d'oka noo.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl listen well/carefully! There was a person who went to broadcast seed (for planting) in his garden.</bt><v n="4" />Ta d'ai ne liba ri noo ne wini he, era do bui la d'ara ruj'ara. Dèka ne dolila he, la tutu pe èla.<bt>While he broadcast those seeds, there were some that fell on the path. Then birds came and pecked making them all.gone.</bt><v n="5" />Era wini do bui la wurai wowadèu Mèriai ne muri nga woie. Pelai ta do menii ne wurai,<bt>There was some seed that fell on rocky soil. That seed sprouted/lived fast. Because the soil was thin,</bt><v n="6" />ta d'èia lod'o, ta meraj'u d'ènge ke, j'e made. Ri ad'o do nara ta merèma ne d'ulu amo.<bt>when the sun came up, then they withered and died. Cuz their roots couldn't enter until deep.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rice is broadcast /liba/ di place"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rice is broadcast /liba/ di place to sprout ; uhu = botok (Setaria italica) in Sabu planted, not broadcast ; both men and women make holes and plant; 4: dolila = burung (generic) ; tutu = toto; 5: bunu = fall (Seba, not Dimu) = bui (used in both places) ; mèriai = cepat ; menii = tipis; 6: meraj'u = layu ; merèma = dalam ; d'ulu = masuk turun ; amo = akar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\sower.jpg" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Era lema had'e ne wini do bui la ro'a j'u'u ae. Tapulara hengèpe ri j'u'u he, j'e lara pod'o-pod'o i'a d'o wue-wila.<bt>There was some other seed that fell in the gaps of a stand of grass. But then those grasses squeezed killing ththem, to-point-that they were not able to have fruit/yield/produce.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are more like cockleburrs, and wouldn't grow up over a wheat stalk or stunt its growth. There are, however, several imported plants that take over native growth and strangle it ("choke" is used in discussions of this), and some can be referred to as "weeds."</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Tapulara era lema wini do bui pa wurai do woie. Muri roo nga woie, mengèru-merede tade era nga wue-wila. Ne wue roo, era do tèlu nguru wari lipa, era do èna nguru wari lipa, era lema do hengahu wari lipa.<bt>But there was some other seed that fell on good soil. Those seeds sprouted well, then they grew until they bore fruit. There were some bore fruit/yield of 30 times, there were some 60 times, and there were some others that were 100 times.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="had'e ~ hag'e koo = pohon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">had'e ~ hag'e koo = pohon duri (tall, dimakan) ; huki = pohon duri (tall) plants don't grow below them ; medera = tinggi ; hengèpe = ngapi ; lara pod'o-pod'o = kuning (dried up) ; wue-wila = berbuah-berbunga; 8: wubèha = pupuk ; mengèru-merede = subur</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Nadèu do nga d'èi ta d'èno, tenae pe woie, mij'e tada muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Whoever wants to listen1, listen2 thoughtfully so you understand/get the point!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tenae = ?? dengar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tenae = ?? dengar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naduu muu donga wodilu, do ie"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Naduu muu donga wodilu, do ie roo ta d'èno nga woie.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ta ngaa Yesus ku pake lii pehèku<bt>Why Yesus speaks using examples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 13:10-17; Luka 8:9-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Pa d'ara nga kiha miha Yesus, ta dèka ke ne do henguru do d'ue ana aj'a Noo, nga do pèri dèu do èla pe rèngi ne lii pehèku Noo. Ta ami roo ta peteleo ne ihi lii pehèku Noo.<bt>When Yesus was alone, those 12 disciples of His, with several other people had heard that teaching of His. They came and asked Him to explain the meaning of that parable/example.</bt><v n="11" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ri do d'èi tèra muu ta toi ne lua pereda Deo, ta peteleo ke ri Yaa pa muu ne ihi lii pehèku na ène. Tapulara pa dèu do hewala he, wie ri Yaa pa d'ara lii pehèku.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Because you-pl really want to understanding God's command/rule, I'll tell that parable's meaning to you. But for other people I just give *parables.</bt><v n="12" />Tuu roo ke, ne lua do èla peb'uke ri mone ub'a Deo, mihe ane,<bt>Those other people are like what God's *prophet1 (spokesperson) actually wrote saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kiha = sendiri ; miha ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kiha = sendiri ; miha = sendiri ; peteleo = menjelaskan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ngèdi ma ri roo, tapulara wae d'o ta tada.<bt>&lt;They have seen, but don't want to understand (the significance).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Rèngi ma ri roo, tapulara wae d'o ta oha.<bt>They have heard, but don't want to know/own it/possess it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="oha ~ unu = milik"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">oha ~ unu = milik</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Hani we roo mij'e ta d'o parahaj'a nga Deo,<bt>Leave/permit.it.like.that so.that that they don't believe God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mi d'o nara ta pehuba ne hala-ludèuroo ri Deo.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so.that the Lord doesn't have to *forgive their wrongs (doublet).&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: Implies that Jesus expected a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">hina: Implies that Jesus expected a negative outcome when he told stories to some people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus peteleo pej'ara lii pehèku j'ara wini do bui la ae kera'a wurai<bt>Yesus explains that seed *parable's meaning</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 13:18-23; Luka 8:11-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta peteleo ri Yesus ne pej'ara lii pehèku nee, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ki d'o tada ke muu pej'ara lii pehèku na ène, mi namii muu ne tada pej'ara lii pehèku do wala?<bt>After that then, Yesus explained that *parable's meaning, saying, &lt;&lt;If you-pl still don't catch this parable's meaning, how are you-pl going to be able to catch the meaning of other parables?</bt><v n="14" />Ne pej'ara noo, mi nahee: dèu do liba wini nee, hela'u mi dèu do pedae-pepeke ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo.<bt>So it's meaning is like this: that person who broadcast those seeds, he's the same as a person who talks.repeatedly about God's Good News.</bt><v n="15" />Wini do bui pa d'ara ruj'ara, j'e tutu èle ri dolila, hela'u mi dèu do d'èno ne lii pedai Deo. Tapulara tui d'o, dèka ne kètu wango la èbe pe'èle lii pedai ne ti d'ara ade dèu na ène.<bt>That seed that fell on the path to-point-that the birds ate it all gone, the same as a person who hears God's news/words/message. But not long after then *Satan comes to snatch away that news from that person's liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil The figure of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil The figure of "take away the seed" loses the thread of the meaning. What the Devil is doing is not taking away seeds, he is removing the ability to assimilate the Word.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Wini do bui pa wurai do wowadèu hela'u mi dèu do d'èno, j'e hème nga mengèlu d'ara ne lii pedai Deo.<bt>The seed that fell on the rocky soil, is the same as a person who hears and.so receives God's news with a happy liver.</bt><v n="17" />Tapulara, muri d'o nga woie, ri ad'o do d'ulu amo. Ri mi nahère ke, lii pedai na ène eta d'o pa d'ara ade dèu na ène. Ki nara noo hedèu ri dèu do hewala, taga ri hème lii pedai na ène, ta hore d'ènge ke ri noo.<bt>But it doesn't grow well, because it doesn't take root. And.this.is.the.reason.why that news is not stored long in that person's liver. If/When other people make things difficult [for him], because he received that news, he straight away lets.go throws it away.</bt><v n="18" />Wini do bui pa ro'a j'u'u ae, hela'u mi dèu do d'èno lii pedai Deo.<bt>The seed that fell in the gaps in the grass, is same as a person who hears God's news.</bt><v n="19" />Tapulara, ri rihi noo ne petadi kale muri mada do gaa do kele'e pa rai-wawa na d'ee. Ri lai na ène ke, ne nyèke lii pedai Deo ti d'ara ade noo, ku b'ule d'o nga guna nengaa pa muri mada noo.<bt>But he is too busy with trying to find an excessive lifestyle. And all those things, push.aside God's news from his liver, to-point-that it no longer has any useful.function in his life.</bt><v n="20" />Wini do bui la wurai do woie, hela'u mi dèu do d'èno woie, j'e hème ne lii pedai Deo, j'e j'ège pedèue ne do d'èi Deo. Ta j'ège ri noo harièle lai do ie, mi wini do muri nga woie tade wue tobo kolo. Ne wue noo, era do tèlu nguru wari lipa, era do èna nguru wari lipa, era lema do hengahu wari lipa.&gt;&gt;<bt>That seed that fell in the good soil, is same as a person who listens well in.and receives God's news, and does according to God's will. Then everything he does is good, like that seed that grew well until it bore fruit/yield. There are some who have fruit 30 times over, some 60 times, and some that are even 100 times.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="use of ihi; 15: tui ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">use of ihi; 15: tui = lama ; tui d'o = sonde lama; 17: eta = tetap, menetap ; hore = buang; 19: keleru-keba'a = bimbang ; kaj'e = jangkau ; gaa = indah ; kele'e = gaya yg menyilau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="muri mada pa d'ara keleru-keba'a, d'èi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">muri mada pa d'ara keleru-keba'a, d'èi ta kaj'e ne muri mada do gaa do kele'e pa rai-wawa nane.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What it is that is being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">What it is that is being multiplied by 30, 60, and 100 isn't clear, and perhaps doesn't need to be.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lapu b'ole henèb'e ri hope<bt>Don't cover a lamp (generic) with a basket</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 8:16-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ta petuwe ri Yesus ngati d'ara kowa nee. Ta wie rike ri Noo hewue ne lii pehèku, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi namii! Ngèdi muu, we ad'o? Dèu do tunu lapu, j'e henèb'e ri hope. Ki ad'o tèke pa d'a'i era bèj'i. Ad'o, to? Ki mi nahère, teleo d'o. Ne tima dèu ta pejèd'èilapu pa era do d'èia, mij'e ta teleo.<bt>Yesus continued to speak from that boat. He gave one more *parable saying, &lt;&lt;How is it! Have you ever or not, seen a person light a lamp, and then cover it in basket? Or else put it underneath a bed! No, right? If it's like that, it doesn't shine. People normally put lamps in a high place so.that it can shine.</bt><note reference="4:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 5:15, Luka 11:33</note><v n="22" />Lai do d'o teleo dae, do ta peteleo ma hine. Lai do d'o toi dae ri dèu do na ène, do ta toi ma hine.<bt>Matters/things which are not yet clear/visible now, later will become clear/explained/shined on. Matters that people don't know now, later will be known.</bt><note reference="4:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:26, Luka 12:2</note><v n="23" />Nadèu do nga d'èi ta d'èno, tenae pe woie, mij'e tada muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Whoever wants to listen1, listen2 carefully so that you understand (the significance)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lapu = segala macam lampu, pelita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lapu = segala macam lampu, pelita also ; henèb'e = tutup, cover over ; petuwe = continue speaking ; tunu = bakar ; tunu lapu = light lamp (pelita only) ; pejèd'i = duduki, letakkan ; ketoe = gantung ; kelala = terang ; teleo = terang Clearer than kelala (both work for lamps); 22: pewuni = sembunyikan ; tengèle = terbuka</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\HK-LB\LB00148C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta pelore rike ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Pengee ko ri muu pe woie! Ruluji do pake ri muu, ta luji wue ai muri mada dèu do hewala, do ta pake ri dèu ta luji muu. Deo do ta luji lema muu mi nahère. Tapulara ruluji Deo do rihi mejèni.<bt>After that Yesus spoke again, &lt;&lt;Think carefully! If you measure/assessment another person's deed(s), people will also measure you-pl like that. God will also measure you-pl like that. But His measuring is even more heavy/severe.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pelore = sambung ; luji ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pelore = sambung ; luji = ukur, nilai (perbuatan) ; d'ahi = daci ; hèko medera = mengukur panjang ; wue ai = perbuatan</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 7:2, Luka 6:38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Hèku nadèu do nga lua d'èi tèra ta kale ne lua do d'èi Deo, juu mèu d'ara noo. Tapulara, dèu dod'o wae nga lua do d'èi Deo, juu b'od'o.&gt;&gt;<bt>if a person wants to really know the God's will, he'll get increasingly smarter/wiser. But if a person isn't at all concerned with the Lord's will, he'll get even dumber.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peb'uwe = tambahkan ; b'od'o ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peb'uwe = tambahkan ; b'od'o = bodoh ; rèpo = kikir</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 13:12, 25:29, Luka 19:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus wie lii pehèku j'ara wini do muri nga miha unu<bt>Yesus gives a *parable about seed that lives by itself</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta lii rike Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Rai pereda Deo juu worena, unupala mi wini do lebe ri dèu pa d'ara d'oka noo.<bt>And then Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;God's *kingdom1 keeps growing like a seed someone scatters in his garden.</bt><v n="27" />Ta èla pe lebe, ta b'ale ke ne dèu do oha ne la èmu la bèj'i nga d'o henge wari ne wini do lebe ri noo. Tapulara muri ne wini nee, juu kepai.<bt>And after he scatters it, that person goes.home to sleep and get.up doen't remember/think about that seed that he sowed anymore. But that seed continues to sprout and grow.</bt><v n="28" />Ne wini na ène, muri nga miha unu, j'e era nga rèu, ke hèb'a, tade wue-wila.<bt>Cuz that seed lives/grows by itself, starts to leaf, flower, to-point-that.it has.contents(fruit/yield).</bt><v n="29" />Kiri ihi ke, dèka ne do oha ne la g'èto noo. Mi nahère lema rai pereda Deo. Harièle nahère, do tao ri Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>If/when the grain is already ripe/full, the garden master/owner just knows to come to pick it. God's kingdom1 is also like that. All that work is done by God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="worena = besar, meluas ; kuj'e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">worena = besar, meluas ; kuj'e = tanam dlm lobang; 27: henèro = usahakan, piara ; liba = (jamak) &gt; lebe /liba + e/ (tunggal, vowel harmony @@); 28: janga = cabang; 29: ihi = masak, matang, siap dipanen ; pue = pick single fruit (mangga) ; hèb'a = ??</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus wie lii pehèku j'ara lua lamuhi woaj'u do rihi wo naiki<bt>Yesus gives a *parable about the (tree)seed2 that is very small</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 13:31-32, 34; Luka 13:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ta lii rike Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ne riko hewue lii pehèku j'ara lua dèu do unu Deo he. Petari rai, hudi we roo, tapulara juu tui, juu ae roo.<bt>After that, Yesus spoke again saying, &lt;&lt;I add one more *parable again like this. You-pl can compare God's people. They begin with just a few, but adding long.time, they add many.</bt><v n="31" />Hela'u mi lamuhi woaj'u do rihi wo naiki.<bt>That is like a (tree)seed2 that is very teeny-tiny.</bt><v n="32" />Kiri bui la wurai, muri noo nga woie, jad'èi aj'u ae. Ae dolila do dèka, la pehuri èni pa ro'a rame. Era lema do tao nyèb'u pa ène.&gt;&gt;<bt>If it has fallen in the ground (=been planted), it lives/grows to become a tree that is very big. And birds come seek shade. And there are some that make nests there.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lamuhi = biji (tree) ; rihi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lamuhi = biji (tree) ; rihi wo naiki = terlalu kecil ; wini = umum yg diusahakan manusia (so doesn't include things that grow wild); 32: kelai-kejanga = bacabang ; bibu-meragi = berkembang subur ; mengèru-merede = subur ; medeka = bertengger, dudu-dudu di atas dahan ; pemanga = bermain ; nyèb'u = sarang ; pehuri èni = berteduh diri di bawa sombar ; rame = sombar ; ro'a = di tengah-tengah, di cela-cela</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Mi nahère ke ne ruj'ara do aj'a ri Yesus pa dèu he, pedèuu nga lai tada roo.<bt>That [was] Yesus' way to teach them, according to their understanding.</bt><v n="34" />Ne tima Noo, aj'a dèu nga pake lii pehèku. Tapulara pa ana aj'a Noo, do pika mola ne pej'ara harièle lii pehèku.<bt>He usually used *parables if he taught them. But to His *disciples, He told them straight the full meaning of that parable.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pika mola = terus terang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pika mola = terus terang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pemilu-peketèna raga-opo<bt>Yesus calms (doublet) a noisy wind (=storm)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 8:23-27; Luka 8:22-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Jèna lod'o he, Yesus pa d'ara kowa ne ko. Ta lii ke Noo pa ana aj'a Noo, &lt;&lt;Mai we dii ma pekèd'èila heb'èka rai.&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was late.afternoon, Yesus was still on the boat. Then he said to/told his *disciples, &lt;&lt;Let us-inc sail/row to the other side.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pemilu = tenangkan ; peketèna ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pemilu = tenangkan ; peketèna = tenangkan ; raga-opo = angin ribut ; raga = angin besar ; opo = ?? (part of doublet) ; merango rai = evening, mulai gelap, 7pm ; merango = samar-samar ; mèd'a ne lod'o = 4-6pm ?? am?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ta ha'e ke roo la ra kowa nee, hela'u nga Yesus. J'e pekèd'èiroo, hani ne dèu do lowe he pa lahalae. Era lema do ha'e kowa do wala.<bt>After that they got.into the boat together with Yesus. And they left behind those many people on the shore/land. There were some who got.into other boat(s).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lahalae = ??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lahalae = ??</Message></Annotation><v n="37-38" />Awe na ène, ta èba ke Yesus nèlu, j'e bèj'i bilu pa wui kowa nee. Tui ded'o ne pekèd'èi dèka ne raga-opo. Wèbe ne kowa roo ri nawa, lale ri èi dae ta tobo. Hèku made ri meda'u, ne ana aj'a Noo he. Ta la peree ke Yesus ri roo, j'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Made ke dii! Kèd'èiwe! Hengee d'o ke j'ii ri Ama ki made j'ii.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time Yesus supported his head on a pillow and.so sleep soundly in the stern of the boat. Not much later then a noisy wind/storm came. Waves hit making water enter until it was almost full. So the *disciples were scared to death. Then they came to wake Yesus up saying, &lt;&lt;Father ee! We're about to die! Wake up! Father doesn't care if we-ex die!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèlu = alas kepala, bantal (kayu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nèlu = alas kepala, bantal (kayu, kapok, kapas) ; wèbe = pukul (ombak) ; nawa = ombak ; tube = pukul keras, datang satu-satu ; lale = masuk ; iga = hampir ; tobo = penuh ; peree = bangunkan ; ihilaka = celaka</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Wèbe nga tube ne kowa ne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Wèbe nga tube ne kowa ne ri kolo èi. Mèke d'oke ne d'obo èi, hèku lale la d'ara kowa roo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ta kèd'èike Noo, j'e j'ege ne raga-opo, &lt;&lt;Pehèngo èni!&gt;&gt; Ta pereda rike ri Noo pa èi lobo nee, &lt;&lt;Ketèna we!&gt;&gt; Ta milu d'ènge ke ne ngèlu. Ketèna ne èi lobo nee.<bt>He woke/got.up and scolded that wind/storm, saying, &lt;&lt;Quiet!&gt;&gt; After that He commanded that lake saying, &lt;&lt;Be calm!&gt;&gt; That wind straight.away stopped. The sea also was calm.</bt><v n="40" />Ta b'ani ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa muu harièle ku rihi meda'u? Parahaj'a d'o muu nga Yaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that Yesus scolded His *disciples, &lt;&lt;Why were you all afraid like that:? You-pl don't *believe in Me?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ege = bentak ; rii ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'ege = bentak ; rii = lagi, ulang; 40: b'ani = scold ; kelete</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Harièle roo ta hengodo ke, j'e meda'u, pedai roo, &lt;&lt;Nadèu ke Noo na d'ee? Hèku ne ngèlu nga nawa ped'èno nga lii pereda Noo!&gt;&gt;<bt>They were all afraid and amazed, also they spoke.to.each.other saying, &lt;&lt;Him here who is he? Even wind and waves also listen/obey him!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie he dèu do maho ri wango do ae<bt>Yesus makes well a person entered/afflicted with many *evil spirits</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 8:28-34; Luka 8:26-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Ta d'ai ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo la heb'èka èi lobo Galilea, la he èhi era, ne ngara noo Gerasa.<bt>And then, Yesus with his *disciples arrived at lake Galilea's other side, at a place named Gerasa.</bt><v n="2-6" />Pa ène, era he dèu momone do maho ri wango tade wuj'u. Ne era pee noo pa rai dare-rai dare. Mèd'a-nilod'o noo pekemale èni nga d'o b'ule b'ara pa ihi, pa kolo-kolo b'ojo pa ène, j'e pekaa-pekèra. Lema dede-wuhe ne ngi'u noo miha ri wowadèutade no'e. D'ai tèra noo ne rui, hèku b'ule d'o he dèu he do nara ta èke noo, maji lema ri rate b'èhi. J'aj'i wari ke ne uj'e ne kae-nga'a nga kae-j'èla noo. Tapulara pehèpo ne rate ri noo, lema pepade ri noo ne tuki b'èhi do pa b'eb'o noo.<bt>There there was a man who was entered/afflicted by *evil spirit(s) until he was crazy/insane. He lived in the graveyard. Night-day he meandered all around those hills stark naked yelling out over and over (doublet). He also beat wounding his body with rocks. He was really very strong, so there was no one who could tie him up, even with iron chains. People had already repeatedly bound his hands feet. But he severed that chain and also broke the iron bands from his feet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Muri Yesus = Tuhan Yesus ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Muri Yesus = Tuhan Yesus ; Deo ~ Yesus Muri di = Yesus yg kita muliakan ; w ~ v ; dèu pedutu = pengikut (ikut-ikutan, belum tentu mau terima ajaran); 6: (lèka [kena] /maho [masuk]) ri vango = 1st is temporary, 2nd is possessed ; Seba tidak membedakan antara bukait dan gunung, dua-dua /lede/; Dimu membedakan; 6: manga = bermain ; pekemale èni = walk himself around, wander ; kolo-kolo b'ojo = can be seen as hills in their entirety ; keula = telanjang (dgn tidak ada barang di badan) ; dede-tuke = angkat lempar (implies other people doing it)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mi nahère Yesus ne puru ngati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Mi nahère Yesus ne puru ngati d'ara kowa, dèka ke he dèu momone do wuj'u do pe pa keko (rai dare). Dèu do na ène, èke roo bèhi pada b'èhi, uje roo rate hèpo rate. D'ai rihi rui noo, hèku b'ule d'oke he dèu he donara ta kèpe noo. nga hio kepale ne ngi'u noo miha</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00303C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Dèu do wuj'u do maho ri wango<bt>A crazy man afflicted by evil.spirits</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mi nahère Yesus he ne puru ngati d'ara kowa, ta ngèdi ke roo ngati j'èu rowi do wuj'u na ène. Ta mèhu èni ke noo ti rai dare-rai dare nee, j'e perai la lèku rutuu pa hed'apa Yesus.<bt>When Yesus (collective) got.down from the boat, then that crazy person saw them from far. Then he exited from that graveyard, and he ran to kneel in front of Yesus.</bt><v n="7-8" />Mi nahère Yesus ne pehapo tangamada nga dèu na ène, ta lii ke Noo, &lt;&lt;Wango apa! Mèhu èni ti d'ara dèu na d'ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing that person's face like that then, Yesus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Evil spirit! Come out of this person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Noo ta lii ke ~ ta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Noo ta lii ke ~ ta lii ke Noo, but 2nd form preferred, 1st is awkward</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta pekaa ke ne dèu ne pemèdèumèdèu &lt;&lt;Ne dèka Èu na d'ee, ta ma tao ngaa ke pa yaa? Tade ma Èu ri yaa, ta Èu ke Yesus, Ana Deo do wiki higa nga kuaha. Ne huba yaa, b'ole ma wole yaa ri Èu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person yelled loudly, &lt;&lt;Your coming here, to do what with me? I know you-sg are Yesus, the Child of God who has the most rights and *power/authority. I request that You don't make.things.hard for me!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa noo, &lt;&lt;Nadèu ne ngara èu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked him, &lt;&lt;What's your-sg name?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta b'ale ke ri noo, &lt;&lt;Ngara yaa <span class="Italic">Legion, </span>rowi j'ii na he do rihi ae, mi tèb'a dèu horod'ad'u he!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person replied, &lt;&lt;My name is |iLegion,|r cuz we-ex here are very many, like thousands of soldiers!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ta pedide ke noo ri wango do pa d'ara noo he, mij'e ta ami pa Yesus ta b'ole hud'èiroo ngati era na ène!<bt>Then the evil spirits used that person to request that Yesus not to order them to leave that place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />J'èu d'o ti ène, era ke ne dèu do nga b'ata wawi do rihi ae. Era ma d'ue tèb'a ngi'u he. Ne wawi na hère pa d'ara nga kale nga'a pa keraha lede.<bt>Not far from there were people who watched one group of pigs. Approximately they are all 2,000 bodies. They were seeking food/feeding on the side of the mountain.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nyuu-nyuu = root around, but too"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nyuu-nyuu = root around, but too specific</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ta ami ke ne wango he pa Yesus, &lt;&lt;Pejuu we j'ii ta maho la d'ara wawi na hii.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then, those evil spirits requested Yesus, &lt;&lt;Order us-ex to go enter in those pigs there.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Era ma d'ue tèb'a = ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Era ma d'ue tèb'a = ma here functions as 'approximately'; 12: na hii = di sana (visible)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ta rèngi ne lii ami roo, ta wae ke Yesus. Moko ne wango he ta mèhu èni ti dèu na ène, j'e maho la d'ara wawi do na hère. Ta wuj'u ke ne wawi he j'e perai peb'igo-gale ti keraha lede nee, j'e maho la d'ara èi lobo, moko ta made bolo èi harièle.<bt>Hearing their request, then Yesus agreed. Then those evil spirits exited from that person, and entered into those pigs. Then those pigs ran and ran falling.over.each.other.in.confusion (doublet), from the side of mountain, falling into the lake, then they all died drowning there.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta ngède ne lai na ène, d'ai meda'u ke hari-hari ne dèu do b'ata wawi he. Ta perai ke roo la pepika pa d'ara rae d'ara kowa pa ène, j'ara lai do èla pejad'èi do lake ri roo. Ta dèka ke ne dèu do lowe he la heleo nengaa ne do èla pejad'èi<bt>Seeing that then those people who were watching those pigs were frightened. Then they ran to tell people all.around the different villages there. Then many people exited coming to go see what had happened.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run out of fear, seek safety, shun, avoid</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Ta kako ke roo la pehapo nga Yesus, era ke ne do wuj'u ne do mejèd'èipa ène. Do nga b'ara pa ihi ke, j'e do mèu d'ara ke noo. Ta ngède mi nahère, muri ne lua meda'u roo harièle, ri toi ke ri roo nadèu ne do nara ta hud'èiwango ti dèu do wuj'u nee, tèra-tèra ne mone ae kuaha Noo.<bt>They came meeting Yesus, and there was that person who had been crazy sitting there. He now wore clothing, and his insides were clear. Seeing like that then, those people all were afraid, because they knew, whoever could evict evil spirits from this person who had been crazy, he really truly was an powerful person.</bt><v n="16" />Ta ped'èii ke roo he dèu nga he dèu nengaa ne do èla pe ngèdi ri namada roo miha, j'ara lua dèu do èla pe'ie ngati wuj'u nee, nga j'ara lua wawi do made bolo èi he.<bt>Then they all tell from person to person what they had seen with their own eyeballs that crazy person healed/now.well, and how those pigs had died drowning.</bt><v n="17" />Ta dèka ke ne dèu-dèu ti rae-rae pa ène la ami pa Yesus ta pekèd'e ti rai roo.<bt>Then those village people there came asking so.that Yesus leave their land/country.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rowi toi ke ri roo naduu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rowi toi ke ri roo naduu ne do nga kuaha pa harièle lai do èla pe jad'i he.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ta d'ai Yesus ne ha'e la d'ara kowa, moko ne dèu do ie ngati wuj'u nee, ta ami pa Yesus mij'e ta pedèuu roo lema.<bt>When Yesus wanted/was.about.to go.up into the boat, then that person who was well from being crazy asked Yesus so.that he could also follow/go.along.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Tapulara wae d'o Yesus. J'e lii Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ale we èu la ped'èii pa a'a-ari èu harièle, nengaa ne do èla petao ri Deo tuu èu. Lema mi namii ne mone ae ruba Deo pa èu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus didn't want that. He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;You go.home to tell all your kin, what God has done for you. And how God loves/has.pity.on you very much.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="w = /w/ ; f ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">w = /w/ ; f = /f/ ; ~ v = /f/ ; b v w f</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="p t c k ' f"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">p t c k ' f s h = tak bersuara ; b d j g v z b' d' j' g' = bersuara</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ta b'ale ke noo, j'e la pedai-pepika la rai henguru b'ue kota, do tima lema ta pale &lt;Dekapolis&gt;. Pa rai na hère, ta pepika ke ri noo mi namii ne ruba Deo do tao ri Yesus pa ngi'u noo. Ta madalae ke harièle dèu do rènge lai na ène.<bt>And then, he went.home and went all.around a region with ten cities which is usually called &lt;Dekapolis&gt;. He narrated how God loved him by what Yesus had done for him. All the people who heard that story of his, they were amazed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pemure wari ana Yairu, nga pe'ie he dèu mobèni do d'o pengaha nara do ra'i<bt>Yesus makes Yairus' child live again, and heals a woman whose flow doesn't stop</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 9:18-26; Luka 8:40-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ta ha'e kowa rike Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo, j'e b'ale la heb'èka èi lobo nee. Ta d'ai roo ta puru ti d'ara kowa nee, ta dèka ke ne dèu lowe he la pewore Noo.<bt>And then Yesus and His disciples climbed back into the boat, and returned to the lake's other side. As they got down from the boat,many people came crowding around Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="CIE rai / ra'i / rahi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">CIE rai / ra'i / rahi</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Pa ène, era he dèu ne ngara noo Yairu. Noo, he dèu kètu èmu heb'aj'a pa rae na ène. Ta d'ai ta ngède ri noo Yesus, ta kako ke noo la lèku rutuu pa hed'apa Yesus,<bt>There, there was also a person named Yairu. He was head of *synagogue (worship house) in that village (broad sense). When he saw Yesus, then he came and knelt before Him</bt><v n="23" />nga lii huba, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ruba ko we ne d'ara Muri Mone, rowi ne ana yaa do mobèni do pemuri henguru d'ue b'ue tèu, nèi do pèd'a ta mate ne hengaa neke. Tulu ko we Ama ta la pe'ie noo.&gt;&gt;<bt>to request, saying, &lt;&lt;Please help, Sir, because my girl child who is just 12 years old, is sick awaiting her last breath (=about to die). Father please2 come to heal her.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="5:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne do b'uke pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani, &lt;&lt;Ruba kowe ne d'ara Ama ta la b'uje ne ngi'u noo mij'e ie ne pèd'a noo, j'e pee noo ta muri mada.&gt;&gt; Pa d'ara pej'ara dèu pa nii, &lt;&lt;ami ta la b'uje&gt;&gt; hela'u nga lii ta &lt;&lt;ami ruba d'ara ta pe'ie&gt;&gt;. Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani, ne pemuri ana mobèni nee do b'uke pa d'ara ayat 42.<bt>The Yunani Bible says, &lt;&lt;Father please come to touch her body, so.that she is healed from her sickness, and lives.&gt;&gt; For their way (of doing things), &lt;&lt;request to touch" meant the same as &lt;&lt;please heal&gt;&gt;. That young-girl's age, in the Yunani Bible is written in verse 42.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta kako ke Yesus penau nga Yairu la èmu noo.<bt>Then Yesus accompanied Yairus to go to his house.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rii = arus ; Seba &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rii = arus ; Seba &gt; Hèb'a (nama leluhur)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta d'ai roo ne pekèd'èi ae tèra ne dèu do pedèue Noo, hèku peb'èra-pewingi roo nga Noo ti heb'èka-heb'èka.<bt>But while they were walking, many people followed Him, jostling Him from side-to-side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'aa (Dimu) ~ yaa (Seba, Liae,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'aa (Dimu) ~ yaa (Seba, Liae, Mehara) ~ jo (Raijua) = 1t; 24: èu = 2t; 24: noo = 3t; 24: dii = 1ji; 24: j'ii = 1jx; 24: muu = 2j; 24: roo = 3j</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ta d'ai roo ne pekèd'i, ae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ta d'ai roo ne pekèd'i, ae tèra ne dèu do pedute Noo, hèku peb'ara-pewingi roo la heb'èka-heb'èka.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ti telora dèu do ae do na hère, era he dèu mobèni do d'o pengaha nara do ra'i helama henguru d'ue b'ue tèu.<bt>In the middle of all those people, there was a woman whose monthly period hadn't stopped for 12 years.</bt><v n="26" />Èla èle ke ne b'ara nga doi noo, ne pake ta ma'i pa dote-dote do la pe'ie noo. Tapulara b'ule d'o do nara ta pe'ie noo. La'a ta juu mejèni we ne pèd'a noo.<bt>She had spent all her money and all her possessions to use them pay for different.doctors to heal her. But none of them could heal her. That sickness of hers continued to recur (and get worse).</bt><v n="27-29" />Ne mobèni na ène, ae ke ne rèngi j'ara lua Yesus. Ta perub'i ke noo nga dèu do lowe he mij'e ta tade d'ae Yesus ti kej'unga. Ane pa d'ara pengee mobèni na ène, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Had'èita d'ae we ri yaa ta b'uje ne b'ara pa ihi Noo, ta ie ma ne pèd'a yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>That woman had heard alot about Yesus. So she was pushing.and.shoving in the middle of those many people so she could come close to Yesus from behind. She had been thinking, saying, &lt;&lt;If.only I can just touch the clothes on His body, I surely will be healed!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="; 26: peloko = care for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">; 26: peloko = care for (Seba), look after pos charms to see for the welfare of child (Dimu) ;; 29: j'ara lua Yesus = tentang Yesus ; ma = also (hope) ~ ke (more certain)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ambiguous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ambiguous</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00310C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mi nahère ri noo ne d'ae ta b'uje ne b'ara pa ihi Yesus, pengaha d'ènge noo ne nara do ra'i. Ta toi d'ènge ke ri noo ta do ie ke.<bt>Just as she touched Yesus' clothes, then that flowing blood of hers immediately stopped. She felt/knew she was truly healed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Pa d'ara awe do na ène lema, toi ri Yesus ta do era kuaha do mèhu èni ti d'ara ngi'u Noo. Ta b'ari èni ke Noo la kej'unga, j'e keb'ali pa dèu lowe he, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Nadèu muu do b'uje ne b'ara pa ihi Yaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Exactly at the time also, Yesus felt/knew there was power/strength/force that exited from His body. Then He turned back to face those many people, saying, &lt;&lt;Who among you-pl touched My clothes?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèti d'ènge ne raa do mili"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèti d'ènge ne raa do mili ngati d'èlu noo.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ti d'ara ngi'u = (power is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ti d'ara ngi'u = (power is seen to reside inside)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta lii ke ne ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Heleo we ri Ama miha. Mi nahee ma ke ne ae dèu do pewingi. Ta keb'ali ri ko Ama ta, &lt;Nadèu do b'uje ne b'ara Yaa?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>His *disciples spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;Father just look for yourself. This many people are obviously pushing.and.shoving each other. Then Father asks, &lt;Who touched My clothes?&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma ke = -lah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ma ke = -lah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Tapulara pee ma Yesus nga heleo peheru ta kale toi ta nadèu ne do èla peb'uje ne b'ara Noo.<bt>But Yesus kept.on looking all.around to find out who it was who had just previously touched Him.</bt><v n="33" />Ta rènge ne lii Yesus mi nahère, kerij'i-kerègu ne mobèni na ène ri meda'u. Moko ke noo ta la lèku rutuu pa hed'apa Yesus, j'e kelolo nengaa ne do tao ri noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Yaa ne do b'uje b'ara Ama ngine.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus speak like that, the woman was frightened. Then she knelt before Yesus and *confessed what she had done, &lt;&lt;Father! I'm the one who touched Father's clothes.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peb'uje = sonto"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peb'uje = sonto</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa mobèni do na ène, &lt;&lt;Pelai ti parahaj'a tèra ina pa Yaa, hèku ie ke ne pèd'a èu. B'ale we èu nga tunge-mengèlu d'ara.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to the woman, saying, &lt;&lt;Because mother truly *believes in Me, that.is.the.reason.why mama is healed of your sickness. Now, mama go.home with happiness (doublet) (polite imperative).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ana J'ae, = Vocative + Possessive;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ana J'ae, = Vocative + Possessive;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Pa d'ara nga pedai lii ko Yesus, ta dèka ke ne dèu pejuu ti èmu Yairu la pika pa Yairu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Èla ke ne ana èu pehèpo hengaa. B'ole pehedèu Ama Guru. Tenge d'oke Dokepai ne ta kako la nii.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus was still talking, then a person came from Yairu's house, to tell Yairu saying, &lt;&lt;(So.sorry), the girl child has breathed her last (+polite). Don't be troublesome for Father Teacher anymore. It isn't neccessary for ElderFather to go anymore.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hèku tenge d'oke ama Yairu ta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Hèku tenge d'oke ama Yairu ta pekewèlo Ama Guru.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ped'èno d'o Yesus nga lii pedai dèu do na ène. Ta lii ke Noo pa Yairu, &lt;&lt;B'ole hedèu ne pengee èu! Parahaj'a we èu pa Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus didn't take concern (pay attention) to that person's talk. So He said to Yairu, &lt;&lt;You trouble your thinking (=don't worry)!Believe/Trust in God.&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="37" />Ta pe'uru èni ke Yesus ti ana aj'a Noo do wala he. Tituwata Petu, J'ako nga ari noo Johani we, ne do èba pedèue Noo.<bt>Then Yesus walked ahead from his other *disciples. Except He brought Petu, J'ako and his younger sibling Johani, to follow/accompany Him.</bt><v n="38" />Ta d'ai roo la èmu Yairu, era ke ne dèu he do wiho-waho, era lema do tangi peloro èni do mèdèu<bt>When they got to Yairu's house, there were many people fussing around, and there were also some who were crying wailing in grief loudly.</bt><v n="39" />Ta maho ke Yesus la d'ara nee, j'e la lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ke muu ne pewiho-waho, nga tangi peloro èni mi hee? Naiki na ènead'o do made. Ne ta bèj'i hewe noo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus went inside,then spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl fussing and crying wailing in grief like this? This child isn't dead. She's only just sleeping.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'èno d'o = tidak dengar ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">d'èno d'o = tidak dengar ; ped'èno d'o = tidak mau hiraukan apa yg dia dengar; 37: ègu = èba ; èba pedute = implies J chose them ; if pedute only = implies they went along on their own</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Ta rènge ne lii pedai Yesus mi nahère, ta mare ta d'ole ke ri roo harièle.<bt>They heard Yesus' talk like that, then they all laughed at Him in scorn.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mare ta d'ole = laugh in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mare ta d'ole = laugh in scorn</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta pereda ke Yesus pa roo hari-hari ta mèhu èni la tele. Ta pedoa ke ri Yesus ne ina-ama naiki ne nga do tèlu ana aj'a Noo, j'e maho roo la kama naiki do made nee.<bt>Then Yesus ordered them all to exit outside. And Yesus called that child's mother-father, and His 3 disciples, and they entered into that dead child's room.</bt><v n="41" />Ta pèro ke ri Yesus ne wolaèba naiki nee, j'e pedai Noo pa d'ara lii rai Aram do pake pa ène, mihe ane, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Talita kum!&gt;&gt;</span> Ki pa d'ara lii rai di, &lt;&lt;Ana mobèni! Kèd'èiwe!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus held that child's hand, then He spoke in their Aram language, saying, &lt;&lt;|iTalita kum!|r&gt;&gt; In our language it means, &lt;&lt;Girl! Get.up!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01713b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.5cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Ta kèd'èid'ènge ke, ne naiki nee, j'e kako. Ta lii ke Yesus pa ina naiki nee, &lt;&lt;Wie ko noo nga'a!&gt;&gt;<bt>Unexpectedly/suddenly, that girl got.up and started walking. Then Yesus ordered the child's mother saying &lt;&lt;Give her something to eat!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Harièle dèu do ngède ne lai do èla pe jad'èi na ène, ta madalae ke roo. Tapulara, ta lara made ke ri Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ole la pedai j'e muu nga nadèu-nadèu ta do èla ke ri Yaa pe pemure wari noo!&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people who saw that that happen, they were amazed. But Yesus strictly forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell anyone that I have made her live again!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="naduu-naduu = sapa-sapa (they like this"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">naduu-naduu = sapa-sapa (they like this pronunciation for REDUP, but say singular is naduu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua nyèke Yesus pa Nasare<bt>Rejection of Yesus in Nasare</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 13:53-58; Luka 4:16-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Ta b'ale ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo la rae Noo, Nasare.<bt>Then Yesus and His *disciples went.home to His village Nasare.</bt><v n="2" />Huru-hapo lod'o na ène lod'o heb'aj'a do Jahudi. Ta maho ke Yesus la èmu heb'aj'a, j'e wie ne lii aj'a pa ène. Ae ne dèu do dèka la heb'aj'a pa lod'o na ène. Madalae harièle dèu do d'èno ne lii aj'a Noo. Pedai roo he dèu nga he dèu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mèu d'ara ti mii ke ne nara Dèu na d'ee? Lua pej'ara ti mii ne nara Noo? Mi namii Noo ne nara ta tao madalae?<bt>At the time it was the Jahudi people's *Sabbath1 (worship day). Yesus entered into the *synagogue (worship house) to give teaching there. That day there were many people who went to worship/pray. As they heard His teaching, they were amazed. And.so they spoke to each other, saying, &lt;&lt;How did this Person's knowledge get like this? How did He get His *power/ability/influence? How can it be that He can do amazing things/miracles?</bt><v n="3" />Tuka aj'u we Noo. Do tade ri dii, ina Noo, Maria; ne ari Noo he, J'ako, Jose, Juda nga Himo. Lema ne nawèni Noo. Harièle roo do rae dii!&gt;&gt; Ri do mi nahère, wae d'o roo ta hème Noo.<bt>He is only a carpenter. We know his mama Maria; and his younger.siblings, J'ako, Jose, Juda and Simo. He also has female siblings. We-inc all live togther in one village!&gt;&gt; This.is.the.reason.why they didn't want to accept Him anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="in title, emphasis is on penolakan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">in title, emphasis is on penolakan ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Maho d'o pa d'ara lua pengee"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Maho d'o pa d'ara lua pengee roo j'ara lua Yesus, hèku wae d'oke roo ta d'èno ne lii aj'a Noo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta pedai lii ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Do petuu ke! B'ale dii dèu, rihi pekeb'ue dèu pejuu Deo ti rai do wala, tapulara dèu pejuu Deo do pa d'ara rae miha, pekeb'ue d'o.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told, saying, &lt;&lt;It really is true! People like to give more respect to God's *prophet2 (delegated person) from other lands/countries/places, but to God's prophet2 in his own village there is no honour/respect.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="B'ale dii he = kalo kita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">B'ale dii he = kalo kita ini (opens a teaching)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="B'ale di he, rihi pekeb'ue dèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">B'ale di he, rihi pekeb'ue dèu do wiu do nga èba lii pedai Deo, ngati dèu donga èba lii pedai Deo maji lema ta tuwuèhu do pa d'ara rae-kowa hela'u.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Johani 4:44</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6a" />Tapulara d'ai tèra ne adèuade dèu pa nii, hèku wae d'o roo ta parahaj'a pa Yesus. Ri mi nahère ke madalae Yesus ne adèuade roo, ku ped'elo d'o ri Yesus ne kuaha Noo pa nii, wala ti pe'ie do pèri dèu do pèd'a.<bt>But those people's livers were extremely hard to-point-that they didn't want to believe in Yesus. This.is.the.reason Yesus was surprised/amazed at their hard livers, and didn't show/reveal His *power/authority anymore there. other than just healed a few sick people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ri mi nahère ke ne woapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ri mi nahère ke ne woapa pengee roo, wae d'oke Yesus ta ped'elo ne kuaha Noo pa nii, wala ti pe'ie do pèri dèu do pèd'a.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pejuu do henguru do d'ue ana aj'a Noo<bt>Yesus orders/commissions His twelve *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 10:5-15; Luka 9:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6b" />Ta pekèd'e ke Yesus la rae-rae do umu pa ène, la aj'a ne dèu he j'ara lua do d'èi Deo.<bt>And then, Yesus went all.around the different.villages that were close to teach people about God's will.</bt><v n="7" />Ta pedoa ke ri Noo do henguru do d'ue ana aj'a Noo, j'e pejuu do d'ue-do d'ue ta la pepeke ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo. Wie lema ri Noo pa roo ne kuaha ta hud'èiwango.<bt>He called his twelve *disciples and commanded them to travel in pairs to go tell God's Good News. He also gave them *power/authority to expel *evil spirits.</bt><v n="8-9" />Ta pereda ke ri Noo pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole teo ta ègu pe ae nengaa tuu lai kako muu. Tenge d'o ta ègu nga'a-nginu, doi, nga taa. Èba we muu kèji, pake helapa, nga b'aj'u pa ihi, j'e kako.<bt>He commanded them, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't need to bring alot on your journey. It's not neccessary to bring food-drink (doublet=generic), money, and bag. (= don't bring). Take your walking.stick, the sandals on feet, and the clothes on your body, and go.</bt><v n="10" />Kiri era dèu do hèmi muu pa èmu roo, pee we muu pa ène tade ta pekèd'èiwari muu.<bt>If there are people who receive you-pl in their house, stay there until you leave again.</bt><v n="11" />Tapulara, kiri d'ai muu la hewue rae, j'e dod'o wae ne dèu he ta hèmi muu, lema wae d'o ta ped'èno nga muu, kèd'èiti ène. J'e lii pa roo, &lt;Pelai ta dod'o wae muu ta ped'èno, hape miha ri muu ne lai apa ne!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But if it.comes.to-point-that you are in a village, and the people there don't want to receive/accept you, and also don't want to hear you, leave from there. tell them, &lt;&lt;Because you-pl don't want to listen, may you carry(on shoulder) the evil consequences yourselves!&gt;&gt; (idiom = general threat: you are responsible for whatever befalls you)</bt><note reference="6:8-11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do asli, do b'uke mi nad'ee, &lt;&lt;lèta awu wurai ti kab'a j'èla&gt;&gt;. Pa awe na ène pa nii, ne dèu he do tima ta lèta awu wurai ti kab'a j'èla, ta jad'èi he èhi rutada kiri dod'o wae dèu ta d'èno, hape miha ri roo ne lai apa ène. Heleo pa <span class="Italic">Luka</span> 10:4-11; <span class="Italic">Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu</span> Yesus 13:51.<bt>There at that time, people would brush off dust from their feet as a sign that people who didn't want to listen/obey, they must shoulder-carry the evil consequences. Also see Luke 10:4-11; and Acts 13:51.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta kako ke roo la pepeke ne Lii Ha'ga D'ara ti Deo. La pika ri roo pa dèu he lii ta hani ne muri mada do d'o mèd'èipa Deo, j'e muri mada pa ruj'ara do d'èi Deo.<bt>And then they went to tell that Good News of God's. They told people to stop living in ways that are not pleasing to God, and live according to God's will.</bt><v n="13" />Hud'èilema ri roo ne wango he. J'e pehuti ri èi mènyi pa dèu do pèd'a he, j'e heb'aj'a roo mij'e ta ie. Ta ie ke ne pèd'a roo.<bt>And they also expelled *evil spirits. And they dripped oil on sick people, and prayed for them to be healed. And they got healed from their sicknesses.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ae ne dèu do pe'ie ri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ae ne dèu do pe'ie ri roo. J'e heb'aj'a roo natuu dèu do pèd'a nga pelobo roo èi mènyi pa wukolo roo.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">J'ako 5:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua pemade Johani, mone peherani dèu<bt>The death of Johani, the man who *baptises people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 14:1-12; Luka 9:7-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Pa d'ara awe do na ène, rèngi ke harièle dèu j'ara lua Yesus. Rèngi lema ke dèue Herode, j'ara lua kuaha Yesus. Era dèu do lii, &lt;&lt;Ta kuaha hengaa Johani mone peherani dèu, do muri wari pa d'ara Yesus. Pelai ri mi nahère ke Noo, ne nara ta tao harièle lua madalae.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time everybody had heard about Yesus. King Herode had also heard about the power/authority Yesus. There were people who said, &lt;&lt;The power/authority of the spirit of Johani who.habitually baptizes poeple, lives again in Yesus. That.is.the.reason.why He can make all those *miracles (amazing signs).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peherani = 1) Christianise, 2) baptise"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peherani = 1) Christianise, 2) baptise (neutral as to method) ; In Sabu (di lingkungan adat) @@ 1) diselamkan dlm kali, /puru loko/ "turun kali" 2) bekin tanda salib di dahi anak dgn ludah sirih-pinang, langsung dicurahkan dgn air, /dab'a/ 3) tanda percik (berlaku se'umur hidup, berhubungan dgn hal-hal yg najis, bekin dingin rumah, dipercikkan dgn air tebuh atau air kelapa) --&gt; penyucian satu hal yg dianggap najis /pihi/ "percik"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tapulara era lema dèu had'e do lii, &lt;&lt;Ad'o! Elia ke noo! Ki ad'o, hala he dèu mone ub'a ngati Deo rai uru he.&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were other people who said, &lt;&lt;No! It's Elia! Or else one of God's other *prophets1 (spokesperson) from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hala he dèu = salah seorang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hala he dèu = salah seorang @@ ; mone ub'a = spokesman ; hala he dèu = salah satu orang</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 16:14, Ma'u 8:28, Luka 9:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ta rènge ri dèue Herode ne pedai roo j'ara lua Yesus mi nahère, moko ta lii ke noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ne toi ri yaa, Johani mone peherani dèu, do hewari nee, èle ke ri yaa pepereda ta ète ne kètu noo. J'e nee ke noo, do muri wari!&gt;&gt;<bt>When king Herode heard them talking about Yesus like that, then he spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;In my thinking this is Johani who.habitally baptizes people,whom at a previous time I ordered that they cut off his head. Now he lives again!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Ta ngaa dèue Herode ne lii mi nahère, rowi pa awe do ludèu do èla pe jad'èi lai mone ae nga Johani. Mi nahee ne lii ped'èii ne: Moko ke dèue Herode ta peloje ihi-èmu ari noo, Pelipu, ne ngara noo Herodia. Tapulara pa awe na ène, ad'o dae Herodia do pehèg'i nga Pelipu. Taga rowi lai na ène ke, ne pekeb'ède loro-loro Herode ri Johani, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama dèue, b'ole peloje ihi-èmu ari èu nee. Rowi ne wue ai èu na d'ee ad'o do pelèka nga had'a rai dii do Jahudi!&gt;&gt; Tapulara ped'èno d'o Herode, hèku banga èmu noo nga Herodia. Pelai ti mi nahère ke, ku pejuu noo dèu la kèpe Johani, j'e pemaho la èmu b'èdo.<bt>Why king Herode spoke like that, was because he had previously had a big dispute with Johani. The story is like this: Raja Herodes had married his younger.sibling Pelipu's wife, named Herodia. But Pelipu and Herodia were not yet divorced. That is why Johani scolded Herode over and over, saying, &lt;&lt;Father king can't be recip-taking (=marry) your younger.sibling's wife. Cuz that violates our-inc Jahudi law/custom!&gt;&gt; But Herode didn't listen, and married Herodia anyway. Then he ordered people to go capture/arrest Johani to put him in jail.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pemaho"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pemaho</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 3:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Pelai ti pekeb'ède loro-loro ri Johani, ta tèka nui ke Herodia, j'e kale ruj'ara ta pemade Johani. Tapulara jad'èi ded'o, ri Johani do pa d'ara èmu b'èdo ko.<bt>Because Johani had scolded over and over, therefore Herodia held.a.grudge (Idiom: stored her liver) and she wanted to find a way to kill him. But there was not yet the opportunity, cuz Johani was in jail,</bt><v n="20" />Pereda lema ri Herode pa horod'ad'u he ta jage Johani pe woie.<bt>Herode also commanded the soldiers to guard Johani carefully.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Herode lema do d'ai meg'ig'i ri Johani. Do toi ri noo ta Johani nee, dèu pejuu Deo. Lema he dèu do woie ade nga pengee. Mengèlu d'ara lema noo ne d'èno lii pedai Johani, maji lema ne lii pedai Johani ta pereja ne pengee noo.<bt>Herode was also in.awe.of.and.afraid of Johani. He knew that that Yohanis, was a servant/underling of God. And also that he was a good person (idiom: in liver and thought). Herodes also liked to hear Johani talk, even though sometimes what Johani said disturbed his thinking.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="meg'ig'i = was-was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">meg'ig'i = was-was</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Pedèka, pa d'ara he lod'o, ta nara ke Herodia ne awe kehoo do rihi woie, ta petobe ne lua pana ade noo pa Johani. Pa lod'o na ène, awe hari jad'èi dèue Herode. Ta pedoa ke ne dèu-dèu do mone ae pa propensi Galilea, ie ngati do pereda, kètu-kètu horod'ad'u, nga kètu-kètu rai.<bt>And so after that, one day, Herodia got an opportunity to revenge her hot liver (=anger) against Johani. That day they were making king Herode's birthday. They invited all the prominant people in the province of Galilea, that is the government people, the soldiers heads, and the traditional leaders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pedèka rai OR Pedèka rahi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Pedèka rai OR Pedèka rahi = akhir, finis (CHECK more) @@</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Pa d'ara rame mengèlu d'ara do na ène, ta maho ke ne ana do mobèni ri Herodia la ledo. D'ai woie tèra ne ledo noo, hèku tobo ri mengèlu d'ara Herode nga harièle dèu do pedoa ri noo. Ta èla pe ledo, ta pedoe ke ne ana mobèni ne ri dèue Herode, j'e lii noo, &lt;&lt;Pika we èu pa yaa, ami nengaa èu. Ta wie ma ri yaa!<bt>In the middle of the feast, then Herodia's daughter came in to dance. Her dancing was very good, to-point-that it made Herode's insides happy and all his invited guests. When the dance finished, king Herode summoned the girl and said to her, &lt;&lt;Tell me whatever you want to request from me. I'll give it to you!</bt><v n="23" />Ta ame heb'èka rai pereda yaa, ta wie ma. Hupa yaa nga ngara Deo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if you also ask half of my kingdom, I'll give it. I swear with God's name!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ledo ~ lendo = generic; can"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ledo ~ lendo = generic; can be one or many, bisa laki-laki atau perempuan, kecil-besar, tua-muda ; @@ rame mengèlu d'ara = pesta suka-cita</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta kako ke ne ana mobèni ne la keb'ali pa ina noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wo mama! Ami nengaa ke dii pa papa, ne do rihi woie?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that girl went to ask her mother saying, &lt;&lt;Wo mama! What would be the best thing for me to ask from papa?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ane mama noo, &lt;&lt;Naaa! Ame ne kètu Johani, b'oke ina tana ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then her mama replied saying, &lt;&lt;Naaa! Go ask for Johani's head, dear girl [+affection].&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Minta kepala Johani, dear mother (but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Minta kepala Johani, dear mother (but euphemism addressing dearest daughter)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ta la pedai ke ne ana mobèni ne nga Herode, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Papa, ee! Ame kètu Johani ri yaa mèd'a d'ee. Pèlo pa d'ara d'ula.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that girl went to Herode and said, &lt;&lt;Papa, ee! Bring me Johani's head now/tonight. Put is on a tray.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ta rènge ne lii ami na ène, lila nèd'a Herode. Tapulara i'a d'o ke noo, ta nyèke ne lii ami na ène, rowi èla ke noo pe hupa pa hed'apa dokepai do pedoa ri noo he.<bt>Herode heard that, then his thoughts flew (panic). But he couldn't do anything to break the request, cuz he had sworn an oath in front of all his prominant invited guests.</bt><v n="27" />Ta pereda ke Herode pa kètu horod'ad'u ta la ète ne kètu Johani pa d'ara èmu b'èdo.<bt>And then, Herode commanded a commander to go cut Johani's head in the jail.</bt><v n="28" />Ta la ète ke ri roo ne kètu Johani, j'e ihe pa d'ara d'ula, j'e la wie pa ana mobèni nee. Hème rowi noo, j'e d'ede la wie pa ina noo.<bt>Then they cut Johani's head, then placed it on a tray, then2 go give it to that girl. She accepted it, then carried taking it to give to her mother.</bt><v n="29" />Ta rèngi ne ana aj'a Johani ta do èla ke pe'ète ne kètu noo, ta kako ke roo la ègo ne ngi'u noo j'e la pedane.<bt>When his *disciples heard that Johani's head had been cut off, they went and took his corpse, to go bury it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ihi + e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ihi + e</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mi nahère ke ne lii ped'èii j'ara lua made Johani.<bt>It's just like that, the story of Johani's death.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus penga'a lèmi tèb'a rihi dèu<bt>Yesus feeds more than five thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 14:13-21; Luka 9:10-17; Johani 6:1-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Pa d'ara he lod'o, ta b'ale ke ne ana aj'a do pejuu ri Yesus he, la peteni wari hela'u nga Noo. Ta ped'èii ke ri roo hari-hari ne do èla pe tao, nga do aj'a ri roo.<bt>One time, those *disciples that Yesus had sent, they all came.home to gather once again with Him. They told all they they had done, and what they had taught.</bt><v n="31" />Tapulara pa awe do na ène, ae tèra ne dèu do pe holi-hoo la kale Yesus, hèku b'ule d'oke roo nga awe kehoo ta pengaha ta nga'a. Ta lii ke Yesus pa ana aj'a he, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mai we dii la kale era do kehii mij'e nara ko dii ta pengaha ihi hudi he.&gt;&gt;<bt>But at that time very many people were travelling going to try and find Yesus, to.the.point.that they couldn't find opportunity to eat. Then Yesus told his disciples, saying, &lt;&lt;Let us-inc go find a lonely place, in.order.that we-inc can stop our tiredness a bit first (=rest).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hudi CIE with hud'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hudi CIE with hud'i</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ta pekèd'èike roo j'ara kowa la kale era do kehii, do j'èu ngati d'ara rae.<bt>So they left by boat in.order.to seek a lonely place, that was far from the village.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Tapulara do ngèdi ri dèu lowe he ne kowa do ha'e Yesus he, do ore ne ngidi èi lobo nee. Ta mèhu èni ke roo ti d'ara rae, j'e kako pe'uru èni la era do ta penawu kowa Yesus he.<bt>But those many people saw Yesus mob's boat going along that lake's edge. Then they exited the village following a land path, then they arrived ahead of where Yesus mob anchored the boat.</bt><v n="34" />Mi nahère Yesus ne puru ngati d'ara kowa, ta ngèdi ke ri Noo ne dèu lowe he do mate Noo. Ta ruba ke ne d'ara Noo nga roo, rowi ne dèu lowe he era mi ki'i-j'awa do d'o b'ule nga mone b'ata he ke, hèku toi d'o ke nengaa ne do madae ta tao ri roo. Moko ke Yesus ta aj'a roo j'ara lua do d'èi Deo,<bt>As Yesus was getting down from the boat, then he saw the many people waiting for Him. And then He felt pity/love on them, because they all did not know what they should be doing, same as sheep that doesn't have a shepherd. Then Yesus taught them God's will,</bt><note reference="6:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Reke Ae Do Isra'el 27:17, 1 Duae-duae 22:17, 2 Lii Ped'iri Rae Pereda Yahuda nga Isra'el 18:16, Yeskia 34:5, Sakaria 10:2, Mateo 9:36</note><v n="35-36" />rai ti nètu lod'o hape la mèd'a lod'o. Ta lii ke ne ana aj'a he pa Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Umu ke ta jèna ne lod'o. Ne era na d'ee do kehii, lema do j'èu ngati rae-kowa. B'ule d'o nga'a-nginu pa d'ee. Pejuu kowe ne dèu lowe he la wèli nga'a pa rae-kowa do umu pa d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>from noon to afternoon. Then His disciples told him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! It's already late afternoon. This is a lonely place, far from villages. There is no food here. Order all these people to go buy food in the nearby villages.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bui ade = rasa kasihan (lit."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">bui ade = rasa kasihan (lit. liver falls)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ane Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole teo ta pejuu ne dèu he! Ta penga'a ri muu we ne dèu he!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied, &lt;&lt;It's not necessary to order the people! You-pl feed them.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta keb'ali ri ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama ee! Kiri penga'a ri j'ii ne dèu do mi nahee ne worèwu ae, d'ai ae doi ne do ta pake ri j'ii! Hela'u nga gaji tuka natuu he wue tèu!<bt>They responded saying, &lt;&lt;Father, ee! If we-ex feed as many people as this, we-ex will have to give out an incredible amount of money! Same as a craftsman's entire year wage!</bt><note reference="6:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani, &lt;&lt;d'ue ngahu <span class="Italic">denari</span> doi melaa pudi&gt;&gt;. He <span class="Italic">denari</span> pa awe do uru, hela'u nga gaji he dèu tuka he lod'o.<bt>The Greek language Bible says, &lt;&lt;two hundred |idenari|r silver money. One denari in the old times, same as a craftsman's wage for one day's work.</bt></note>Mi namii ke j'ii ne nara doi do mi nahère ne ae!&gt;&gt;<bt>How can we-ex get that much money!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ta lii rike Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;La kale toi ko ri muu, nadèu do nga èba nga'a.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go find out, who has brought food.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta èla ri roo pe kale toi, ta b'ale ke roo la pika pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Era lèmi b'ue roti, nga d'ue ngi'u nadèuu we.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then they went to find out, then they returned to tell Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;There's 5 fruit (counter) of bread, and 2 bodies of fish.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\HK-LB\HK00155C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa dèu he harièle ta mejèd'èipa kolo j'u'u he, hekewolo-hekewolo.<bt>Then Yesus told all those people to sit in.groups on the grass.</bt><v n="40" />Moko roo ta mejèd'èipedèue ne lii Yesus. Pa d'ara he kewolo, era do hengahu, era lema do lèmi nguru dèu.<bt>Then they went to sit according to Yesus' instructions. There were those in groups of 100 people, and those of 50 people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ta èba ke ri Yesus ne roti do lèmi b'ue, nga nadèuu d'ue ngi'u he. J'e tengara Noo la liru ta peha'e lii ie ae pa Deo. Èla pe mi nahère ta pipe ke ri Noo ne roti he, j'e wie pa ana aj'a he ta peb'agi pa dèu he hari-hari. Mi nahère lema ne nadèuu he.<bt>And then, Yesus took those 5 fruit of bread and those two bodies of fish. Then he looked.up to the sky to reciprocate thank-you to God [CHECK if term for thank you is known by younger generation]. After that He hand.broke that bread (into pieces), then gave them to his *disciples so.that they go divide them out to all those people. The same with the fish.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peha'e lii ie ae ~ peha'e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peha'e lii ie ae ~ peha'e lii terima kasi</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ta nga'a ke roo harièle tade b'èhu.<bt>And then they all ate until satisfied.</bt><v n="43" />D'ai roo ne èla pe nga'a, ta pekupu ke ri ana aj'a he ne nga'a do rihi he. Tobo henguru d'ue hope ne ae.<bt>After eating then, those disciples went to collect that food that was extra. 12 full baskets1.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hope = 2-blek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hope = 2-blek</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Ne dèu do nga'a he, ne pe'ira era ma do lèmi tèb'a dèu momone; reke d'o mobèni nga naiki.<bt>The people who ate were approximately 5,000 men; not counting the women and children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="reke ded'o = belum hitung tapi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">reke ded'o = belum hitung tapi akan dihitung ; reke d'o = tidak dihitung</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus nèru pa kolo èi<bt>Yesus walks on top of the water</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 14:22-33; Johani 6:16-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ta moko harièle ne lai na hère, ta pejuu ke ri Yesus ne ana aj'a Noo la ha'e kowa, mij'e ta uru la heb'èka èi lobo, la rae Betsaida. Pe leto èni ko Yesus mij'e ta pejuu ne dèu do lowe he ta b'ale.<bt>After that, Yesus ordered His *disciples to get.into the boat to go ahead to the village Betsaida on that lake's other side. He himself still stayed there, to order those many people to go home.</bt><v n="46" />Ta b'ale harièle dèu, ta ha'e ke Noo la hewue lede j'e la heb'aj'a pa ène.<bt>When they had all gone(home), then He went.up a mountain to *pray1.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47-50" />D'ai ta mèd'a, ta puru ke Yesus. Ngèdi ri Noo ne kowa ana aj'a he, do d'ai ke la telora èi lobo nee. Era ke roo nga tuku hetenga made ne kowa nee, rowi awe na ène do rihi mèdèungèlu d'uru. Umu ta mèu rai, ta kako ke Yesus nèru pa kolo èi, la dèuu ne ana aj'a he. Ta d'ai Noo ne umu ta hihu ne kowa roo, moko ta ngède ke Noo ri roo. G'ig'a tèra roo. Ta pekeb'ali ke roo he dèu nga he dèu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Heleo ko ri muu! Nengaa ke na nii? Wango ke na nii, we nengaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was dark/night then, Yesus went down. [See NLT and BAGD, plus vs. 35-36 followed by series of events listed] He saw/had seen his disciples' boat had arrived in the middle of the lake. But they were paddling very hard, because that boat was sailing opposing the front wind. Nearing daylight, Yesus went following them, walking on top of the water. When He was about to pass by the boat, then they saw Him. They were extremely afraid. Straight.away they asked.each.other saying, &lt;&lt;Have a look! What's this? An *evil spirit, or what?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dutu ; pehihu = saling melewati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">dutu ; pehihu = saling melewati ; hihu = pass</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tapulara ta lii d'ènge ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;B'ole meda'u muu! Yaa ma na d'e rii!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus immediately talked saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't be.afraid! It's Me.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Ta d'ai Yesus ne ha'e la d'ara kowa nee, milu d'ènge ne ngèlu. Madalae tèra ne ana aj'a he harièle.<bt>When Yesus got into the boat, then that wind was immediately calm. His disciples all were totally amazed.</bt><v n="52" />Maji lema ri roo ta èla pengède ne kuaha Yesus ne penga'a do rihi ngati lèmi tèb'a dèu, tapulara tade ded'o ri roo nga petuu ne kuaha Noo, pelai ta do adèuade-pengee roo.<bt>They had just seen Yesus use His *power/authority to feed more than 5,000 people, but they still didn't truly understand His power, because their liver/thinking (doublet) were hard.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bèlu ded'o ri roo ne madalae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Bèlu ded'o ri roo ne madalae kuaha Yesus ne penga'a do lèmi tèb'a dèu nga rihi ri ko. Tapulara tade ded'o ri roo nga petuu ne kuaha Noo, pelai ta do adu ko ne pengee roo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie dèu-dèu do pèd'a pa Genesare<bt>Yesus heals sick people at Genesare</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 14:34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Ta d'ai roo la heb'èka èi lobo, ta penawu ke ne kowa roo pa ngidi èi lobo pa rae Genesare.<bt>When they arrived at the lake's other side, then they went.into.shore at Genasare beach.</bt><v n="54" />Mi nahère roo ne puru ti d'ara kowa, ae ne dèu pa ène do ngèdi roo. Ta petoda ke roo, &lt;&lt;Nee ke Yesus, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they got.down from the boat, many people had already seen them. And they shouted, &lt;&lt;Yesus has come, oo!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="55-56" />Ta perai ke roo la pepika pa hari hewue rai na ène. Ta dèka ke ne dèu lowe he, nga merèi ne dèu-dèu do pèd'a he.<bt>They ran to go tell all.around there, then many people came, and shoulder.carried sick people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Had'èita rèngi we ri roo ta Yesus do era pa he èhi era, ta ègu ke ri roo ne dèu do pèd'a he j'e la pebèj'i pa keb'èla. Ane pa d'ara lai pengee roo, &lt;&lt;Had'èita d'ai we ta b'uje ne b'ara pa ihi Noo ri do pèd'a he, do ta ie ma roo.&gt;&gt; Harièle dèu do nara ta b'uje ne b'ara pa ihi Noo, ie d'ènge ne pèd'a roo.<bt>Whenever they hear that Yesus was at a place, they shoulder.carried sick people. to lay them on the flat land/area/field. They thought to themselves, &lt;&lt;If only those sick people just touch the edge of His clothes (that He is wearing), then they'll be healed.&gt;&gt; All the people who touched the clothes on His body, were healed of their their sicknesses.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua petèka dèu rai-wawa b'ole gate lii pereda Deo<bt>Human regulations shouldn't replace God's commands</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 15:1-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Era he kejie do Parisi nga do pèri dèu guru agama ngati Yerusalem, dèka la pehapo nga Yesus.<bt>There was a group of Parisi people and several religious teachers who came from Yerusalem to meet with Yesus.</bt><v n="2-5" />Ne do Parisi he do d'ai tèra roo ne henèru ta pekako had'a rai Jahudi do petèka ri ama-èpu roo. Unupala, uru nga do d'o nga'a, j'amu uru èi pedèuu nga had'a rai. Mi nahère lema ki b'ale ti paha, do j'èma ta j'iu èi. Rihi ti na ène, ne b'ara-b'ara do pa d'ara èmu leo hogo nga'a roo, mi èru hogo, pai-kab'a, kab'a nginu, lonye uru ko hari-hari pedèuu nga had'a rai, j'e'itu pake.<bt>Those Parisi people hold really tight to carrying out their Jahudi customs from their forefathers. For example, if a person wants to eat, must wash hands according to the ways of custom. Like that also, if return.home from market, they must bathe before.doing.anything.else. More than that, their kitchen things, like cooking.pots, dishes (doublet = generic), drinking vessels [glasses and pitchers under one cover term], all must be washed following the ways of custom, only.then can they be used.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="èru hogo = pariuk masak ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">èru hogo = pariuk masak ; pai-kab'a = mangkok, tempat kuah, piring, ; èmu leo hogo nga'a</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ki era do Jahudi do wala he, do d'o pedèuu ne had'a rai na ène, bubu d'ara ne do Parisi he.<bt>If there are other Jahudi people who don't follow that custom, the Parisi people get angry.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Pelai ti mi nahère ke roo ne bubu d'ara, ta d'ai ne ngèdi ne ana aj'a Yesus he do nga'a uru nga do d'o j'amu èi pedèuu nga had'a rai. Ta dèka ke roo la pehale Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ne ana aj'a Èu ku nga'a uru nga d'o j'amu èi? Lai na ène, do j'èle ne had'a rai, do petèke ri ama-èpu dii!&gt;&gt;<bt>This.is.the.reason.why they got angry when they saw Yesus' *disciples eating without washing hands according to the custom. Then they came to accuse Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;Why do your disciples eat, but they don't wash hands before.hand? That way they've already violated the customs from our-inc ancestors!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-7" />Tapulara b'ale ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Muu he, dèu do peworèwu èni ta dèu do mèu! Petuu nengaa ne do b'uke ri Yesaya rai uru, j'ara lua muu, mihe ane,<bt>But Yesus replied, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl here are people who present yourselves as clean/holy! 9conventional implication: but are not really like that) It is true what from long.ago Yesaya about you-pl, saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ne dèu nahee do pekelode Yaa,<bt>&lt;These people *praise Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ri ub'a we, ad'o do rai ngati d'ara ade.<bt>only just by mouth, but not from inside their liver.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Parahuma we roo ne tao mi nahère.<bt>They do like that, and its just fruitless/no.results.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Wae d'o roo ta pekeb'ue ne do d'èi Yaa,<bt>They don't care.about/pay.attention.to My will,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tituwata rihi pekeb'ue lua petèka dèu rai-wawa we.&gt;<bt>they only just value humans' regulations.&gt;</bt><note reference="7:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Mi nahère lema ke muu.<bt>You-pl also are like that.</bt><v n="8-9" />J'èle ri muu ne lii pereda Deo mij'e ta nara ri muu ta pekako ne lua petèka dèu rai-wawa we. D'ai tèra muu ne i'a peheru èni!<bt>You have left.behind God's commands, so you just carry out humans' regulations. You are really very skilled at doing like that!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Rai uru he do èla ke pepeke ri Musa ne lii pedai Deo, mihe ane, &lt;Pekeb'ue ina-ama muu.&gt; Nga lii pereda do wala wari, &lt;Nadèu do wègi-menihi ina ki ad'o ama noo, wole noo pemade.&gt;<bt>Long ago Musa told God's command saying, &lt;Give honor to your-p mother-father.&gt; And another command, &lt;If a person curses his mother or father, must punish by putting him to death.&gt;</bt><note reference="7:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 20:12, 21:17, Kètu Agama nga Lua Petèka Agama 20:9, Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 5:16</note><v n="11-12" />Mi nahère ke ne lii pereda Deo, tapulara aj'a muu do wala. Aj'a muu dèu, mihe ane, &lt;Kiri era dèu do jaji ta j'ola he èhi b'ara natuu Deo, ie d'oke ta wie pa ina-ama noo, maji lema roo ta do pa d'ara hedèu-herui. Ne b'ara na ène nara d'o ta pake ta rab'a roo, rowi do èla ke pejaje mij'e ta j'ole pa Deo.&gt;<bt>God's command is like that, but you-pl teach something different. You-pl teach people, saying, &lt;If a person promises to present a thing to God, even if his mother-father are in extreme suffering (doublet). That thing cannot be used to help them, cuz it has been promised that it will be presented to God.&gt;</bt><v n="13" />Rowi mi nahère ke ne lii Yaa pa muu ngine, èla ke ri muu pe j'èle ne lii pereda Deo, j'e pehure ri muu ri lua petèka do wiu. Ae ko ne lua petèka muu do tebèli ti lua do d'èi Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>This.is.the.reason.why I said earlier, you-pl have stepped on (=violated and belittled) God's commands, and.so you have exchanged [it] with a new regulation. There are many regulations which you have deviated from the will of God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="natuu = bagi, untuk ; natu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">natuu = bagi, untuk ; natu = semacam penyakit gila jalan-jalan ; CIE peheru + pehure</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nengaa do pa d'ara petèka pengee"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Nengaa do pa d'ara petèka pengee muu ta wie pa Deo, ie d'oke ta wie pa ina-ama muu maji lema roo ta do pa d'ara hedui. Lii aj'a do mi nahère hela'u lema nga lii ta b'ole heleo ina-ama pa d'ara hedui.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lai do apa do kepue ti d'ara ade dèu<bt>Evil matter/cases which are sourced from people's heart(liver)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin kamomos"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">bekin kamomos</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 15:10-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta pedoa ke ri Yesus ne dèu lowe pa ène, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;D'èno we pe woie, mij'e tada muu.<bt>And then, Yesus called other people there, and said, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully, so.that you-pl can understand.</bt><v n="15" />Nengaa we ne do maho la d'èlu dèu, b'ule d'o do pera'i dèu. Tapulara nengaa do dèka ti d'ara dèu, na ène ne do nara ta pe'apa dèu.<bt>What enters in the stomach of a person, that doesn't make people dirty. But what comes from a person's insides, that's what makes defiles a person.</bt><v n="16" />[Nadèu do nga d'èi ta d'èno, tenae pe woie, mij'e tada muu!]&gt;&gt;<bt>[Whoever really wants to listen1, listen2 carefully, so that you can understand!]&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="7:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ad'o do b'uke ne ayat na d'ee (16) pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do rihi dèu he.<bt>The Greek language Bible which are older don't write this verse 16.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ta peb'agi ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo nga dèu do lowe he j'e maho la d'ara hewue èmu. Ta keb'ali ke ne ana aj'a Noo mi namii ne pedèb'o lii pehèku do èla pe pedai nga dèu do lowe he.<bt>Then Yesus with His *disciples separated from those other people and entered a house. Then His disciples asked that *parable's meaning that He had told those people.</bt><v n="18-19" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Pee ko ma muu nga d'o tada? Mi nahee ne lua pedèb'o ne: nengaa ne do nga'a ri dèu, do ie. Tapulara, nengaa ne do mèhu èni ti dèu nee, ad'o do woie. Nengaa we ne do nga'a ri dèu, maho la d'èlu, j'e mèhu èni wari. (Ne pedèb'o lii Yesus, ie ma dèu ta nga'a nengaa we. B'ule d'o do petaru.)<bt>Yesus replied, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl still don't understand? It's meaning is that what people eat, that is good. But that which comes out from a person, is not good. What a person eats, enters the stomach, and then comes out again. (Yesus' meaning that people can eat whatever. It is not prohibited.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehèg'i = implies things not right"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehèg'i = implies things not right between them ; pedèb'o = maksud ; lii pehèku = perumpamaan, (ilustrasi, comparison, purpose to clarify meaning of s.t. unclear, banding dgn hal yg lebih jelas atau lebih gampang dimengerti) ; lii pepèhi = bahasa lempar (like lii Wae Temun in Buru), memakai kiasan/lukisan; 19: peb'ata = bertentangan @@ ; @@ rue = haram ; petaru = dilarang, larangan adat, tidak boleh mendekati ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Tapulara, nengaa ne do mèhu èni ngati d'ara ade dèu, na ène ke ne do pe'apa dèu, hèku Deo wae d'o ta pe'umu èni nga roo.<bt>But, what comes out from inside a person's liver, that is what defiles a person, so God doesn't want to be around/associate with them.</bt><v n="21-22" />Rowi ae lai do apa do kepue ti d'ara ade dèu. Mii: lai pengee do apa, kenyoo nga dèu do ad'o ihi-èmu noo, mena'o, pemade dèu, menga'a, tao apa, pote-èpi, lala-hopa, mèta d'ara, wègi-menihi dèu, wue èni, b'ule d'o nga had'a, nga paja kètu.<bt>Because many evil things are sourced/rooted from a person's liver. Such as: evil thoughts, sexual relations outside a spouse relationship [NOTE: /porneia/ and adultery combined into one.], stealing, killing people, greed/gluttony, doing evil, deceit, coveting (expalined as: unconstrained wanting what other people have), jealousy, cursing-clandering (doublet), pride/arrogance, uncouth/uncultured/rude, stubborn.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'umu = mendekati, bergaul; 22: mena'o"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'umu = mendekati, bergaul; 22: mena'o = mencuri ; pemade dèu = bunu orang; 22: b'ege = jijik ; kenyoo lènga huka = cabul, promiscuous bersinaan secara bebas, ; lènga = keluar jauh ; huka = pikiran, budi ; kenyoo = sina (hubungan seks di luar perkawinan yg sah) (but gray area if nyong and nona have made an agreement) ada tingkat kenyoo (5-6 types) 1. rue ae (sina besar, sina berat): isteri yg su nikah berselingkuh dgn suami yg su nikah; 2) rue iki (sina kecil): isteri yg su nikah berselingkuh dgn suami yg su berkeluarga ma balom nikah; 3) pewèba kolola (sina dlm hati): perempuan yg su berkeluarga, ada laki-laki yg menyentuh tubuh orang dgn perasaan seksual, tapi belum ada hubungan seks; 4) mamaru rukenana leko wue (makan daun sirih yg menggambarkan pribadi): kasih sst pada nona dgn maksud mau mencintai secara seksual, nona terima tapi tidak membalas dgn kenyataan; 5) nged'e pakolo d'are (bersukaria di atas pusaran/kuburan) isteri atau suami yg su meninggal belum pulang ke marga lalu hubungan seks dgn lawan jenis, /kèd'i/ ritus pelepasan hukum perkawinan (can be 1 wk to 2 yrs after death of spouse) 6) wawi j'èli kerab'a (babi injak tempat makan) isteri yg su nikah berselingkuh dgn anak muda. [Pdt. Tari notes that /sina/ in Sabu is prejudiced against the woman.]; 22: kenyoo lènga-huka = hubungan sembarang, promiscuity ; menga'a = balalas, galoju, ambisi, rakus ; pote-èpi = putar-balek ; lèlo pengee = (not known) ; mèta d'ara = iri hati ; dèu do lala do hopa ~ lala-hopa = ingin mimiliki sembarang (cars, things, food, girls) ; wègi-menihi dèu = caci-maki, fitnah ; wue èni = sombong ; kura aj'a ~ b'ule d'o nga had'a = kurang ajar, sonde tahu adat ; paja kètu = kapala batu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lai do rue do b'ege:"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lai do rue do b'ege:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Naa. Harièle lai do apa na hère do kepue pa d'ara ade dèu, do ma pe'apa dèu. Lai do apa na hère ke, do b'ege Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa. All the evil things like that, which are sourced/rooted in a person's liver, is what defiles a person. God also is repulsed by those evil things.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus ruba d'ara nga he dèu mobèni ad'o do Jahudi<bt>Yesus helps/takes pity on a woman who is not a Jahudi person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 15:21-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta pekèd'èirike Yesus he la hewue kota ne ngara noo Tirus. Ta d'ai la ène, maho roo la d'ara hewue èmu, mij'e ta dod'o toi ri dèu ta do era ke Noo pa nii. Maji mi nahère, pee ma ta toi ri dèu he ne lua dèka Noo.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) left that place, to go to a city named Tirus. Arriving there, they went into a house, so that people wouldn't know He was there. Even that being the case, people still found out about His coming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lua mèno = kepercayaan, iman ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lua mèno = kepercayaan, iman ; lua dèka = kedatangan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Pa ène era he dèu mobèni, ad'o do Jahudi. Ngati rai Penesia ihi propensi Siria. Ta toi ri noo ne lua dèka Yesus, ta kako ke noo la huba pa Yesus, mij'e ta la hud'e ne wango ti d'ara ana noo do mobèni.<bt>There there was a woman who was not a Jahudi person. She was from the Penesia area of Siria province. When she found out that Yesus had arrived, she went to ask Yesus to expel *evil spirit from her daughter.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Dogs&quot; implicit to make the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">"Dogs" implicit to make the word play make sense.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ta wie ke ri Yesus ne lii pepèhi, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Nga'a peb'èhu uru ko naiki he, j'e wie ne do rihi pa ngaka.&gt;&gt; (Ne pedèb'o Yesus, ta pemoko uru ri Noo dèu Noo do Jahudi, j'e le to dèu do hewala he).<bt>Yesus gave her a riddle saying, &lt;&lt;The children must eat full first, only.then give the leftovers to the dog.&gt;&gt; (With Yesus' meaning, He must help His Jahudi people first, only.then can he help other people).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lii pepèhi = arti kiasan, tersembunyi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lii pepèhi = arti kiasan, tersembunyi ; peb'èhu = kasi kenyang ; ngaka = anjing ; hewewe = dia bina (moral), bimbing, layani ; pemoko = melengkapi (lahir dan batin); rab'a = tolong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta b'ale ke ri mobèni na ène, &lt;&lt;Petuu ke ne lii pedai Ama! Ngaka lema do era pa da'i meja nga'a, ta nga'e ne nga'a do bui ti d'èia meja naiki he.&gt;&gt; (Ne pedèb'o nee, pa d'ara awe nga'a naiki, era nga'a do bui, j'e nga'e ri ngaka. Maji lema Yesus ta pemoko uru dèu Noo do Jahudi, do j'èma lema Noo ta heleo dèu do hewala.)<bt>That woman responded saying, &lt;&lt;It is true what Father said! (But) the dog is also under the eating table, and eats the food that falls from the children's table.&gt;&gt; (With meaning that, when children eat, there falls that which the dogs also eat. Even though Yesus must first help His Jahudi people, He must also look.after other people.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tebui = sisa ; da'i ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tebui = sisa ; da'i = bawah ; pa da'i = di bawah ; mata = tunggu ; hepèla = jilat ; @@ ngaka CIE with nga'a ; pehenèru = merawat, memperbaiki kehidupan ;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="era lema do bui do nga'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">era lema do bui do nga'a ri ngaka.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta rènge ri Yesus ne lii mobèni nee, ta lii ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Do petuu ne lii èu ina, ó! B'ale we ina la èmu, ie ke ne ana èu, rowi èla ke ne wango ne pemèhu èni ti d'ara noo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing what the woman said, Yesus spoke, &lt;&lt;Mother has spoken very truly, oo! Mother go.home (imperative), your child is well, cuz that evil spirit has already come out of her.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ta b'ale ke noo la èmu. Ta d'ai la èmu, era ke ne ana noo do bèj'i bilu, rowi èla ke ne wango ne pemèhu èni.<bt>Then she went.home. Arriving at the house, her child was sleeping soundly,because that evil spirit had already come out of her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèj'i bilu = tidur nyenyak, sonu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">bèj'i bilu = tidur nyenyak, sonu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie he dèu do b'ènga nga hoe wodilu<bt>Yesus heals a person dumb and deaf</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta pekèd'èirike Yesus he ti kota Tirus, j'ara lahalae lake kota Sidon. Nèru roo teruu la èi lobo Galilea. Ngati ène, kako wari roo teruu la rai henguru b'ue kota, do tima ta pale, ta, &lt;Dekapolis&gt;.<bt>Then Yesus mob left that city Tirus, following the road along the coast going by Sidon city. They continued walking to Galilea lake. From there, they went to a region with ten cities which they usually refer to as &lt;Dekapolis&gt;.</bt><v n="32" />Pa nii, era he dèu do bènga riko do hoe. Ta ègo ke noo ri ihianga noo nga Yesus. J'e ame ri roo Yesus ta tèka ruai pa wukolo noo, mij'e ta pe'ie noo.<bt>There there was a person who was dumb and deaf. His friends brought him to Yesus. They asked Yesus to put hands on his head to heal him.</bt><v n="33" />Ta petala èni ke Yesus nga dèu na ène ti dèu do lowe he. Ta pemaho ne kolo ku'u Noo la ro'a wodilu dèu ne hari d'ue b'ue. Pebob'e ri ne kehui ai Yesus ri ilu Noo, j'e tèke pa we'o dèu do na ène.<bt>Then Yesus retreated from those many people to go alone with that person. He put his finger(s) in both that person's ear holes. Yesus put spittle on His finger, then touched that person's tongue.</bt><v n="34" />Ta tengara ke Yesus la d'èia, j'e tule hengaa, j'e pali Noo, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Epata&gt;&gt;</span> (ki pa d'ara lii rai dii, &lt;&lt;Boka èni we!&gt;&gt;)<bt>Yesus looked.up to the sky, drew a long breath, then spoke, &lt;&lt;|iEfata|r&gt;&gt;, (which in our-inc language is &lt;&lt;Open (imperative)!&gt;&gt;)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ènga = kelu, bisu, tidak bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ènga = kelu, bisu, tidak bisa bicara ; hoe (1) = tuli hoe (2) = sial, celaka ; lake = lewat ; lahalae = pantai; 32: ihianga = kawan ; d'ede = angkat; 33: petala = pisahkan ; kehui ai = jari ; ro'a = lobang ; pelobe = membasahi ; ilu = ludah ; we'o = lidah ; pebob'e = kasi basah; 34: tule = push out, mengeluarkan (nafas) ; boka = buka</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Mi nahère we ne lii Yesus, rèngi d'ènge noo. Ne we'o noo do hekoto, lumu d'ènge, i'a d'ènge pedai lii nga woie.<bt>He said just like that, then he could hear immediately. That person's tongue that was akward/stiff, became soft/pliable immediately, to-point-that he started talking well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hekoto = kaku ; lumu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hekoto = kaku ; lumu = lembut</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Èla pe mi nahère ta b'ale ke roo nga dèu lowe he. Ta pereda ke Yesus pa dèu pa ène, &lt;&lt;D'èno ie ri muu! B'ole ped'èii muu pa dèu ta Yaa do pe'ie dèu na d'ee.&gt;&gt; Maji ta lara ri Noo, pee ma ne dèu he ta pedai ne lai na ène pa mii-pa mii.<bt>After that they returned to the many people. Yesus commanded the people there, &lt;&lt;Listen well! Don't tell people that I have healed this person.&gt;&gt; Even though He forbade, they still told the story all over the place.</bt><v n="37" />Madalae tèra ne dèu do rèngi ne lai do na ène. Pedai roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;D'ai tèra Dèu na ène! Pejad'èi ri Noo harièle lai pe'ie. Do hoe jad'èi ita rèngi. Do b'ènga i'a pedai lii.&gt;&gt;<bt>The people who heard that story, they were truly amazed. They talked.back.and.forth saying, &lt;&lt;This Person is extraordinary! He makes everything become well/good. Deaf people can hear. Dumb people can talk.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèka lii = nasehati ; j'èga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèka lii = nasehati ; j'èga = kerja, buat ; merig'a = meluap ; pe'ie ~ pe'ie ; wo'ie ~ woie ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus penga'a do èpa tèb'a dèu<bt>Yesus feeds four thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 15:32-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1-3" />Hewari, ae ne dèu do peteni la d'èno ne lii aj'a Yesus. Tèlu lod'o ke roo ne pedèue Noo, hèku b'ule d'oke roo nga nga'a-nginu. Ta pedoa ke ri Yesus ne ana aj'a Noo, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Ruba d'ara ke Yaa nga dèu do lowe he. Era do dèka ngati rae do j'èu, j'e tèlu lod'o lema ke roo ne pedèu, tade ta èla ke ne nga'a unu roo. J'e ma d'oke ta peb'ale roo nga d'èlu wue. Ngee ta melanu pa telora ruj'ara.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, many people came gathering to hear Yesus teach. They had already been following him for three days, so.this.is.the.reason they had no more food (doublet). Then Yesus called His *disciples and said, &lt;&lt;I feel pity toward these many people. There are those who came from far villages, and they have also accompanied for three days, to-point-that, there is no food anymore. They shouldn't go.home with empty stomachs. Lest they faint in the middle of the road/trip.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="la'a = unu = milik ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">la'a = unu = milik ; d'èlu wue = perut kosong ; lud'ara = pingsan ; melanu = collapse from weakness ; pekupu = kumpul</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta b'ale ke ri ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wo Ama. Ne era na ène j'èu ti rae-kowa. Hèku nara d'o dii ta penga'a dèu do mi nahee ne ae!&gt;&gt;<bt>His disciples replied saying, &lt;&lt;Wo Father. This place is far from any village. So it's impossible for us-inc to to feed as many people as this!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Wo Ama = signals objection"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Wo Ama = signals objection</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Henga ne roti do era pa muu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked them, saying, &lt;&lt;How much/many bread do you have?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="henga = berapa Q"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">henga = berapa Q</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta b'ale ke ri roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;He pidèu b'ue roti we.&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, &lt;&lt;Just seven fruits (counter) of bread.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa dèu lowe he, ta mejèd'èipa wurai. Èla pe mi nahère, ta èba ke ri Noo ne roti do pidèu b'ue he, j'e heb'aj'a ta peha'e lii ie ae pa Deo. Ta pipe ke ri Noo ne roti he, j'e wie pa ana aj'a Noo he. J'e la peb'agi pa dèu lowe he.<bt>Then Yesus told all those people to sit on the earth. After that, he took those seven fruit of bread, and.so requested thankyou to God. Then he broke (into small pieces) that bread (with His hands) and.so gave it to his *disciples. Then they went dividing it out to the people.</bt><v n="7" />Nara lema roo pèri ngi'u nadèu. Hebaj'a wari Yesus ta ami terima kasi pa Deo tuu nadèu he. Ta lii ke pa ana aj'a Noo, ta la peb'agi pa dèu lowe he.<bt>They also had a few bodies (counter) of fish. Yesus requested thankyou again to God for that fish. Then He told His *disciples to go divide it out again to those people.</bt><v n="8-9" />Era ma roo harièle do èpa tèb'a dèu. Nga'a roo tade b'èhu. Ta èla roo pe nga'a, ta pekupu ke ri ana aj'a Noo, ne do rihi he, tobo pidèu hope worena. Ta lii ke Yesus pa roo ta b'ale.<bt>They all were 4,000 people. They ate until they were full. After finishing eating then, the disciples collected the leftovers, full 7 baskets2. After that, Yesus told them all to go home.</bt><v n="10" />Ta ludèuroo, ta ha'e ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo la d'ara kowa, j'e pekèd'èila hewue era, ne ngara noo Dalmanuta.<bt>When they had gone, then Yesus and his disciples got into the boat to go to a place named Dalmanuta.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pemae = hancurkan; 9: hope worena"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pemae = hancurkan; 9: hope worena = large basket; 10: ludu = lewat, left</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Do Parisi kale lai ta pebue Yesus<bt>Parisi people want to bring down Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 16:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Mi nahère Yesus he ne puru pa Dalmanuta, dèka ke do pèri dèu ti kejie Parisi la pehapo nga Noo. Ne dèka roo ta la pekerèi-keb'ali nga Yesus ta kale lai ta hie Noo. Ta ami roo pa Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ped'elo ko pa j'ii ne lai madalae ta he èhi rutada, ta kuaha do era pa Èu, ngati Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (collective) disembarked at Dalmanuta, then there were several people from the Parisi people came to meet Him. They came to debate with Yesus to try and find a way to trap Him. They requested of Him, saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Show us-exc *miracles as a sign that You really have gotten your *power/authority from God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kale lai = cari hal ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kale lai = cari hal ; pebue = kasi jato ; kewèhu = aturan, penetapan ; pekerèi-keb'ali = soal-jawab ; hie = jerat, hiki ; telia = tanda, indicator ; rutada = sign, (bukti)</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 12:38, Luka 11:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta hèpi hengaa ke Yesus pemèdèu j'e lii pa roo, &lt;&lt;Menyaha ne ade Yaa ne rèngi lii ami muu. Ta ngaa ke muu ne ami rutada madalae? B'ole mi nahère. Era ma pa Yaa ne lua madalae nee, tapulara pengède d'o pa muu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus drew a long breath, and told them, &lt;&lt;My liver regrets when I hear your-pl request. Why are you asking for miracles? Don't do that! I do have miracles (lit. there are miracles at Me), but I won't display them for you-pl.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Menyaha = menyesal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Menyaha = menyesal</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 12:39, Luka 11:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ta hani ke roo ri Yesus, j'e ha'e b'ale la d'ara kowa nga ana aj'a Noo he. J'e pekèd'èiroo la heb'èka èi lobo.<bt>And then, Yesus went leaving them to go get back in the boat with his disciples. Then they left to go the lake's other side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus lii ta jaga-meniga ti lai apa do Parisi<bt>Yesus says to watch.out.for/be.careful.of the Parisi people's evil</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 16:5-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta d'ai Yesus he la telora èi lobo, ta henge ri ana aj'a Noo he, taa d'o do èba nga'a-nginu. Hewue we ne roti èba roo.<bt>When Yesus (collective) arrived in the middle of the lake, the *disciples remembered that they forgot to bring food (doublet). They had only brought one fruit (counter) of bread.</bt><v n="15" />Ta rèngi roo nga pedai roti, ta lii ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Meniga pe woie muu! B'ole luu muu ri lai apa do dèka ti dèue Herode nga do Parisi he. Ne lai apa roo do j'ala mi ragi do pekiwu pa terigu ta peha'e roti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing them talk about bread, Yesus said, &lt;&lt;You-pl must be careful! Don't you be deceived by raja Herode and the Parisi people's evil. Their evil spreads like yeast which is mixed in to raise bread.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lai apa = kejahatan; 15: pej'a'i"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lai apa = kejahatan; 15: pej'a'i = whispering ; meniga = jaga, hati-hati, awas ; luu = tertipu ; muu = mur ; j'ala = merambat ; bibi = bibit roti</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 12:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ta rènge ne lii pedai Noo mi nahère, b'ingu ana aj'a Noo. Ta pedai ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Tada d'o dii lii pedai Noo ne! Maga-maga dii ta d'o èba roti ku pedai Noo mi nahii.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Him talk like that, His disciples were confused. Then they talked.to.each.other saying, &lt;&lt;What is He saying? Probably He is talking like that, because we-ex forgot to bring bread.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ingu = bingung (can also be"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ingu = bingung (can also be from mental illness); piku kètu = shake their heads ; Wuri Ae ~ dokepai = beliau ; Maga-maga = jang-jang, barangkali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Toi ri Yesus ne lua pengee roo. Ta lii ke Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa muu hèku pedai j'ara dod'o b'ule nga èba roti? Tada ded'o muu ne pedèb'o lii Yaa? D'ai rèpo ne kewadèukètu muu!<bt>But Yesus knew their thinking. So he talked saying, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl only just talking about not bringing bread? You don't catch My meaning, do you? Your brains are really exceedingly dense (metaphor = no space for anything to move, so not agile)!</bt><v n="18" />Ngèdi ke ri namada muu miha, tapulara pee ma muu nga d'o tada. Mi do b'èdèuhe muu. Rèngi ke ri wodilu muu miha, tapulara pee ma muu nga d'o tada nengaa-ngaa. Mi do hoe he muu. Bèlu ke muu<bt>You have seen with your own eyes, but you still don't know its meaning! Same as if you never saw/are blind. You hear with your very own ears, but you don't understand anything. Same as if you are deaf! You have forgotten</bt><note reference="8:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yermia 5:21, Yeskia 12:2, Ma'u 4:12</note><v n="19" />ne roti do lèmi b'ue do pipe ri Yaa, j'e penga'a do lèmi tèb'a dèu he? Pekupu ri muu do hewari nee, ne do rihi pèri hope?&gt;&gt;<bt>those 5 fruits of bread that I broke(into small pieces) to feed those 5,000 people, have you? That previous day you gathered that bread's leftovers how many baskets?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèpo = padat, noo space (brain"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rèpo = padat, noo space (brain can't function) ; kewadu kètu = otak</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">B'ale ri roo, &lt;&lt;Henguru d'ue hope.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, &lt;&lt;12 baskets..&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Keb'ali wari Yesus, &lt;&lt;Hewina ko ri muu ne roti do pidèu b'ue do pipe ri Yaa, j'e penga'a do èpa tèb'a dèu he? Pekupu ri muu do rihi pèri hope?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked again, &lt;&lt;You still remember that time I broke those 7 loaves of bread to feed those 4,000 people, do you? You gathered leftovers how many baskets (generic)?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">B'ale ri roo, &lt;&lt;Pidèuhope worena, Ama ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, &lt;&lt;7 large.baskets, Father!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ane Yesus, &lt;&lt;Do petuu! Ngèdi ke ri namada muu miha, tapulara ta ngaa muu ku pee nga d'o tada, ta dèka ti mii ne kuaha do pa Yaa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;That's correct! You have already seen with the eyes on your very own heads, but why do you still not yet understand where my *power/authority comes from?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie do b'èdèupa Batsaida<bt>Yesus *heals a blind person at Betsaida</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ta d'ai rike Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo la rae Betsaida. Ta dèka ke ne dèu nga ègo he dèu do b'èdèunga Yesus. Ne ami roo pa Yesus, mij'e ta pe'ie ne namada dèu na ène.<bt>After that, Yesus and His disciples arrived at Betsaida village. There people came and brought a blind person to Yesus. They requested Yesus heal that person's eyes.</bt><v n="23" />Ta pera'o ke ri Yesus ne do b'èdèune la tele rae. Ta hebue ke ne ilu Noo pa namada dèu na ène, j'e b'uje ri Noo. Keb'ali Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi namii? Ngèdi ke èu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus took that blind person's hand to take him outside the village. Then he spit His spittle into that person's eyes, then He touched (them). He asked saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? Can you see?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'èdu = buta; 23: pera'o ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'èdu = buta; 23: pera'o = tarik, bimbing, tuntun ; hebue = sembur ; penyi'o = meludah ke tanah ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta d'ede ke ne tangamada noo, j'e heleo ke la keriu-keg'ana, ta b'ale ke ri noo, &lt;&lt;Wa! Ngèdi ke yaa dèu do kako. Tapulara era mi aj'u do kako!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person lifted his face to look left-right, then he responded, &lt;&lt;Wa! I see people walking. But it's like trees are walking!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="keriu-keg'ana = left-right"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">keriu-keg'ana = left-right</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ta tèke rike ne wolaèba Yesus pa namada dèu nee. Ta hèku rike noo ta heleo, ngèdi woie ke.<bt>Then Yesus put again His hand on that person's eyes. Then that person tried to look again, now he could see clearly.</bt><v n="26" />Ta pejue ke noo ri Yesus ta b'ale la èmu, j'e tèka lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ale we èu lake ruj'ara do wala! B'ole lake ri j'ara Betsaida.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered him to.go.home, then he instructed him, saying, &lt;&lt;You go.home by a different road! Don't return again by the Betsaida road.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèka lii = pesan ; ra'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèka lii = pesan ; ra'a lii = susun bhs</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua ketèra Petu ta Yesus nee, Kristus, do pej'èu'e ri Deo rai uru<bt>Petu confesses that Yesus [is] Kristus, the person whom God had appointed from long ago</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 16:13-20; Luka 9:18-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Èla pe na ène, ta nèru ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he la rae-kowa pa Kaisarea-Filipi. Pa telora ruj'ara, ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Pedèuu nga lii pedai dèu, nadèu ke Yaa na d'ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>And after that, Yesus and His disciples walked the villages in Kaisarea-Filipi. In the middle of the road Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;If you follow people's story, who am I?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lua ketèra = pengakuan sungguh-sungguh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Lua ketèra = pengakuan sungguh-sungguh</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ane roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Era do lii, ta &lt;Johani, mone peherani dèu&gt;. Era do lii ta &lt;Elia&gt;, mone ub'a Deo do uru he. Era lema do lii, ta hala he dèu ngati mone ub'a Deo do wala he pa awe do uru.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;There are those who say &lt;Johani the One.who.habitually baptizes people&gt;. There are those who say &lt;Elia&gt;, God's *prophets from long.ago. There are others who say one of God's other *prophets (spokesperson) from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="8:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ma'u 6:14-15, Luka 9:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta keb'ali rike Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;Pedèuu tade ri muu miha, nadèu ke Yaa na d'ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked them again saying, &lt;&lt;According to you-pl yourself, who am I?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta b'ale ke ri Petu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Èu ke Kristus! Do èla pe pej'èu'e ri Deo rai uru.&gt;&gt;<bt>Petu answered saying, &lt;&lt;You are Kristus! The one God has appointed/designated from long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="8:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Johani 6:68-69</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ta lara ke ri Yesus, ta &lt;&lt;B'ole pedai nga nadèu-nadèu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell anyone at all!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus ped'èii d'ènge j'ara lua hedèu nga made Noo<bt>Yesus fore tells/reveals His suffering and death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 16:21-28; Luka 9:22-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta j'ari ke Yesus ta pika pa ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu. Hine do ta lake ri Yaa ae lua hedèu, ri do ta nyèke Yaa ri dokepai rae he, ketèu ngati kètu agama he, nga guru agama he. Do ta pemade Yaa ri roo, tapulara muri wari Yaa nèli.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus started to tell His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;I here, am the True/Prototype Human. Later I will get much suffering, because the traditional leaders, the religious leaders (*priests), and the religion teachers all will reject Me. They will kill Me, but exactly on the day.after.the.following.day [CHECK dialect clash diff words for "day after tomorrow"], I live again.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Seba nèli = lusa ; hemèd'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Seba nèli = lusa ; hemèd'a = tula BUT Dimu has noo nèli, and hemèd'a = lusa @@ !! ***</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate and rejected</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Ta rèngi ne lii pika Yesus, ta la pera'o ke Yesus ri Petu la keraha. J'e tèka lii noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ole pedai mi nahère, Ama ee! Wie d'o ri yaa ta d'ai ai roo pa Ama!&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard what Yesus said, then Petu pulled Yesus to the side. He scolded saying, &lt;&lt;Father shouldn't talk like that! I won't allow them to connect their hand against (physical abuse) Father.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ari = mulai @@@@ (PUT stuff"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'ari = mulai @@@@ (PUT stuff of board in dictionary!!); 32: d'ai ai = sampai tangan, harm, pukul, menyakiti</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Tapulara ne lii pedai Petu ad'o do hela'u nga d'èi Deo. Ta b'ale hed'apa ke Yesus nga ana aj'a do wala he. J'e j'ege ri Noo Petu, &lt;&lt;Lii pedai kètu wango he na ène! Lènga ti d'ee! Ad'o èu do pengee ne lua do d'èi Deo, pengee ne lua do d'èi dèu rai-wawa we!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petu's talk wasn't according to God's will. Then Yesus turned.to face his other disciples. Then he scolded Petu, &lt;&lt;That's *Satan speaking! Get out of here! You-s only just think human's will/desires, not God's will.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pekèta = sesuai, sama ; pelèka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pekèta = sesuai, sama ; pelèka = kena</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Satanaa: Devil</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ta pedoa ke ri Yesus ne dèu lowe he la pe'obo nga ana aj'a Noo he. J'e aj'a roo ri Noo, &lt;&lt;Nadèu do d'èi ta pedèue Yaa, mèka tee noo ta pedèue helod'o-helod'o. Hore ne lua do d'èi miha, j'e pedèue ne lua do d'èi Deo we. Maji lema ta era dèu do ta pemade noo, pee ma nga pedèuu teruu, mi dèu do nga hape aj'u ketoe ta la pemade.<bt>And then Yesus called other people to gather with his disciples. Then He taught them, &lt;&lt;Whoever wants to follow Me, he must follow continually every day! He must throw.away his own will/desires, to just follow the God's will/desires. Even if someone wants to kill him/her, s/he must just keep on following, just like someone shoulder.carrying his/her *cross (hanging pole/tree) to go die/be killed.</bt><note reference="8:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:38, Luka 9:23, 14:27</note><v n="35" />Dèu do d'èi ta muri mada tuu ngi'u miha, do ta ele ne muri mada noo nga mi nahère we! Tapulara nadèu do moko ta la made taga pedèue Yaa, nga pepeke ne ruj'ara muri mada do d'èi Deo, do ta muri loro noo hela'u nga Deo.<bt>The person who only wants to live just for his own self, it will disappear/be lost just like that! But whoever is ready to die because he follows Me and tells God's Life Way, later he will be able to live continually with God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:39, Luka 17:33, Johani 12:25</note><v n="36" />D'èno we! Kiri bab'o ri èu harièle ihi hewue rai-wawa d'ee, tapulara nyèke èu ri Deo, ngaa ne nara èu?<bt>Listen, we! If you-s obtain the world's entire contents, but God rejects you, what have you gained?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psykhees: this is not eternal life,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">psykhees: this is not eternal life, the life characteristic of the age to come; it's life as a person has it right now</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Maji lema ta èbe ri èu hari ihi hewue rai-wawa na d'ee, nara d'o ta pehure nga muri mada do peloro nga Deo!<bt>Even if you also carry away the world's entire contents, you can't exchange it with eternal life with God!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèka = mampu ; tee ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèka = mampu ; tee = bertahan ; hore = buang ; aj'u ketoe = tiang gantungan, jaman dulu dipake untuk gantung orang sebagai hukuman (dari raja), ada yg sampe mati, juga jaman Jepang ; aj'u lèba-tèlu = crossed wood (simbol orang Jinitiu, pake di kandang hewan, mungkin untuk melindungi hewan); 35: moko = siap, sedia; 36: bab'o = garap semua; 37: pehoo ~ pehure = tukar ; pehoo can also mean tebus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you pay to get back something in exchange (for your life): there is nothing that would compensate you for such a loss.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Henge ie ri muu! Dèu rai-wawa pa d'ara awe na d'ee, muri mada pa d'ara ae kera'a apa-kerewe. Ped'uli d'o ke roo ta pedèue Deo. Hèku nadèu do mekae d'ara ta pedèue Yaa, ki ad'o mekae d'ara ta pèro lii pedai Yaa, mekae d'ara lema Yaa ta hème noo pa hed'apa Deo. Rowi Yaa, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu na d'ee, hine do ta dèka wari ti liru-bèla. Nga dèu pejuu Deo he, dèka hela'u nga Yaa. Ne puru j'ii ti liru-bèla nga kuaha Deo do mèu-megala, itu toi Yaa ri dèu, nadèu Yaa na d'ee.<bt>Remember well! This people in the world now live in all sorts of evil (doublet). They don't care about following God. So whoever is embarrassed/ashamed to follow Me, or else embarrassed to hold My words/teachings/sayings, I also will be embarrassed/ashamed to accept him before God. Cuz I, this True/Prototype Human here, I will return from *heaven (doublet). With God's *angels also will come together with Me. We-ex will come.down from heaven with God's extraordinary power/authority which is *glorious (doublet= shining-clean/holy), only.then will people know who I here am.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ped'uli = perduli ; mekae d'ara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ped'uli = perduli ; mekae d'ara = malu ; mèu-megala = bersih-bersinar/bercahaya , also kemuliaan; kerihi = terlebih</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />B'ole bèlo ri muu ne lii pedai Yaa na d'ee. Era ti telora muu na hee, dod'o made, do ta ngède Deo do pereda nga kuaha Noo do kerihi.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl don't forget what I am saying here. There are those from among you-pl here, who will not die, but will be able to see God's governing with great power.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus do wala wewo pa kolo lede<bt>Yesus' changes/becomes different on top of a mountain</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 17:1-13; Luka 9:28-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Èna lod'o èla pe na ène, ta ègu ke Petu, J'ako nga Johani ri Yesus, la hewue lede do d'èia, do kehii. Ta d'ai roo la kolo lede nee, ngède ri roo ne Yesus èla ke pe rihu èni.<bt>After six days then, Yesus took Petu, J'ako and Johani, up a tall mountain that was empty (of people). When they got to the top, they saw Yesus had changed/become different.</bt><v n="3" />Ne b'ara pake Noo do pudi kewa'a, do weo do kana. B'ule d'o b'ara pa rai-wawa na ène do wo pudi kelala mi b'ara pake Noo.<bt>And His clothes had become pure shining white. In this world there is nothing that is whiter that those clothes of His.</bt><v n="4" />Pa d'ara awe na ène d'ènge, ta ngède ke ri roo Yesus era do pedai lii nga Elia nga Musa.<bt>Suddenly, then they could see Yesus was talking with Elia and Musa.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="worèwu = face ; wewo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">worèwu = face ; wewo = bentuk yg lain ; rihu èni = berubah sendiri; 3: pudi kewa'a = white Max ; do weo do kana = bersinar ; kelala = kain sutra ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Petu he made ri meda'u. B'ale Petu ta b'ingu ke, tade pedai wala. Ta lii ke noo pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama. Rihi woie dii pa d'ee! Rihi ie j'ii ta petitu tèlu b'ue leo. Hewue tuu Ama, hewue tuu Musa, nga hewue tuu Elia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Petu mob were really frightened. And Petu was just confused, to-point-that he talked aimlessly. So he told Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Father! It's really good we-ex are here! So it would be a good idea if we-ex erected three open.huts. One for Father, one for Musa, and one for Elia.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pedai wala = omong sembarang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pedai wala = omong sembarang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ta dèka ke ne merèmu la herimu roo. J'e rènge ri roo ne lii pedai ti d'ara merèmu nee, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;D'èno we. Yesus na d'ee, Ana d'èi Yaa. Ped'èno ie we muu nga Noo!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, then a cloud come to blanket them. Then they heard a voice come out of that cloud, saying, &lt;&lt;Listen! This Yesus, is My beloved Child. You-pl just listen carefully to Him!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="merèmu = awan ; herimu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">merèmu = awan ; herimu = selimuti</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:2-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Petu 1:17-18; Mateo 3:17, Ma'u 1:11, Luka 3:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ta rènge ri Petu he ne lii pedai na ène, heleo pehero ke ri roo pa era na ène. B'ule d'o dèu do hewala pa ène, wala ngati Yesus miha.<bt>When Petu mob heard that voice, they looked all.around that place. They could not see the other people there, other than Yesus himself.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Èla pa mi nahère, ta puru ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he ti kolo lede na ène. Pa d'ara puru roo, ta tèka lii ke Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole ped'èii muu pa nadèu we, nengaa ne do ngèdi ri muu ngine. Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu, made uru ko. Kiri muri wari Yaa, j'e'itu pepeke ri muu pa dèu lowe.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and His *disciples started going down that mountain. While they were descending, Yesus instructed them, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell anyone, what you just saw. I here, the True/Prototype Human, must die first. When I am alive again, only.then may you-pl tell other people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Pedèuu tèra roo nga lii tèka Yesus, b'ule d'o roo nga pedai nga he dèu tèra he. Ta pekeb'ali ke roo tèlu, &lt;&lt;Nengaa ke ne pedèb'o lii pedai Noo, ta &lt;Muri wari ki èla pemade? Mi namii?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>They really followed that instruction of Yesus, and they really didn't tell a single person. The three asked.each.other, &lt;&lt;What did He mean, saying that He will &lt;Live again after being killed? How's that?&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ta keb'ali ke roo pa Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ane guru agama he, &lt;Elia ta dèka uru, j'e'itu dèka Kristus.&gt; Pedèuu lii Ama, mi namii?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they asked Him, &lt;&lt;Those religion teachers say &lt;Elia must come first, only.then Kristus comes.&gt; According to Father, how is it?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 4:5, Mateo 11:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Tèra, do petuu! Dèka uru ko Elia, ma pemoke ruj'ara tuu Kristus, do pej'èu'e ri Deo rai uru he. Mi namii? Pee ko ma muu nga dod'o tada nengaa ne do hure do b'uke j'ara lua Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu ne? Do lore ke pe b'uke ki ri dèka Noo, do ta pehedèu Noo ri dèu, j'e pemade.<bt>Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;That's true! Elia must come first to prepare the path/way for Kristus, that person that God has designated from before. How is it? You-pl don't yet understand what was written about that True/Prototype Human? They have written, that when He comes, people will cause Him difficulty and murder/kill (Him).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do b'uke pa d'ara b'uku Deo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">do b'uke pa d'ara b'uku Deo do mèu-megala = written in the scriptures</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />D'èno pe'ie ri muu. Elia, èla ke pedèka. Tapulara, pehedèu noo ri dèu, pedèuu nga d'èi roo. Harièle na hère petobe ne lai do b'uke ri mone ub'a Deo rai uru he.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you must listen carefully. Elia has already come. But people made difficulty for him following their own will. And all that also was exactly like what God's spokesmen had written earlier.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hure = b'uke = tulis ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hure = b'uke = tulis ; lore ke pe b'uke = sudah ditulis duluan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie he dèu naiki do maho ri wango apa<bt>Yesus heals a child afflicted with an evil *evil spirit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 17:14-21; Luka 9:37-43a)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta d'ai Yesus nga do tèlu ana aj'a Noo he, la pekupu wari nga ana aj'a do had'e he, era rike ne dèu lowe he do pekupu. Ne lua dèka dèu lowe he, ta la heleo ne ana aj'a Yesus he pa d'ara peb'aj'a nga guru agama Jahudi he.<bt>When Yesus and those 3 disciples of His meet again with the other disciples, they could see many people gathered. Those many people had come to see Yesus' other disciples debate with the Jahudi religious teachers.</bt><v n="15" />Mi nahère ne ngède Yesus ri dèu lowe he, ta keb'èdi hala ke roo, rowi pa d'ara peira roo, Yesus do pa kolo lede ne ko. Moko ke roo ta perai la pehapo nga Noo.<bt>When those many people saw Yesus, they were surprised, cuz they thought/assumed He was still on top the mountain. Then they ran to meet Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="goa = bisu ; peb'aj'a ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">goa = bisu ; peb'aj'a = bertengkar, adu pendapat; 15: keb'èdi hala = takuju ; peira = perkiraan, sangka</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Peb'aj'a nengaa muu pa d'ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked them, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl are debating what here?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Dèka he dèu la pika, &lt;&lt;Ama. D'èno ko ri Ama! Yaa ne èba ana yaa do momone, pe'ie ko we noo, ri Ama. Do b'ènga noo, i'a do pedai lii, pelai ti maho ri wango.<bt>There was a person who came saying, &lt;&lt;Father. Listen please! I have brought my boy child, so.that Father can heal him. He is dumb, can't talk, cuz he is afflicted/entered by *evil spirit(s).</bt><v n="18" />Kiri maho ke ne wango ne la d'ara noo, ta wèbe b'ure-b'ure ke ri noo pa rai. Tade woro ne ub'a, pekiho ne ngutu. J'e hekoto noo mi aj'u made he. Èla ke ri yaa pe'ami ne ana aj'a Èu he, ta hud'e ne wango nee, tapulara jad'èi d'o.&gt;&gt;<bt>If/when that evil spirit has entered into him, he hits and hits this child's body on the earth. To the point that the child's mouth foams, and he grinds his teeth. Then his body is stiff like dry wood. I have requested Your disciples to help expel that evil spirit, but it didn't happen.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="g'ug'e = kocok, kucak ; wèbe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">g'ug'e = kocok, kucak ; wèbe = pukul ; b'ure-b'ure = ulang-ulang ; riho-riho = balik-balik ; woro = buih ; pekiho = grind ; ngutu = teeth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ta j'aga ke ri Yesus ne ana aj'a he, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Rihi tèra muu! Aj'a loro-loro muu ri Yaa, pe ma muu ngad'o tada. Ad'o muu d'o parahaj'a petuu nga Yaa. Hape la mii ke Yaa ne mèka-wènge pehed'apa nga muu? Èbe ko ma d'ee, naiki ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus got angry at the disciples, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl are just too much! (exasperation) I have taught you over and over/daily, but you don't understand. And you don't believe truly in Me! I must be patient with you until when! Bring that child here!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="20" />Ta hero'e ke ri roo ne naiki ne nga Yesus. Ta ngède Yesus ri wango nee, ta hore ke ri noo naiki ne la wurai, peb'are-gore pa ène. Woro ne ub'a noo.<bt>Then they carried that child to Yesus. When that evil spirit saw Yesus, then he threw that child until he fell rolling around on the ground. His mouth was foaming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'aga (jamak) = j'ege (tunggal) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'aga (jamak) = j'ege (tunggal) ; mèka-wènge = sabar; 20: peb'are-gore = taguling-guling</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa ama naiki nee, &lt;&lt;Rai pèri ke nee, naiki ne pèd'a do mi nahee?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Yesus asked that child's father, &lt;&lt;Your-s child has been like this here, for how long?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">B'ale ri ama noo, &lt;&lt;Rai tana iki.<bt>His father answered saying, &lt;&lt;Since he was little.</bt><v n="22" />Tui ke ne wango nee, ne d'èi ta pemade noo. J'aj'i wari ke noo, ne bui la d'ara rao ai, ki ad'o pebole pa d'ara èi. Ruba ko we, ne d'ara Ama. Ki jad'èi he, pe'ie ko ri Ama ne naiki na d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>That evil spirit for a long time has wanted to kill him. He makes fall him over and over in the fire, and makes him submerge/drown in water. Father, please help/have pity! If possible, Father heal this child.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rao ai = (tempat) api ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rao ai = (tempat) api ; pebole = tenggelamkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ku lii, &lt;ki jad'èi ? Jad'èiri Yaa harièle, had'èita parahaj'a we nga Yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;Why do you-s say &lt;if possible&gt;? I can do all, as.long as (you/people) believe in Me first!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta b'ale ke ri ama naiki nee, nga he mèri ta tangi, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Do parahaj'a ma ke yaa. Ruba we ne d'ara perue riko ne parahaj'a yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the child's father answered and just about to cry, saying, &lt;&lt;Father! I believe. Help so.that my belief is even stronger!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perue = kasi kuat ; lua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">perue = kasi kuat ; lua mèno = iman</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Pa awe na ène, ngèdi ri Yesus ae ke ne dèu do dèka la peworo la ène. Ta pereda ke ri Noo pa wango nee, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wango apa! Mèhu èni we èu ti d'ara naiki na d'ee, mij'e nara ta rèngi, i'a noo pedai lii. B'ole b'ale wari èu la d'ara noo!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus saw many people already come crowding there. Then he commanded that evil spirit saying, &lt;&lt;Evil evil.spirit! You-s get out of this child (imperative), so.that he can hear, and he can speak. You don't enter him again!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ège = usir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ège = usir</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ta rènge ne lii pereda Yesus ri wango nee, ta pekaa ke noo pemèdèumèdèu Ta pekelole ke ri noo ne naiki nee, j'e ked'èji-d'èji, j'e mèhu èni noo ti d'ara naiki nee. Hekoto ne naiki, mi do made he. Ane ne lii dèu pa ène, &lt;&lt;Made ke naiki ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus command like that, then that evil spirit yelled loudly. He made that child fall convulsing, only.then exited from inside him. That child fainted just like he was already dead. The people there talked saying, &lt;&lt;The child is dead!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pekelole = banting di tanah ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pekelole = banting di tanah ; ked'èji-d'èji = convulse,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ta pèro ke ri Yesus ne naiki nee, j'e pekèd'e noo. Ta kèd'èid'ènge ke noo.<bt>But Yesus held that child's hand and helped get him up. Then that child stood up immediately.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta pekèd'èike Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo ti ène, j'e maho roo la d'ara hewue èmu. Roo ke miha, pa d'ara èmu nee, ta keb'ali ke ne ana aj'a he pa Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ta ngaa j'ii ku d'o nara ta hud'e ne wango ne?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus and his disciples left and entered into a house. When they were alone in the house his disciples asked Yesus, &lt;&lt;Father! Why earlier couldn't we-ex expel that evil spirit?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;D'èno ko ri muu pe woie! Wango he do apa. Ki d'o heb'aj'a muu ta ami kuaha ngati Deo, nara d'o muu ta hud'èiwango do mi nahii.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told them, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully! Evil.spirits are indeed evil. If you-pl don't pray request power/authority from God, obviously, you will not be able to expelling an evil spirit of that type.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pedai wari j'ara lua made Noo<bt>Yesus speaks once again about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 17:22-23; Luka 9:43b-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ta pekèd'èirike Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he ngati ène, la propensi Galilea. Ne d'èi Noo, b'ole era do toi ri dèu ne lua dèka roo la nii,<bt>After that, Yesus with His disciples left that place, going to Galilea province. His desire was to not want people to know He had come there,</bt><v n="31" />ri ne d'èi Noo ta aj'a ne ana aj'a Noo he we. Ta lii ke Noo nga roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Tui d'oke, j'e pewie Yaa ri he dèu pa dèu do wola. J'e pemade Yaa ri roo, do Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu d'ee. Tèra Yaa ta made, tapulara pa nèli, ta muri wari.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz He wanted only to teach just his disciples. He told them, saying, &lt;&lt;Not much longer, someone wants to *betray (sell) Me to other (foreign; non-us) people. They will kill Me, this True/Prototype Human. I'll actually die, but later on the day.after.the.following.day, I'll live again.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ta pika Yesus mi nahère, ta b'ingu ke roo pelai ta d'o tada roo. B'ani d'o ke roo ta keb'ali ne lua pedèb'o Yesus.<bt>Yesus told like that, but His disciples were confused. They didn't dare ask more what Yesus' intention was.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ana aj'a Yesus peb'ata ta nadèu ne do ke rihi<bt>Yesus' disciples debate about who is greater/more</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 18:1-5; Luka 9:46-48)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ta nèru rike Yesus he la Kapernaum. Ta d'ai roo ne maho la d'ara èmu, ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa ana aj'a he, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Peb'at'a nengaa ke muu pa ruj'ara he ngine?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then after that, Yesus (collective) travel on to Kapernaum. As they entered into a house, then Yesus asked his disciples, saying, &lt;&lt;Earlier you-pl were debating what on the road/journey?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peluru = bergumul, ; peb'ata ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peluru = bergumul, ; peb'ata = bertengkar ; pelulu = berguling</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />B'ule d'o he dèu he do b'ani ta b'ale, ri pa ruj'ara he ngine do peb'ata roo ta nadèu ne do rihi pa telora roo.<bt>There was not anyone brave to reply, cuz on the journey they had been arguing about who was the greatest from them all.</bt><note reference="9:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 22:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ta mejèd'èike Yesus, j'e aj'a roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Nadèu do d'èi ta dèu do ke rihi, muri mada noo petuu-petuu mi do ènu do pemoko dèu lowe.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus sat to teach them saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever wants to be a great/important person, his life must really-really be like that of a *slave/servant who serves other/many people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peketèu èni = angkat diri bos"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peketèu èni = angkat diri bos ; dèu kako-kèd'i = pelayan, servant KT (not known by UNS's) ; hewewe (wrong exeg, turned on head again) ; noo = dia ;</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 20:26-27, 23:11, Ma'u 10:43-44, Luka 22:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ta hero'e ke ri Yesus he dèu naiki, j'e b'ale pa telora roo. J'e lii Noo,<bt>Then Yesus pick.up.embracing a small child, and.so He returned to their middle. Then He spoke,</bt><v n="37" />&lt;&lt;Nadèu do pedèue Yaa, j'e pemoko dèu mi naiki na d'ee, ne pedèb'o nee, dèu na ène lema do pemoke Yaa. Lai na ène lema, pemoke Ama do pejue Yaa ma rai-wawa d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Whoever follows Me and.so serves a small people like this child, its meaning, that person also is serving Me. And he also is serving My Father who appointed Me to come to this world.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="petito = kasi badiri ; b'uri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">petito = kasi badiri ; b'uri = potong</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:40, Luka 10:16, Johani 13:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Nadèu do jad'èi ita dèu kejie dii?<bt>Who is a person of our-inc group?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 9:49-50)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Moko ta kelaa ke Johani, ana aj'a Yesus, ane noo, &lt;&lt;Ama. Hewari, era he dèu do hud'èiwango nga pake ngara Èu. Tapulara ta lara ke noo ri j'ii, ri ad'o noo kejie dii.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus' disciple Johani objected/complained/protested saying, &lt;&lt;Father. One time, there was a person using Your name to expel evil spirits. But we-ex forbade him, cuz he was not of our-inc (social)group.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kelaa = protes, pengaduan, keberatan ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kelaa = protes, pengaduan, keberatan ; b'ate = larang, bantah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;B'ole lara noo. Ri nadèu do pake ngara Yaa, ta tao madalae, ad'o noo ta pe'ape ngara Yaa.<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Don't forbid him. Cuz whoever uses My name to do *miracles, he is not going to speak making My name rotten (talk bad about).</bt><v n="40" />Ki ad'o noo do pelawa nga dii, tatu noo lema kejie dii.<bt>If he is not opposing us-inc, he is surely also our-inc group.</bt><note reference="9:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 12:30, Luka 11:23</note><v n="41" />Henge pe'ie ri muu! Kiri era dèu do tada muu ta dèu do pedèue Kristus, j'e rab'a-d'èru muu, tatu ta d'o bèlo ri Deo ne lua lob'o noo. Maji lema muu ta penginu èi loko wue he we, bèlo d'o ri Deo ne lua woie noo.&gt;&gt;<bt>So Remember this well! If there is person who knows that you-pl follow Kristus, then they help (doublet) you, surely God is not going to forget that person's effort/sacrifice. Even if he only just gives one glass of plain water, God will not forget his goodness.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="muhu = musu ; pelawa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">muhu = musu ; pelawa = melawan ; pehihu = selisih ; tatu = tentu; 41: henèru-pelako = setia-layani ; rab'a-d'èru = bantu, tolong (sakit, lapar, sesat, move house) ; la'a rui = usaha (luas) ; lob'o = kecapaian, pengorbanan ; èi loko wue = air kosong ; lua woie = kebaikan</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:42</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">B'ole pemanga-manga nga hala-ludèu<bt>Don't play around with sin (doublet)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 18:6-9; Luka 17:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Ta pika rike Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ki era dèu do èbe he dèu naiki la ruj'ara do hala, moko ne naiki ne ta dod'o parahaj'a pa Yaa, jaga ie ó! Rihi ie dèu na ène, ta perète pa lakoko ri wowadu worena, j'e hore la lèu ae.<bt>Then Yesus told again to them saying, &lt;&lt;If a person who takes a small child along the wrong path, then that child doesn't believe anymore in Me, watch out, oo! It's better for that person, to suspend a large rock on his neck, then cast him into the deep sea.</bt><note reference="9:42" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani, wowadu do pake ta gili are-gandum ta tao lawo terigu.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying &lt;stone for milling&gt; that they use to mill grain-wheat to make flour.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ki pake kae-nga'a èu ta tao hala-ludu, ète j'e hore! Rihi ie èu ta maho la muri mada nga Deo nga he laa kae, ngata hore èu la d'ara ai naraka nga d'ue laa kae.<bt>If you-sg do wrong (doublet) using your hand, just cut.off throw.away! It's better to enter life with God with just one hand, rather than (they) throw you away into the fire of *hell (assimilated loan) with both hands.</bt><note reference="9:43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 5:30</note><v n="44" />[Ne naraka nee, era hedui-herui. Ne ai pa nii, do peloro-loro. Lema ne ètu pa ène, nga'a pewèu peb'èku loro-loro ne dèu do maho la ène.]<bt>[That hell, is a suffering place (doublet). Its fire doesn't ever go out. And the worms there they also don't stop making the people who enter there rotten.]</bt><note reference="9:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ad'o do b'uke ne ayat na d'ee (44) pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do rihi wodui he.<bt>In the oldesr Greek language Bible this verse 44 isn't written.</bt></note><v n="45" />Ki pake kae-j'èla èu ta tao hala-ludu, ète j'e hore! Rihi ie èu ta maho la muri mada nga Deo nga he laa kae, ngata hore èu la d'ara ai naraka nga d'ue laa kae.<bt>If you-sg do wrong using your foot, just cut.off throw.away that foot. Its better you enter life with God with your one foot, than (they) throw you into the fire of hell, with both of your feet.</bt><v n="46" />[Ne naraka nee, era hedui-herui. Ne ai pa nii, do peloro-loro. Lema ne ètu pa ène, nga'a pewèu peb'èku loro-loro ne dèu do maho la ène.]<bt>[That hell, indeed a suffering place (doublet). Its fire doesn't ever go out. And the worms there they also don't stop making the people who enter there rotten.]</bt><note reference="9:46" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do rihi wodui, ad'o do b'uke ne ayat 46 d'ee.<bt>In the oldest Greek language Bible this verse 46 isn't written.</bt></note><v n="47" />Ki pake namada èu ta tao hala-ludu, ruke j'e hore! Rihi ie èu ta maho la muri mada nga Deo nga hewue namada, ngata hore èu la d'ara ai naraka nga d'ue b'ue namada.<bt>If you-sg do wrong using your eye, just dig.out throw.away that eye! It's better you enter life with God with one eye, than (they) throw you away into the fire of hell with both eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="topo = kudung ; naraka ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">topo = kudung ; naraka = KT ; laa = batang; 44: ètu = ulat, ; wèu = bau ; b'èku = busuk ; pewèu peb'èku; 46: wolo = hukuman; 47: ruke = cungkil, do'i (Dimu)</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 5:29</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="48" />&lt;Ne naraka nee, era hedui-herui.<bt>&lt;That hell, indeed a suffering (doublet) place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ne ai pa nii, do peloro-loro.<bt>Its fire there never goes out.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lema ne ètu pa ène, nga'a pewèu peb'èku loro-loro ne dèu do maho la ène.&gt;<bt>And the worms there, keep eating making rotten the people who enter there.&gt;</bt><note reference="9:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ne lii aj'a Yaa nee, do rihi ne mejèni. Naduu do d'èi ta pedute Yaa, do paraluu noo ta mèka tee ta pedute loro-loro Yaa, mi hed'ai do tao ri mengèhi j'e noe pa lod'o, mij'e ta d'o wèu, maji lema ta tèke petui.<bt>This teaching of Mine is very heavy. Whoever wants to follow Me, he must continually endure following Me day after day, like meat which people place salt to dry in the sun, so.that that meat does not rot, so it can endure/last a long time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèka tee = tahan kuat ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèka tee = tahan kuat ; mengèhe = garami (vt) ; mengèhi = garam (n) ; page = panggang ; hed'ai = daging ; tèke petui = disimpan lama</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Mengèhi do ie. Do nara ta pe woie nga'a. Tapulara ki ele ne hèro noo, b'ule d'oke noo nga guna. Ta hore heke. Hèku muu he, do ie ta jad'èi mi mengèhi he, tuu muri mada pehaj'a-ped'èi nga harièle dèu.<bt>Salt is good. It can make food tast good. But if it becomes non-salty, it has no more usefulness. Just get rid of it. So you-pl must be good like salt, to live in mutual love (doublet) with all people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="melae = rasa tawar ; heke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">melae = rasa tawar ; heke = saja ; pehaj'a-ped'èi = kasih-mengasihi, sayang dan kasih</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Pengaha we muu ne pelule j'ara lua naduu do rihi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa! Stop your jockeying for who is greatest!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 5:13, Luka 14:34-35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Do Parisi kale ruj'ara ta pebue Yesus j'ara lua banga-èmu nga pe'ela-peheg'i<bt>Parisi people look for way to trap Yesus about marriage-divorce</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 19:1-12; Luka 16:18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ta pekèd'èike Yesus he la propensi Yudea, nga era do hewala pa heb'èka bara dimu loko Yarden. Pa mii-pa mii we Noo ne era, dèka la pewore ri dèu lowe. Aj'a roo ri Yesus, mi pa tima.<bt>And then, Yesus (collective) went to Yudea province, and other places on the Yarden stream's east side. Everywhere He was, many people came crowding around. Like usual, Yesus taught them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'ela-peheg'i = kawin-cere"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'ela-peheg'i = kawin-cere</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Era do pèri dèu do Parisi ne dèka la kale lai ta pebue Yesus. Ta keb'ali roo, &lt;&lt;Pedutu lua petèka agama dii, momone do èla pebanga èmu, ie ta pe'ela-peheg'i, we ad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>There were several Parisi people who came to find issues to make Him fall (trap Him). They asked, &lt;&lt;According to our-inc religious regulations, if a man has married, can he divorce (doublet), or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pebanga èmu = kawin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pebanga èmu = kawin</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exestin: is it permitted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">exestin: is it permitted</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Henge ko ri muu! Lua petèka Musa j'ara lua banga-èmu, mi namii?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;Remember! Musa's husband-wife regulations say what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta b'ale ke ri roo, &lt;&lt;Lua petèka Musa, ie ma dèu ta pe'ela-peheg'i, had'èita wie ne huri pe'ela-peheg'i pa ihi-èmu noo do mobèni.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded, &lt;&lt;Musa's regulations say, people may divorce, as.long.as they make a divorce letter to his spouse.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hio = robek ; huri ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hio = robek ; huri = surat ; ihi-èmu = suami, isteri ; ihi èmu = isi rumah, keluarga</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 24:1-4, Mateo 5:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />B'ale ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu! Ta rihi paja kètu muu, ku b'uke ri Musa mi nahère!<bt>Yesus responded saying, &lt;&lt;Listen! Because your-pl stubborn heads, that's.the.reason Musa wrote like that!</bt><v n="6" />B'ole bèlo ri muu lii ped'èii petari rai awe tao ri Deo liru nga rai-wawa. Do b'uke, mihe ane,<bt>Don't you-pl forget that story of the beginning when God made heaven and earth! It's written that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Woro dèu rai-wawa ri Deo, momone nga mobèni.<bt>&lt;God made humans, male and female.</bt><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Ped'iri Pe'era Liru nga Rai-wawa 1:27, 5:2</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Ri mi nahère ke, ku momone do ta kèd'èiti d'ara kad'o ina-ama noo,<bt>That's.the.reason a male leaves the protection/comfort/lap of his mother-father,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'ara kad'o = dalam pangkuan, dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">d'ara kad'o = dalam pangkuan, dari pengawasan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">la muri mada hewue ade-pengee nga ihi-èmu noo,<bt>to go live one liver-thinking (Idiom=common purpose and looking out for each other) with his spouse,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peheuj'u ade = ikat satu hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peheuj'u ade = ikat satu hati (hidup bersama) ; hewue ade-pengee = satu hati satu pikiran (dame, serasi, aman, tidak ingat diri, dua-dua satu sumber)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">
      <v n="8" />ku hari do d'ue roo jad'èi he èhi.&gt;<bt>they two have now become one one2 (one unit).'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and other parallels.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Ped'iri Pe'era Liru nga Rai-wawa 2:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ki èla ke roo d'ue pe pejad'èi èhi ri Deo, ie d'o ta pe'ela wari ri dèu rai-wawa!&gt;&gt;<bt>If God himself has made them two become one, humans don't make divorce!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta maho ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he la d'ara hewue èmu. Ta keb'ali ke ri roo ne ihi lii aj'a do ngine nee.<bt>After that, Yesus and his disciples entered a house. There they asked about Yesus' teaching earlier.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ta peteleo ke ri Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Naduu do pe'ela nga ihi-èmu noo, j'e banga èmu wari nga mobèni do wala, èla ke noo petao lai kenyoo!<bt>Yesus explained saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever divorces throw.away his spouse, then marries again a different woman, that's already adultery!</bt><v n="12" />Mi nahère lema he dèu mobèni! Naduu do pe'ela nga ihi-èmu noo, j'e banga èmu wari nga momone do wala, èla lema ke noo petao lai kenyoo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Women also like that! If she divorces throws away her spouse, then marries again a different man, that's also adultery!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 5:32, 1 Korintu 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus mengao mèngi tuu naiki<bt>Yesus speaks giving *blessing to the children</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 19:13-15; Luka 18:15-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Hewari, ta dèka ke ne dèu nga èba ana roo nga Yesus, mij'e ta tèka ruai, j'e mengao ne mèngi tuu naiki. Ta b'ani ke ne ana aj'a Yesus nga roo.<bt>One time, people brought their children to Yesus, so that He place His hands and utter *blessing on the children. But Yesus' *disciples scolded them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèro ie-menyèro mèngi = kasi karunia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèro ie-menyèro mèngi = kasi karunia ; mengao = mengucapkan ; mengati = ucapkan (memohon dari pihak lain)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta ngèdi ri Yesus mi nahère, ta bubu d'ara ke Noo nga ana aj'a he, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Hani we ne naiki na hère, pe dèka nga Yaa! B'ole b'ata roo! Ri dèu do mi nahère ke, ne dèu do unu Deo.<bt>Yesus saw it like that, and He got angry at His disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Allow those children come to Me! Don't prevent them! Cuz people like them here, are God's people.</bt><v n="15" />Henge ri muu pe woie! Naduu do ta dèka nga Deo, paraluu ne lua d'èi noo nga Deo, mi d'èi naiki na hee nga ina-ama noo. Ki ad'o mi nahère, j'èma d'o roo ta jad'èi dèu do unu Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl must remember well! Whoever wants to come to God, s/he must desire God like these children desire their mother-father. If not like that, they are not appropriate to become God's people.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 18:3</note><v n="16" />Ta èla Yesus pe lii mi nahère, ta ked'aka ke ri Noo ne naiki he, j'e tèka ruai, mengao ne mèngi tuu roo hedèu-hedèu.<bt>After that, Yesus cuddled/embraced those children, and placed hands, uttering blessing one by one.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leru ade = gelisah (kurang dipakai);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">leru ade = gelisah (kurang dipakai); 16: ked'aka = peluk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Do kaja kale ruj'ara ta muri mada loro nga Deo<bt>A rich person looks for a way to live continually with God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 19:16-30; Luka 18:18-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ta d'ai Yesus he d'èi ta pekèd'èiti ène, dèka ke he dèu do kaja nga perai la pehapo nga Yesus. Ta lèku rutuu ke noo pa hed'apa Yesus, j'e keb'ali, &lt;&lt;Ama Guru do woie. Ne ta keb'ali ko yaa hudi. Mi nahee, Ama. Nengaa ke ne do ta tao ri yaa, mij'e toi tèra ri yaa, ta do maho yaa la liru-bèla ta muri mada hela'u nga Deo?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (collective) wanted to leave, then a rich person came running to meet with Yesus. He knelt before Yesus, then he asked, &lt;&lt;Honoured Teacher! I want to ask a little. Like this, Father. What must I do in order that I really know, I can enter heaven to live together with God?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaja = kaya ; gaa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kaja = kaya ; gaa = pantas</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ta b'ale ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa èu ku lii pa Yaa, ta &lt;do woie&gt;!? B'ule d'o he dèu he do woie, tituwata Deo we.<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Why do you-s say to Me, &lt;honoured&gt;!? There is no one who is honoured, except only God.</bt><v n="19" />Toi ma ri èu ne lii pereda Deo, rai uru:<bt>You already know God's commands from before:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;B'ole pemade dèu;<bt>&lt;Don't kill people;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèb'u = tikam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèb'u = tikam</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">B'ole kenyoo;<bt>Don't commit adultery;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">B'ole mana'o;<bt>Don't steal;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="loi = steal bit-by-bit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">loi = steal bit-by-bit</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">B'ole jad'èi hakahii pote;<bt>Don't become a lying witness;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hakahii = saksi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hakahii = saksi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">B'ole èba unu dèu nga ruj'ara pepote;<bt>Don't take other people's belongings by deciet;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peluu = tipu ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peluu = tipu ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Pekeb'ue ina-ama èu!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Honour your-sg mother-father!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 20:12-16, Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 5:16-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ta b'ale ke ri dèu na ène, &lt;&lt;Do petuu, Ama Guru, ee! Rai nga ngèru, harièle na hère, èla ke ri yaa petao.&gt;&gt;<bt>That person responded, &lt;&lt;True, Teacher, ee! Starting from youth, I have followed all those (commands).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ngèru = muda, (teen, belum berkeluarga)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ngèru = muda, (teen, belum berkeluarga)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Bui ne ade Yesus nga dèu na ène. Ta lii ke Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Petuu! Tapulara ne ko he èhi lai. Awe na d'ee, b'ale we èu la pewie pe'èla ne puhaka èu. Ne doi he, la peb'agi pa do kehia. J'e mai èu ma pedute Yaa. Do ta wie pa èu ri Deo, ne puhaka do wala pa liru-bèla.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus loved/pitied (lit. liver fell on) that person, then He said, &lt;&lt;True! But there is still one more thing. Now you must go.home to sell make finished (completely sell off) all your wealth/inheritance. Its money, you go divide out to the poor people. Then you come to follow Me. Later God will give you other wealth/inheritance in heaven (doublet).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teruj'a = unaware, kekurangan yg dibuat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">teruj'a = unaware, kekurangan yg dibuat tanpa sadar ; kura = kurang ; puhaka = pusaka (tanah, rumah, hewan, kebun ; dèu do hedui = orang susah ; do kehia = orang miskin ; do ta = akan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ta rènge ri noo ne lii pedai Yesus, mèje ne ade noo. B'ale noo nga hedui pengee, ri do kaja tèra noo.<bt>When he heard what Yesus said, his liver was burned (idiom). Then he went home with his thoughts in strife, because he was truly rich.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèje ne ade noo = Idiom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèje ne ade noo = Idiom ; melara = terbakar, perih</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ta heleo peheru ke Yesus, j'e pedai lii nga ana aj'a Noo he, &lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu! D'ai hedui do kaja ta maho la d'ara liru-bèla.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus looked around, and spoke to His disciples, &lt;&lt;Listen up! It is very difficult for rich people to enter heaven.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00038C.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;textWrapping:none">B'ada unta<bt>Unta (camel) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta rènge ne lii pedai Noo, ta hengodo ke ne ana aj'a. Ta petabe rike ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;D'èno pe'ie! D'ei ta jad'èi dèu do unu Deo, rihi hedui! B'ole pengee ta do memud'e.<bt>Hearing Him talk like that, the disciples were confused. Then Yesus added more, &lt;&lt;Listen well! Wanting to become a person of God's, is very extremely difficult! Don't think its easy.</bt><v n="25" />Tuu do kaja maho la liru-bèla ta jad'èi dèu unu Deo, hela'u hedui nga b'ada unta do mone ae, maho la d'ara bèdo j'ara ro'a wui-wohe j'ej'au.&gt;&gt;<bt>For a rich person to enter heaven becoming God's person, that is the same difficulty as a large camel animal entering into its enclosure through a sewing-needle hole.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bèdo = kandang ; wui-wohe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">bèdo = kandang ; wui-wohe = pangkal (jarum) ; j'ej'au = jarum (Seba) &lt; aj'u j'au (kuno) ; (Dimu) ~ j'ej'au ~ j'ij'ao</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rihi memud'e hengi'u keb'ao maho la"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Rihi memud'e hengi'u keb'ao maho la d'oka b'èdo j'ara toka do mi bèla ro'a wui wohe j'ij'ao, ngati he dèu do kaja ta muri mada pa d'ara lua do d'èi Deo.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ri lii pedai Yesus, buwu b'ingu roo. Ta pekeb'ali rike roo, &lt;&lt;Ki do petuu ke mi nahère, naduu ke ne do ta nara helama?&gt;&gt;<bt>That talk of Yesus' made them all even more confused. Then they asked, &lt;&lt;If that's indeed true like that, who can get *salvation?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buwu = tambah ; helama ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">buwu = tambah ; helama = selamat (from danger, ill health, spiritual)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ta heleo ke roo hedèu-hedèu ri Yesus, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Tu dèu rai-wawa, era lai dod'o jad'èi Tapulara tu Deo, hari-hari lai do jad'èi we!&gt;&gt;<bt>Looking at each one of them, then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;For humans, indeed it's not possible. But for God, absolutely everything can happen/come to be.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ketèri = 1) memperhatikan, lihat secara"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ketèri = 1) memperhatikan, lihat secara tajam; 2) memfitnah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta lii ke Petu, &lt;&lt;Ama. Èla ke pehani ri j'ii, harièle ne oha-unu j'ii, tuu ta ma ped'ute Ama. Nengaa ke ne nara j'ii?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Petu spoke, &lt;&lt;Father. We-ex have already left all our possesions, in.order.to follow Father. What do we get?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29-30" />Ane Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ne lii Yaa pa muu mi nahee: Naduu do pedute Yaa, nga ruj'ara hani ina-ama noo, 'a'a-ari noo, ana-ana noo, lau-d'oka noo, lua j'èga noo, nga harièle ihi èmu-kemali, tuu ta la pika pa dèu pa mii-pa mii j'ara Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Deo, do ta hème wari ri noo hengahu wari lipa. Harièle nengaa do èla pehani ri noo, do ta hème wari nga do rihi. Do ta nara lema noo, hedui-herui taga pedute Yaa. Tapulara, pa awe pedèka rahi rai-wawa d'ee, do ta muri mada noo peloro-loro hela'u nga Deo. Na ène ke ne pala noo!<bt>Yesus said, &lt;&lt;I want to tell you-pl like this: Whoever follows Me, and leaves behind his mother-father, his elder-younger.sibling, his children, his fields (doublet), his work, and all his household (=contents &amp; people), in.order.to tell people everywhere about God's Good News, later he will receive in reciprocation up to 100 times. Everything that he has left behind, he will later receive back in abundance. And he will also be afflicted with torture/suffering (doublet) because he follows Me. But later when it's the end of the world, he will live continually together with God. That's his portion/reward!</bt><v n="31" />Henge ri muu! Pedutu nga pengee Deo, naduu do ped'èia èni, do ta jad'èi noo ta rihi naiki. Tapulara naduu do pewawa èni, pedutu nga pengee Deo, do ta jad'èi noo ta dèu do nga keb'ue.<bt>Remember! According to God's thinking, whoever tries to make himself high (status), later he will be the smallest/insignificant person. But whoever considers himself low, according to God's thinking, he will later be a big/valued person.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tuwuèhu = saudara kandung ; rahi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tuwuèhu = saudara kandung ; rahi = era pee (berakhirnya tempat) ; pala = bagian; 31: pewawe = rendahkan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dèu do èla pe hani ina"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Dèu do èla pe hani ina nga ama, tuwuèhu do momone nga tuwuèhu do mobèni, ana pa dara èmu noo, lau-d'oka nga j'èga b'uju noo, nga ihi d'ara èmu kemali noo j'e la pelebe ne lii pedai Deo, do ta hème ri noo hine hengahu wari lipa. Harièle ne do èla pe hani ri noo, do ta hèmi wari ri noo keb'ali nga rihi riko. Lema, noo do ta lake hedui-herui taga ti pedute Yaa. Tapulara pa d'ara awe do ta dae, do ta hème ri noo ne muri mada do peloro hela'u nga Deo.; 31: noo ri Deo (?). Lema naduu do uru, do taperiho ta do leto. Naduu do leto, do ta periho ta do uru (?)&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 20:16, Luka 13:30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus ped'èie j'ara lua made Noo ketèlu wari<bt>Yesus tells about His death the third time</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 20:17-19; Luka 18:31-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Hewari, ta kako ke Yesus he la Yerusalem. Yesus ne do leko j'ara. J'e lere ri ana aj'a Noo nga dèu do hewala he. Henge ri roo ne lii pedai Yesus ta do era dèu ta pemade Noo pa Yerusalem. Ri mi nahère ke, meg'ig'i ne lai pengee roo meda'u ri lai na ène. Ta rèngi ke ri Yesus ne lii pedai ana aj'a Noo he, ta pedoa wala ke roo, j'e la pika ri ne lai do wala do ta tao ri dèu pa Noo pa Yerusalem.<bt>One/At that time, Yesus (coll-pl) was traveling to Yerusalem. Yesus was walking at the front. His disciples and other people were following Him. They were remembering what He said before, that people would kill Him in Yerusalem. Because of that, they became confused, and afraid. Hearing that, then Yesus called his disciples by themselves, to tell again what other/foreign people would do to Him in Yerusalem.</bt><v n="33" />Lii ri Noo, &lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu! He ke dii ta la Yerusalem. Yaa na d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu. Tapulara d'ai nii, do ta pewie Yaa pa mone ketèu pa kètu agama he, nga guru agama he. Ta hèpo ke ri roo, ta pemade Yaa. J'e j'ole ri roo Yaa pa dèu do hewala do d'o tade Deo.<bt>He said, &lt;&lt;You-pl listen! We-inc now are going to Yerusalem. I here, am True/Prototype Human. But arriving there, (people) will *betray (sell) me, give to the heads of priests and the religious teachers. Then they will give me a death sentence. Then they will hand Me over to other/foreign people who don't know God.</bt><v n="34" />J'e pedai roo mij'e ta mekae d'ara Yaa pa hed'apa dèu lowe. Hebue Yaa ri ilu roo. Wuhe d'abe-d'abe, tade mae èle ne ihi Yaa. Itu pemade Yaa ri roo. Made tèra Yaa, tapulara nèli do ta muri wari Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they will speak shaming Me in front of many people. They will throw spit at Me. They will swing.a.whip repeatedly, destroying my body. Then they will kill Me. I will really die. But the day.after.the.following.day, I will live again.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Afta three days&quot; is not the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">"Afta three days" is not the same as "Day numba three." In Jewish counting, today is the day 1, tomorrow is day 2, day after is day 3. "Afta three days" could be day 4. CHECK.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leko j'ara = memandu jalan ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">leko j'ara = memandu jalan ; reja = gelisah, resah ; meg'ig'i-meda'u = enggang ; meg'ig'i = kuatir, was-was ; pengero = pikiran; 33: 1) priest = kètu agama ; 2) chief priests = kètu ngati kètu agama he ; 3) high priest = Kètu Mone Ae agama; 34: mare d'ole-d'ole = ketawa, olok-olok ; wuhe = pukul ; d'abe-d'abe = ulang-ulang ; mae = ancor (luka-luka) ; itu = baru (cnj) ; Ursula based in Batu, came and went to Sabu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">J'ako nga Johani ami ta jad'èi dokepai<bt>J'ako and Johani request to become important people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 20:20-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Èla pa na ène, dèka ke nga Yesus, J'ako nga Johani, ana Sabadeu. Ami roo, &lt;&lt;Ama Guru! Ne nga paraluu ko j'ii.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then, J'ako and Johani, Sabadeu's children, came to Yesus. They requested, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! We have a need [to talk with you.]&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Paraluu nengaa muu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked, &lt;&lt;You-pl need what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />B'ale ri roo, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee. Mi nahee. Ki d'ai Ama ne mejèd'èita pèru pereda, ne ami j'ii, pejèd'èiwe j'ii he dèu pa ked'anga, nga he dèu pa keriu Ama, ta pereda hela'u nga Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, &lt;&lt;Father,ee. It's like this. Later, if/when Father is sitting holding rule/governing, we-ex request Father to seat us, one on Father's right side, one on the left side, so we also rule together with Father.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pejèd'i = seat us (vt) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pejèd'i = seat us (vt) ; keg'ana = kanan ; ai keg'ana = tangan kanan (= wakil) ; keriu = kiri ; ai keriu = tangan kiri (orang ketiga)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Tada d'o muu d'ue nengaa ne do ami muu. Yaa ne hine, do ta nara hedui do rihi ae. Ku mi namii? Ne pengee ri muu, mèka muu ta hape ne hedui hela'u nga Yaa tade made?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;You-pl two here don't understand what you are asking. I here, later will get an increase (in number)edible amount of suffering. So, how is it? You think you also are able to shoulder.carry that suffering together with Me until death?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 12:50</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />B'ale ri roo, &lt;&lt;Mèka, Ama, ee!&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered, &lt;&lt;We can, Father, ee!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta lii rike Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;Tèra. Hine do ta hape lema ri muu ne lua hedui mi do hape ri Yaa.<bt>Yesus spoke again to them, &lt;&lt;True. You also later will shoulder.carry that suffering like Me carry.</bt><v n="40" />Tapulara naduu do ta mejèd'èipa ked'anga nga pa keriu Yaa, ad'o lai petèka Yaa. Na ène lai hèpo Deo. Do èla pehèpo ke ri Noo ta naduu do mejèd'èipa era na ène.&gt;&gt;<bt>But who later sits on My right and left, that is not Me who decides. That is God who has the right (to decide). He has already decided, who it is that sits in those places.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kerij'i = gemetar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kerij'i = gemetar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ta rèngi ri ana aj'a do wala he ne lii ami J'ako nga Johani, ta bubu d'ara ke roo.<bt>When the other disciples heard J'ako and Johani's request, they were extremely mad.</bt><v n="42" />Ta pedoa ke harièle roo ri Yesus, j'e pedai nga roo, &lt;&lt;Mi nahee! Toi ri muu. Do pereda do tima ta j'èli kerupu dèu rai tade dod'o i'a kemuki. Nga kètu rai dèu dod'o tade Deo, e'e ne d'èi roo we ne tao pehedui ana rai, tade dod'o nara roo ta pekèd'èikètu.<bt>Then Yesus called them all, and He said to them, &lt;&lt;It's like this! You need to understand. The people who govern normally and repeatedly press.down/step on their people, to-point-that they can't move. And heads from nations that don't know God, like to give make things difficult to-point-that their citizens are not able to lift their heads.</bt><v n="43" />Muu he b'ole j'èga mi nahère! Naduu ti telora muu do d'èi ta pemone ae èni, paraluu noo ta jad'èi mi jongo do pemoko dèu do hewala.<bt>But you-pl are not to do like that! Whoever from you who wants to be a prominent person, he must become the same as the lowest.servant in.order.to serve other people.</bt><note reference="10:42-43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 22:25-26</note><v n="44" />Nga naduu do d'èi ta jad'èi kètu, paraluu noo ta jad'èi mi do ènu.<bt>And whoever wants to become a head, he must make himself like a slave.</bt><note reference="10:43-44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 23:11, Ma'u 9:35, Luka 22:26</note><v n="45" />Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu. Ne dèka Yaa, ad'o mij'e ta ma pemoke Yaa ri dèu. Tapulara ne dèka Yaa, ta ma pemoko dèu lowe. Ne dèka Yaa, ta ma wie bolo-bolo ne muri mada Yaa ta ma pehèu dèu lowe ngati hala-ludu roo.&gt;&gt;<bt>I am the True/Prototype Human. My coming was not so people would serve me. But My coming was to serve many people. I came to give my whole-complete life in.order.to *redeem many people from their sins (doublet).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'èli = injak ; kerupu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'èli = injak ; kerupu = ulang-ulang ; dèu rai = ana rai = masyarakat, rakyat ; kemuki = bergerak ; e'e = sesuka; 43: b'uri = potong, belah ; pemolaga èni = (kiasan) membesarkan diri ; jongo = jongos, semua kerja dalam rumahtangga ; pelako = melayani (Dimu) not widely used , prefer pemoko; 45: bolo-bolo = bulat-bulat (anteru) ; pehèu = tebus</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pa dèu do herua-do pemane lai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pa dèu do herua-do pemane lai wèlu do lowe.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pe'ie do b'èdu<bt>Yesus heals a blind person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 20:29-34; Luka 18:35-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he nga dèu lowe he d'ai la kota Yeriko. Ta d'ai roo ne mèhu èni ti nii, era ke he dèu do b'èdu do mejèd'èipa ngidi ruj'ara, nga henata ai ta ami nengaa pa dèu do lake. Ne ngara noo Bartimeo, ana ri Timeo.<bt>Yesus and His *disciples, and many people arrived at Yeriko city. When they wanted to continue on, there was a blind man who sat begging at the side of the road from people who passed. His name Bartimeo, child of Timeo.</bt><v n="47" />Ta rènge ri noo, ta Yesus do Nasare do lake j'ara ène, ta pekaa ke noo pemèdu-mèdu, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Kolo-loro Dau ee! Tui ke Èu ne mate ri j'ii do Jahudi! Ruba kowe ne d'ara nga yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard that that the one who passed by, was Yesus from Nasare, then he yelled loudly (and repeatedly), &lt;&lt;Yesus! Dau's descendant, ee! We-ex Jahudi people have been waiting a long time for You! Love/Pity me!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nga henata ai = sorong tangan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nga henata ai = sorong tangan minta; 47: ana = limited to one generation ; Kolo-loro = turunan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Ta rènge ne lii pekaa noo, ta b'ani ke ne dèu he, &lt;&lt;He! B'ole toli!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing him yell like that, then people scolded him, &lt;&lt;He! Be quiet!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toli = ribut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">toli = ribut</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tapulara, juu mèdu ne lii pekaa noo, &lt;&lt;Wo Yesus! Kolo-loro Dau ee! Ruba kowe ne d'ara nga yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But he yelled even more loudly, &lt;&lt;Wo Yesus! Dau's descendant, ee! Love/Pity me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ta titu ke Yesus. j'e lii Noo, &lt;&lt;Èbe ko noo ma d'ee ri muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus stopped (lit. stood), and He said, &lt;&lt;You-pl bring him here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta kako ke roo nga noo, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Pehèngo èni we! Pedoe èu ri Ama Guru. Mai we!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they went to him, and said, &lt;&lt;You-sg be quiet! Father Teacher is calling you. Come on!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Ta rèngi mi nahère, ta hore ke ne hij'i noo, j'e kèd'èimèri ai la pehapo nga Yesus.<bt>Hearing that, he jumped throwing.off his blanket(man's sarong/outer garmet), and he stood up real fast to go meet Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hore = lempar ; hij'i ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hore = lempar ; hij'i = selimut</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Keb'ali ke Yesus pa noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ami nengaa èu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked him, saying, &lt;&lt;You want what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta b'ale ke ri noo, &lt;&lt;Muri, ee! Ami ta ngèdi ne namada yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>He answered, &lt;&lt;Sir/Lord/Master! I request so.that I can see.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Muri = tuan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Muri = tuan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Ta lii rike Yesus pa noo, &lt;&lt;Ri parahaj'a èu, ta do i'a Yaa pe'ie èu, ie tèra ke èu! B'ale we.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus said again to him, &lt;&lt;Because you-sg believe that I can heal you, now then you're already well! Go on (home) now (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pelai roo lua mèno èu ta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Pelai roo lua mèno èu ta do nara Yaa ta pe'ie èu, pa d'ara awe nane ie ke ne namada èu!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta ngèdi d'ènge ke, ne namada noo. Pedutu le noo la pengèdo Yesus.<bt>And his eyes straight away were indeed good. After that, he went following to escort Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pengèdo = antar (pulang)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pengèdo = antar (pulang)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus maho la Yerusalem, lere ri dèu lowe nga hod'a-kej'eka mi lere he dèu duae<bt>Yesus enters Yerusalem, accompanied by many people praising Him, like greeting a king</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:1-11; Luka 19:28-40; Johani 12:12-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Ta umu roo nga kota Yerusalem, ta d'ai ke roo la rae Betfage nga Betania, pa keraha b'ojo Saitun.<bt>When they were already close to Yerusalem city, they arrived at (two-CHECK) villages Betfage and Betania, on the slope of hill Saitun.</bt><note reference="11:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne pehune ne ngara noo ta b'ojo &lt;Saitun&gt;, ri pa ène do era d'ai ae ne d'oka saitun. Lema era ngapi wo saitun mita nara èi mènyi. Ne j'èu b'ojo Saitun ngati Yerusalem, era ma hekilo he.<bt>They gave the name &lt;Saitun&gt; to that hill, because (tagal) in that place there are many saitun groves. There is also a place to press its oil from that tree's fruit. That Saitun hill is approximately one kilo from Yerusalem city.</bt></note>Ta pengaha ke Yesus he, he melila pa ène. Ta pejuu uru ke ri Yesus do d'ue ne ana aj'a Noo.<bt>Yesus (collective) waited there awhile. Then Yesus sent two of His disciples to go ahead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hod'a-kej'eka = sorak-sorai ; he melila"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hod'a-kej'eka = sorak-sorai ; he melila = sebentar ; pedihi = ditampung ; wo = buah ; ngapi = squeeze (with instrument) ;</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Nga lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Kako uru ko muu la rae na nii. D'ai muu ne maho la d'ara rae nee, do tangède ri muu he ngi'u ana keledei do èke. Ad'o dae do ngèdi ta menya'e ri dèu. Ma'e ri muu j'e pera'o ma d'ee.<bt>He spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go on ahead to that village over yonder. As you entering into the village, you will see a keledai animal's offspring, is tied there. People have not yet ever tried to ride (mount) it. You go open (undo) his rope and.so pull bring him here.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pera'o = hela"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pera'o = hela</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Kiri era dèu do keb'ali pa muu, &lt;Pera'o ta ngaa ri muu ana keledei nee?&gt; Pika ri muu, &lt;Ta paraluu Muri dii. Kiri moko ne pake, ta peb'ale d'ènge ma.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>If someone asks you, &lt;Why are you undoing that keledai?&gt; you tell them, &lt;Our-inc Lord/Master needs it. If/When finished using, then He will send [him] back straightaway.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&lt;Ta ngaa hèku pera'o ri muu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">&lt;Ta ngaa hèku pera'o ri muu ne keledei ne?&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'ènge = memang (2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">d'ènge = memang (2)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00033C.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.5cm;textWrapping:none">B'ada keledei<bt>Keledei (donkey) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta pekèd'èike roo d'ue la nii. Era tèra ke, ne ana keledei ne do èke pa hed'apa èmu pa ngidi ruj'ara. Ta ma'e ri roo, j'e pera'o.<bt>Then those two people went yonder. There really was a keledai's offspring tied.up in front of a house on the side of the road. Then they untied and.so brought him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="najawi = binatang umur satu tahun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">najawi = binatang umur satu tahun untuk hewan besar (kuda, kerbau, sapi)</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ta keb'ali ke ne dèu do titu pa ène, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa! Ku pera'o ri muu ne ana keledei ne?&gt;&gt;<bt>But people who stood there said, &lt;&lt;Why! You-pl are freeing that keledei?&gt;&gt; (Idiomatic demand).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ta b'ale ke ri roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ta paraluu Muri dii. Kiri moko ne pake, do ta peb'ale d'ènge ma ri j'ii ma d'ee.&gt;&gt; Ta hani ke ri dèu he, ta pera'o ri roo ne ana keledei nee.<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;Our-inc Lord/Master needs it. When finished using, we-ex will make sure it gets back.&gt;&gt; Then that person allowed them to pull take away that keledei offspring.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="golo = lepas, tidak ada keberatan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">golo = lepas, tidak ada keberatan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Moko ne dèu na hère ta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Moko ne dèu na hère ta pedutu ne lua d'ai ana aj'a he, j'e golo roo nga pera'o ne keledei nee.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ta pera'o ke ri roo la wie pa Yesus. Ta wèle ke ri roo ri hij'i pa dèni ana keledei nee, j'e j'ole pa Yesus ta menya'e.<bt>They led it to give to Yesus. Then they put their blankets (male sarong) on top of that keledei offspring, then Yesus got.up (mounted the keledei).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rai dèni (Dimu) ~ rudèni (Seba)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rai dèni (Dimu) ~ rudèni (Seba) = punggung (but in Dimu rudèni is pubic hair)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00315C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan Yesus maho la d'ara kota Yerusalem<bt>Lord Yesus enters into the city of Yerusalem</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ta d'ai roo ta umu d'ara kota, hèga ne dèu he la wèla ne b'ara pake roo pa d'ara ruj'ara. Era lema had'e do la para ruaj'u do mii runyiu he<bt>As they were about to enter the city, there were many people who spread their clothes on the road. There were also some who went cutting leaves similar to coconut leaves</bt><note reference="11:8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne do b'uke ri Markus &lt;kelai aj'u&gt;. Tapulara pedutu nga do b'uke pa Johani 12:13, rèu palèm do mii runyiu.<bt>Markus' original writing said &lt;branches&gt;. But we know from Johani 12:13, that it was palam leaves, like coconut leaves.</bt></note>pa ngidi ruj'ara, j'e la wèla pa ruj'ara, do ta lake ri Yesus. Ne tao roo mi nahère, he èhi pekeb'ue Yesus ta mihe dèu duae.<bt>from the side of the road in.order.that they could spread them in the road to make a way for Yesus. They did that, as a way to show honour/respect to Yesus like they greet/welcome a king.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèga = orang berkerumun ; wèla"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hèga = orang berkerumun ; wèla = buka (tikar, kain) [jamak] ~ wèle [tunggal] ; ruaj'u = leaves ; runyiu = coconut palm leaves ; para = potong ; kelai = cabang, ranting</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Era had'e do pe'uru èni nga Yesus, era had'e do lere Yesus. Ta hod'a-kej'eka ke roo, mihe ane,<bt>Then some people went to walk in front of Yesus and some followed behind Yesus. They begin shouting.happily saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hod'a-kej'eka = sorak-sorai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hod'a-kej'eka = sorak-sorai</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Hosana!</span> Pekelode ne ngara Deo!<bt>&lt;&lt;|iHosana!|r Praise the name/reputation of God!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara lii Aram, <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;</span>. Ne pedèb'o nee, &lt;wie ri noo ne helama&gt;. Do tima ri roo ne pake ta wue-waje Deo.<bt>In their Aram language they said &lt;|iHosana|r&gt;. Its meaning is &lt;he gives salvation/he saves&gt;. They usually used that word to praise2 God.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ta wie ri Deo ne mèngi pa dèu do dèka nga ngara Deo,<bt>God gives blessing to the person who comes using God's name/reputation,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ri Noo ke do pejue ri Deo.<bt>because God has sent/commissioned Him!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Pekelode ne ngara Deo!<bt>|iHosana!|r Praise the name/reputation of God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ri Deo miha do tama pekèd'e wari kuaha pereda duae Dau!<bt>Because God is going to rebuild king Dau's governing.authority!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Pekelode ne ngara Deo!<bt>|iHosana!|r Praise the name/reputation of God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ri Deo ke do mejèd'èita pereda ti liru-bèla do ketutu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because God is the one who sits governing, in the highest sky/heaven (doublet)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ketutu = puncak tertinggi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ketutu = puncak tertinggi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ta d'ai Yesus he la d'ara kota, ta maho ke roo la keb'èla rae Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Pereha ri Noo hari hewue ne d'ara keb'èla rae Èmu Heb'aj'a nee. Tapulara ri umu ke ta jèna lod'o, nara d'o ke roo tatao nengaa wari pa ène, ta b'ale ke roo la rae Betania.<bt>Arriving in the city, then Yesus (collective) entered into the *Temple (God's Main Worship House)'s yard. Then Yesus examined all.around that Temple (short form) complex. But because it was late afternoon/near sundown, there was no more time to do anything, they returned to Betania village.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00250C.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Keb'èla rae Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo<bt>God's *Temple and its yard</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pereda ri Yesus pa he kepue aj'u lii ta b'ole wue wari<bt>Yesus commands a tree so-that it can no longer have fruit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta j'èmi ae do b'èli rai nee, ta pekèd'èike roo ti Betania b'ale la kota Yerusalem. Pa telora ruj'ara, ta menganga ke Yesus.<bt>Very early the next morning, they left Betania to return to Yerusalem city. In the middle of the road/journey, Yesus felt hungry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lii ta = supaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lii ta = supaya</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ta ngède ke ri Noo he kepue aj'u pa ngidi ruj'ara. Do tima tanga'e ri dèu ne wue noo.<bt>He saw a tree on the side of the road. People usually eat its fruit.</bt><note reference="11:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara lii J'awa, mihe ane, &lt;pohon ara&gt;. Tapulara pa d'ara lii rai Yunani, <span class="Italic">sukei</span>. Pa d'ara Buku Deo, do peke mii aj'u do tima ta nga'e ne wue noo. Pa Indonesia bira dimu, ne wue &lt;pohon ara&gt; ène, ad'o do nga'e ri dèu. Tapulara, pi'ad'o aj'u pa rai dii do hela'u nga aj'u <span class="Italic">sukei</span> pa Isra'el, mii do ped'èie pa Alkitab.<bt>Bahasa Indonesia (lit. J'awa) uses the word &lt;pohon ara&gt;. But in the Yunani language it is <span class="Italic">sukei.</span> In God's Book it designates a tree from which people usually eat its fruit. In Indonesia's eastern side, people do not eat &lt;ara tree's&gt; fruit. But there is no tree on our land/island which is the same at the &lt;ara tree&gt; in Isra'el as spoken about in the Bible. [CHECK]</bt></note>Ta kako ke Yesus la pe'umu-èni, la heleo ngee ta do era nga wue. Ta d'ai Noo la kepue aj'u nee, heleo ri Noo b'ule d'o nga wue, rèu ne we do bibu. Pa d'ara awe do na ène, ad'o tèra ma do awe wue.<bt>So Yesus approached that tree to see perhaps if there was fruit (or not). But when he got to that tree, He didn't see any fruit, It had only just started to have leaves. It wasn't really its fruit season yet.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'umu-èni - deka-deka ; bibu -"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'umu-èni - deka-deka ; bibu - rimbun ; pi'ad'o = tidak ada</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do mengèru (do d'ai bibu ne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">do mengèru (do d'ai bibu ne rau ne).</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa aj'u na ène, &lt;&lt;Pelai ti dod'o b'ule èu nga wue tu Yaa, j'ari ngati awe na d'ee, b'ole era wari èu nga wue ta wie pa dèu do hewala!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to that tree saying, &lt;&lt;Because you don't give your fruit to Me, starting from now, you will not be able to give your fruit to other people anymore!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Rèngi lema ri ana aj'a Noo ne hekoto lii pedai Yesus pa aj'u nee.<bt>His disciples heard Yesus talk severely/upset to the tree like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hekoto = kaku ; kecewa ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hekoto = kaku ; kecewa ; keras</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus maho la d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. B'agi pemenyèla ri Noo ne era pewie pa nii<bt>Yesus enters the *Temple. Then he tears.apart throw.away the selling place there</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:12-17; Luka 19:45-48; Johani 2:13-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ta èla pe mi nahère ta nèru ke roo teruu la Yerusalem. Maho ke Yesus la d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Pa keb'èla rae Èmu Heb'aj'a na ène, do tao mi paha he ri dèu ta pewie koro j'awa, ta b'ara j'ola wie Deo. Ta ngèdi ri Noo mi nahère ta hud'èila tele ke ri Noo. Nyèka ri Noo pekeb'èla ne meja-meja pehuru doi, lema b'agu-b'agu ihi d'aga koro j'awa he.<bt>Then they continued walking, arriving at Yerusalem. Then Yesus went again into the *Temple (full form). In that Temple's (short form) yard, people had made it as a market in.order.for them to sell doves that people used for *offerings to God. Seeing that then, He went to evict them outside. He threw.down making the tables thrown.about which they used to exchange money, and threw.down making upside.down the benches which they used to sell those doves.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pekeb'èla = melentang ; pehuru ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pekeb'èla = melentang ; pehuru = tukar ; ihi d'aga = saudagar ; b'ara j'ola = persembahan</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Lara ri Noo harièle dèu, ta b'ole lake nga èba nengaa we, j'ara d'ara rae Èmu Heb'aj'a ène.<bt>He also forbade all the people in.order.that they not bring their things to take a short-cut through that Temple yard any more.</bt><v n="17" />Aj'a ri Noo dèu, ane Noo, &lt;&lt;Do toi ke ri muu, nengaa ne do hure do b'uke, mihe ane, &lt;Ne pe'era ri Yaa ne Èmu na d'ee, tuu harièle kejie dèu, ta maa heb'aj'a pa d'ee.&gt; Tapulara lare ri muu ne Èmu na ène, ta era pekupu do peraba dèu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He taught them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl already know what has been written and established, saying, &lt;I build this House, so.that people from all (social) groups come worship here.&gt; But you-pl have made this House become robbers gathering/meeting place!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do peraba dèu = NP perampok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">do peraba dèu = NP perampok ; lare = robah, alihkan fungsi ; do hure do b'uke = (kata majemuk ditetapkan-ditulis)</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 56:7, Yermia 7:11</note></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01787b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ta rèngi ri mone ketèu pa kètu agama he nga guru agama he ne lii pedai j'ara lua tao Yesus do mi nahère, bubu d'ara tèra roo. Moko ke roo ta kale ruj'ara ta pemade Noo. Tapulara meg'ig'i roo, ri ae tèra ke ne dèu do d'èi nga lii aj'a Noo.<bt>When the heads of the priests and the religious teachers heard about what Yesus had done like that, they were really angry. Then they began to look for a way to kill Him. But they also were afraid/in.awe because many people liked very.much His teaching. [CHECK: do we need ftn here? priest - chief priest - high priest]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone ketèu pa kètu agama ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone ketèu pa kètu agama = KT</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ta umu ta jèna lod'o, ta pekèd'èike roo ti kota Yerusalem, la bèj'i la Betania.<bt>When the sun was beginning to sink, then they left Yerusalem city, to go sleep in Betania.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kiri ta parahaj'a tèra dii pa Deo, do ta wie ri Noo nengaa we ne do ami dii<bt>If we truly believe in God, He will give what we ask</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:20-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Ta j'èmi ae do b'èli rai ène, ta b'ale rike roo la Yerusalem. D'ai le telora ruj'ara, ta lake ke roo j'ara aj'u do mid'a nee, do pedai lii Yesus nga noo nee. Ta ngède ne aj'u na ène, ta madalae ke ne ana aj'a Noo he harièle, ri made ke hari nga amo nee, ne aj'u na ène. Ta henge ke ri Petu ne lii pedai Yesus pa aj'u na ène. Ta lii ke noo, &lt;&lt;Ama! Heleo ko ri Ama ne aj'u do mid'a nee, do wole ri Ama nee, made ke!&gt;&gt;<bt>Very early the next morning, they returned again to Yerusalem. In the middle of the road/journey, they passed.by that tree which yesterday Yesus spoke to it. His disciples were amazed, because they saw that tree was already dead dry all the way down to its roots. Then Petu remembered that Yesus had spoken to the tree yesterday. Then he told said, &lt;&lt;Father! Please look at that tree which yesterday Father punished/cursed there, it's dead!&gt;&gt; [Note: dried up is explicit to implicit]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mid'a = kemarin ; wole ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mid'a = kemarin ; wole = hukum</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Do tèra! Had'èita parahaj'a lema muu pa Deo mi nahère.<bt>Then Yesus responded, &lt;&lt;True! If only you-pl would also believe in God like that.</bt><v n="23" />Kiri parahaj'a tèra muu, nara lema muu ta lii pa hewue lede, ta b'ita èni j'e lari èni la d'ara dahi ae. Do ta lare ma ri Deo ne lede na ène, ki parahaj'a muu nga petuu. Parahaj'a we muu nga ketèra pa Deo.<bt>If you-pl truly believe, you can order a mountain to be picked up and cast into the ocean. And God will move that mountain, as long as you truly believe! You must truly believe in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ita = tercabut ; wèru (èni)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ita = tercabut ; wèru (èni) = (Dimu) tabuang ; (Seba) 1) putar 2) lepaskan ; ketèra = yakin</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 17:20, 1 Korintu 13:2</note><v n="24" />Naa, b'ole bèlu, oo! Had'èita parahaj'a tèra muu ta Deo do nara ta wie nengaa we ne do ami muu, do ta wie tèra ma ri Deo pa muu!<bt>Naa, don't forget, oo! As long as you truly believe that God is capable to give what you ask, certainly He will give it to you!</bt><v n="25" />Tapulara ki heb'aj'a muu, j'e era nga pengee do apa nga dèu do wala, la pe'ie uru ko nga dèu na ène. Mi nahère lema Ama muu pa liru-bèla do ta lonye-pemèu uru lema ne hala muu.<bt>But if you-pl are praying/worshipping, and you are thinking bad things toward another person, you must get.in.a.good.relationship with that person first. Like that, only.then your-pl Father in heaven (doublet) be prepared to *forgive1 (wipe away) your wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pemoke = merawat ; menjaga ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pemoke = merawat ; menjaga ; bereskan ; siapkan ;</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />[Kiri era do petèka pengee do apa, nga d'o wae ta pehuba hala dèu do wala, tatu Ama muu pa liru-bèla bèlu le d'o maa ne hala-ludu muu.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[If there are those store up evil thoughts, and don't want to forgive2 the wrongs of other people, surely your Father in heaven also won't want to forget your wrongs (doublet).&gt;&gt;]</bt><note reference="11:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii rai Yunani do rai uru he, ad'o do b'uke ne ayat 26 na d'ee.<bt>In the oldest Yunani Bible they don't write this verse 26.</bt></note><note reference="11:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 6:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pekeb'ali j'ara lua higa Yesus<bt>They make.an.issue.over Yesus' rights/authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:23-27; Luka 20:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ta nèru teruu ke roo. Ta d'ai le Yerusalem, ta maho ke roo la d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Ta d'ai roo la d'ara rae nee, ta dèka ke ne mone ketèu pa kètu agama he nga guru agama he.<bt>Then they continued walking. Arriving in Yerusalem, they entered again into the *Temple. When they entered the yard, the heads of the priests and the religious teachers came.</bt><v n="28" />Ta keb'ali ke roo pa Yesus, &lt;&lt;Naduu do pepue Èu ma tao kenya'u pa d'ee mid'a d'ee? Naduu ne do wie higa pa Èu?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked Yesus, &lt;&lt;Who ordered you to come make chaos here yesterday? Who gave you the right/authority?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Do toi ri Yesus ne lua pedèb'o roo ta kale ruj'ara ta pebue Noo. Ta b'ale ri Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;Ta keb'ali lema Yaa pa muu. B'ale uru ri muu ne lii keb'ali Yaa, j'e'itu wie muu ri Yaa ne lii b'ale!<bt>Yesus knew they were seeking a way to make Him fall. Then He responded to them, &lt;&lt;I also want to ask you-pl. You answer My question first, only.then will I answer you!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pebue = kasi jato"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pebue = kasi jato</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Ne lii keb'ali Yaa mi nahee: tade ri muu Johani, mone peherani dèu. Naduu do pejue noo la peherani dèu? Deo, we dèu rai-wawa?&gt;&gt;<bt>I want to ask like this: you-pl know Johani, that One.who.habitually baptized people. Who was it who ordered him to go *baptize people? God, or humans?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta pengee b'ale-b'ale ke ri roo, j'e pelii roo, &lt;&lt;Wee! Apa ke dii! Ki b'ale ri dii, &lt;ta pereda ri Deo&gt;, lii Noo nèb'o, &lt;kiri mi nahère ta ngaa muu ne d'o parahaj'a pa Johani!&gt;<bt>Then they thought.and.thought, and consulted.among.themselves, &lt;&lt;Wee! {Surprise!} We-ex have misfortune (we're caught/trapped). If we answer, &lt;God commanded (him)&gt;, then he'll respond, &lt;If so, why didn't you believe in Johani!&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abu = dapat (DH. abhu) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">abu = dapat (DH. abhu) ; nèb'o = nanti, sebentar (DH. nèbhu) ; apa = bad, evil, misfortune (celaka)</Message></Annotation><v n="32" />Jad'èid'o ke dii ta lii &lt;ta ti dèu rai-wawa&gt;. Ta kenya'u ke dèu lowe he nga dii. Ri do parahaj'a tèra ke roo, ta Johani, mone ub'a ngati Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>We also can't say, &lt;Humans told (him)&gt;. All the people will go.beserk/get.riled.up against us-inc. Because they really believe that Johani, is God's spokesperson.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone wub'a = Dimu &gt; mone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone wub'a = Dimu &gt; mone ub'a (Seba)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ta lii ke roo pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Toi do ri j'ii!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they just spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;We-ex don't know!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Moko ta lii ke Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;Kiri mi nahère, wae led'o ma Yaa ta b'ale ne lii keb'ali muu, ta naduu ne do wie higa pa Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus said to them, &lt;&lt;If so, I also won't answer your question about who it was who gave Me the right/authority.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii pehèku Yesus j'ara dèu do hab'a d'oka ago<bt>Yesus *parable about the person(s) who works a grape garden</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hab'a = usaha menanam ; mone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hab'a = usaha menanam ; mone hab'a = pekerja laki-laki (pertanian) ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 21:33-46; Luka 20:9-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Ta j'ari ke Yesus ta pedai lii nga mone ketèu pa kètu agama Jahudi he, guru agama he, nga dokepai-dokepai do Jahudi he. Ta pake ke Noo lii pehèku, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Era he dèu ta j'ari doka ago pa rai noo miha. Ta wue ke ri noo ri pudi. Ta tao ke ri noo ne b'aa ta pengèhi èi ago. Lema tatao ke ri noo ne leo do d'èia ta meniga d'oka. Èla pe mi nahère, pehab'e ri noo ne d'oka ne pa dèu do hewala, tuu ta peb'agi ihi rai nga noo. J'e pekèd'e noo la tele rai.<bt>After that, Yesus talked again with the head(s) of the Yahudi priests the religion teachers, and various Jahudi leaders. [From 11:27] He used a *parable saying, &lt;&lt;There was a person went to open a (new) grape (loan) /orchard/garden on a piece of his (own) land. Then he made a (stone)fence around it. And he made a tank to catch.liquid the grape juice. Also he built a guard hut that was high. After that, he rented out that garden to other person(s), for them to work dividing the results/yield with him. Then he left to go out of the country.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'ari = mulai ; pudi ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'ari = mulai ; pudi = pagar batu ; pedihi = kasi kumpul pelan-pelan ; pengèhi = tadah ; b'aa = bak ; meniga = jaga ; pekehewe = disewakan (but clash with share cropping) ; pej'ege = have someone work ; pehab'e = have someone manage and share crop (long term)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 5:1-2</note></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\HK-LB\LB00103C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">D'oka ago, leo meniga d'oka do d'èia, nga era pengèhi èi ago<bt>Field of anggor, high guard house, and place for collecting grape juice</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ta d'ai ne awe puu wo ago, ta pejue ke ri noo he dèu ne ènu noo la hèmi ihi rai pa dèu hab'a ago he.<bt>When the time for picking grapes arrived, then he ordered one of his slaves to go to that working person(s), to receive his share.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="puu = pick (using hands) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">puu = pick (using hands) ; ènu = membaktikan diri</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Ta d'ai ne dèka ènu do pejue ri noo, hème d'ènge ri dèu hab'a he ta kèpe, j'e merèho. Èla pe mi nahère, j'e peb'ale noo nga ai wue.<bt>When the slave he had sent arrived, those working people immediately captured him, then beat him (repeatedly). Then they returned him with empty hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="merèho = pukul berulang-ulang ; ai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">merèho = pukul berulang-ulang ; ai wue = tangan kosong ; peb'ale = kembalikan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta pejue rike ri mone oha d'oka ne he dèu ne ènu noo la hèmi ihi rai. Hème wari ri dèu hab'a he ta merèho, tade boo kètu. Lema pemekae d'ara noo, j'e hud'e-perage.<bt>Then that owner of the field sent another slave to receive the yield. Those work people also beat him until there were wounds on his head. They also shamed him, and chased him away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wège-menihe = caci maki (hak kedudukannya,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wège-menihe = caci maki (hak kedudukannya, status) ; dio-pedèd'e = caci-maki (hal moral) ; pemekae = bekin malu ; perage = usir (not just shooed, but also chased) ; tade boo kètu = lit. head leak, but normal way of saying there was blood (from small or serious wounds) ; lii ped'iri</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ta pejue rike ri mone oha d'oka ne he dèu ènu do wala. Tapulara pemade ri roo. Maji ta mi na mii le ne tao roo, ta pejue teruu ma ne ènu noo he. Tapulara ri dèu hab'a he, era do hèmi ta merèhu, era had'e do pemade.<bt>Then the owner of the field sent once again another slave. But they killed him. Even.if they did whatever (No matter what they did), he kept sending his slaves. But those work people beat some, and killed some.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèb'o = tikam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèb'o = tikam</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Hiha ana noo ke do mone miha, ana d'èi noo. Ri d'o b'ule ke ruj'ara do wala, ta pepue ke ri noo ne ana d'èi noo. Pa d'ara pengee noo, mihe ane, &lt;Kiri pepue ri yaa ne ana metana yaa, do ta hème nga woie, j'e d'èno ri roo ne lii pedai noo.&gt;<bt>The only one left was his own male child whom he loved. Because there was no other way, he just sent that beloved child of his. He thought saying, &lt;If I send my own child, surely they must recieve him well, and they will listen to/obey what he says.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ta pejue ke ne ana noo la nii. Ta ngède ri roo ne ana noo ta dèka ta pelii ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;Heleo ko ri muu! Nène ke ri ama noo do pejue ne ana noo miha! Ki made ama noo, noo ke nee do hèmi puhaka. Mai ri dii ma pemade, mij'e bui pa dii ne puhaka noo!&gt;<bt>So he sent his child there (remote). But when they saw his child coming, then they said to each other, saying, &lt;You-pl look there! His father has sent his own child. If his father dies, he here is the one who receive all that inheritance. Let's kill him, in order that his inheritance falls to us-inc!'</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nedo = yang akan (kata sandang)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nedo = yang akan (kata sandang) ?? nee do</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ta kèpe ke ri roo ne ana do na ène, j'e pemade. Èla pe mi nahère hore noo la tele d'oka ago nee. Mi nahère ke ne lii pehèku d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they grabbed the child [can be an adult--it's the relationship with the father that is in focus--I am also a child in this context], and they killed him. Then they tossed him outside the garden. That's the parable.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wèro = (Dimu) lempar buang (dengan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wèro = (Dimu) lempar buang (dengan gaya yg lebih keras) ; hore = buang, lepas (Seba) ~ nab'e (Seba)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ta keb'ali ke Yesus pa dokepai he, &lt;&lt;Pa d'ara pengee muu, nengaa ke ne do ta tao ri mone oha d'oka ne pehed'apa nga dèu hab'a he? Pedutu pengee Yaa, do b'ara tatu ke noo, ta dèka la pemade harièle dèu hab'a he. Hème ne d'oka nee, j'e pehab'e pa dèu do hewala.<bt>And then Yesus asked the important people, &lt;&lt;According to your-pl thinking, what is that owner of the field going to do to those work people? According to My thinking, it's already obvious he will come to kill all of those work people. After that, he will farm out that garden to other person/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ara tatu = barang tentu (barangkali?)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ara tatu = barang tentu (barangkali?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Do aj'e ke ri dii, ne lii pedai Deo do era do hure d'o b'uke, miha ane,<bt>We-iinc all have already read what God has said in writing, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hure = b'uke ; do hure"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hure = b'uke ; do hure d'o b'uke = (majemuk) tertulis</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Era hewue wowadu do hore ri tuka wowadu he.<bt>&lt;There is one stone that the craftsmen have thrown out.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tapulara, ne wowadu na ène, èla ke pejad'èi ita wowadu kepue gerii.<bt>But that stone has now become a base stone under a post (implied main house post).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wowadu kepue = batu yang sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wowadu kepue = batu yang sonde bergerak ; gerii = tiang ; gerii ae ; gerii tèra ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Deo miha ne do èla pe pid'e, j'e pejèd'e ne wowadu ène.<bt>God himself chose it, and set that stone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pid'e = pili ; pejèd'e ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pid'e = pili ; pejèd'e = kasi dudu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ri mi nahère ke, d'ai gaa ne heleo ri dii!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>This is why we-inc see its beauty!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="merake = indah (untuk hiasan yg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">merake = indah (untuk hiasan yg berkilauan) ;</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 118:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Toi d'ènge ma ri mone kepai-mone kepai he, ta ne lii pehèku Yesus do lèka pa roo. Roo ke ne do pehèko nga dèu hab'a ago he. Ta j'ari ke roo ta kale ruj'ara ta kèpe Noo. Tapulara meda'u roo ri dèu lowe he, do d'èi nga lii aj'a Noo. Ta pehèg'a ke roo ti ène, j'e hane Yesus.<bt>Those important people straight.away understood that Yesus had aimed/targeted at them using that parable. They were compared with those grape garden workers. And so they started to look for ways to capture/arrest Him. But they were afraid of the many people who liked His teaching. So they just dispersed and went away from Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehèko = diumpamakan &lt; pehèku (specific)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehèko = diumpamakan &lt; pehèku (specific) ; hane = kasi tinggal ; pehèg'a = bubar, pisah bae-bae</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pehero Yesus nga pake lua ma'i b'ea<bt>Trying to trap Yesus over paying tax</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'ea = balasteng (Du-archaic), pajak ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'ea = balasteng (Du-archaic), pajak ; pehero = cari akal untuk jerat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 22:15-22; Luka 20:20-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Èla pe na ène, ta pejuu ke ri mone kepai do Jahudi he, do pèri dèu, do Parisi nga ti paratei Herode, la keb'ali pa Yesus, ta kale ne hala lii pedai Noo.<bt>After that, the Jahudi leaders sent several people, Parisi people and from Herode's (political) party, to question Yesus and find a way to accuse Him.</bt><v n="14" />Ta dèka ke roo, j'e keb'ali pa Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wo Ama Guru! Toi ri j'ii ta Ama mone mola ngee, ad'o do pote-èpi. Do tère lohe ade dèu. Do pedai nga woie ri Ama, ne d'èi Deo, nga d'o heleo worèwu dèu. Nga na d'ee ta keb'ali j'ii he èhi lai. Pedutu lua petèka agama dii do Jahudi, ie ko ma ke dii ta ma'i b'ea pa Kehe, Duae Mone Ae Roma, we ad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>So they came and asked Him, saying, &lt;&lt;Wo Father Teacher! We-ex know that Father is a straight/right thinking/character, and not deceitful (doublet). Father sees into people's livers/inner character. Father speaks well/truly the will of God, and does not look at the face of people (Idiom = no bias). We want to ask one matter. According to our-inc Jahudi religious regulations, may we pay taxes to Kehe (from 'Keser"), the top-level King of Roma, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kehe = Kaisar (Roma atau Eropa)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Kehe = Kaisar (Roma atau Eropa) also sometimes Kehe Hawu (archaic) ; tère lohe = lihat tembus</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Do toi ri Yesus ne lua huni pengee roo, mij'e ta pedai Noo ta pelawa nga duae Roma. Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus nga kèri, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa ke muu ku pehero Yaa nga lii keb'ali na d'ee? Wie ko pa Yaa ri muu ne he mada doi melaa-pudi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus knew what they were thinking, wanting Him to speak against the king of Roma. He responded coarsely/harshly, &lt;&lt;Why do you-pl try and trap Me with that question? Give me a silver coin!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hegèri = kasar (like a dog)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hegèri = kasar (like a dog) ; kèri = kasar, tersinggung (less strong) ; doi melaa-pudi = silver coin, uang perak ; namada doi = mata uang ; he lamuhi doi melaa-pudi = conveys a spherical silver coin (?), not round ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\HK-LB\HK00166C.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;TextWrapping:none">Namada doi oha do pereda Roma<bt>Face on money from the Roma govt.</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ta j'ole ke ri roo he mada ne doi melaa-pudi. Ta hème ke ri Yesus, j'e pereha ne doi na ène. Ta keb'ali ke Noo pa roo, &lt;&lt;Gaba na d'ee, worèwu naduu? J'e ngara naduu na d'ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>They handed over a silver coin. Yesus accepted/received it, and examined it. Then He asked them, &lt;&lt;This picture, is whose face? And whose name is here?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gaba = gambar ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gaba = gambar ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ane roo, &lt;&lt;Na d'ee, unu Duae do pereda Roma!&gt;&gt;<bt>They said, &lt;&lt;That is owned by the King of the Roma government!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ta lii ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;Kiri mi nahère, wie pa do pereda ne do unu do pereda, j'e wie pa Deo ne do unu Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus said, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, give to the government (people) what is the right of the government, and give to God what is the right of God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="higa = authority, right"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">higa = authority, right</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kiri mi nahère, wie pa do"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Kiri mi nahère, wie pa do pereda ne do higa do pereda, j'e wie pa Deo ne do higa Deo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta rènge ne lii b'ale Yesus mi nahère, ta madalae ke roo hari-hari, ri ne lii pedai Noo do petuu. Hèku nara d'o roo kewèhu ta kèpe Yesus.<bt>Hearing Yesus' response like that, they were all amazed, because He had spoken truly. So they couldn't find an issue to arrest Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kewèhu = alasan, hal, masalah (simpul)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kewèhu = alasan, hal, masalah (simpul) ; hengodo = Dimu-heran + Seba-bingung ; kebèda = Seba (takuju) kagum + speechless or unable to do anything = (Mehara) gèb'a ~ hena ; hemèla = @@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua muri wari, nga lua pebanga-èmu pa liru-bèla era ko, we ad'o?<bt>The issue of living again, and marriage in heaven or not?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 22:23-33; Luka 20:27-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Era èhi paratei agama do wala, ne ngara paratei Saduki. Ne lii aj'a roo, do made nara d'oke ta muri wari. Pa d'ara he wari, dèka do pèri dèu ngati paratei Saduki la pehero Yesus.<bt>There was another religious party, named the Saduki party. They taught that dead people cannot live again. One time, several Saduki party people came to trap Yesus.</bt><note reference="12:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu Yesu 23:8</note><v n="19" />Pedai roo nga Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama Guru! Lua petèka ama-èpu dii Musa, do hure d'o b'uke wie dii, mihe ane: ki era he dèu momone do banga-èmu, j'e made nga d'o b'ule ana, ne mone ari ri noo ta banga-èmu nga mobèni ihi-èmu a'a nee, mij'e ta era kolo-loro natuu a'a noo do made nee.<bt>They spoke with Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! Our-inc ancestor Musa wrote establishing for us-inc, like this: if a man marries and dies without a child, that male's younger.sibling must marry that wife of his older sibling, in.order.that there be descendants for that elder.sibling of his that is dead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kolo-loro = turunan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kolo-loro = turunan</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 25:5</note><v n="20" />Mi nahère ke ne lii aj'a Musa. Ne keb'ali j'ii mi nahee: Era mone pidu. Mone a'a nee, ta banga-èmu ke. Moko ta made, nga d'o b'ule nga ana.<bt>Musa actually did teach like.that. But we-ex want to ask like.this. There are seven male siblings. The first marries. Then he dies, and has no child.</bt><v n="21" />Moko ne mone ari do penanuhi nga noo, ta banga-èmu ke nga ihi-èmu a'a noo. Tui d'o, ta made ke ne momone, nga d'o b'ule nga ana. Mi nahère lema nga ari do ketèlu; bènga-èmu nga mobèni na ène. Made, nga d'o b'ule nga ana ri ma.<bt>Then his younger.sibling that follows him, marries that older sibling's wife. Not long he also dies, with having a child. Like.that also with younger.sibling number three: he marries that woman. He dies, and has no child.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ri ma = pula"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ri ma = pula</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Mi nahère ke teruu, tade mone ari tèka. Made, nga d'o b'ule nga ana lema. Ta made leke ne mobèni nee.<bt>Like that continuing until younger.sibling youngest.child. He dies, without children. And then, that woman dies.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Naa! Ne keb'ali j'ii mi nahee: ne mobèni na ène do èla ke banga-èmu nga hari do pidu dèu. Kiri d'ai ne pedèka rai rai-wawa, j'e pemuri wari ri Deo ne do made he, na mii ke ne ihi-èmu mobèni na ène, ti telora do pidu dèu he?&gt;&gt;<bt>So! Now we want to ask like.this: that woman has already been married with 7 males! But when the end of the world when God gives live again to the dead people, that woman will be whose wife from among those 7 people?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Pa d'ara lii keb'ali muu na ène, tada d'o muu ne ihi do hure d'o b'uke. Lema tada d'o muu ne kuaha Deo. Hèku, rihi hala ke ne pengee muu!<bt>Then Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;If you-pl ask like.that, it.means you do.not understand the contents of God's Book. And you also do.not understand God's power/authority. So, your thinking here is really wrong!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />D'èno we mi nahee! Pa liru-bèla b'ule d'o ke lua pebanga-èmu. Harièle do made do pemuri wari ri Deo, ad'o ke do ta banga-èmu. Mi nahère lema mi dèu pejuu Deo he, ad'o do ta banga-èmu.<bt>Listen, it's like.this! In heaven, there is no marriage. All dead people whom God makes live again, there is none that marries. It's like that also for *angels (God's underlings) don't marry.</bt><v n="26" />Ngine nee, keb'ali muu ne dèu do made he, do ta muri wari roo, we ad'o? Ta pika Yaa pa muu do hure do b'uke ri Musa, era ne lii ped'èii j'ara lua he kepue na aj'u, do weo ri ai, tapulara kèpu d'o. He wina ko ma ke ri muu ne lii ped'èii na ène, we ad'o? Ta d'ai ne weo ai pa aj'u do na ène, ta pika ke Deo pa Musa, mihe ane, &lt;Yaa ke na d'ee, Deo Muri ri ama-èpu èu, Abraham, Isak nga J'ako. Harièle roo mejura teruu pa Yaa hape ma awe do na d'ee.&gt;<bt>Earlier you-pl asked about dead people, whether they will live again, or not? I tell you what is written/established by Musa, there is a story about that small tree/bush that burned.with.fire but didn't burn.up. Do you remember that story, or not? When the fire was burning shining in that bush, God told Musa saying, &lt;I here [am] your-sg ancestor's/forefather's Lord God. That is Abraham, Isak, and J'ako. They all continually worship Me until now.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="weo = menyala ; kana ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">weo = menyala ; kana = mengkilap, bersilau ; he kepue na aj'u = a small tree (na &lt; ana)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 3:6</note><v n="27" />Toi ri dii, ta ne ama-èpu dii nahère, tui ke ne made. Ku dèu do muri do mejura pa Deo, ad'o do made, to? Tapulara, ri do pedai ke Deo, ta Noo ke ne Deo Muri roo, ku do pedai dii ta do muri wari ke roo. Hèku dèu do made, do muri wari. Hèku, ki pèro teruu ri muu ne lii aj'a ta do made ad'o do muri wari, rihi hala ke muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc know that those grandfathers were already long dead. Actually it's living people that worship God, not dead people, right? But because God had already said He still is their Lord God, that.is.why we know that they have lived again. Thus, dead people live again. So if you continually hold that teaching saying, dead people don't live again, you really are extremely wrong!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ne lua pejara ti lii pedai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ne lua pejara ti lii pedai na ène, Deo ad'o natuu do made, tapulara Deo natuu do muri. Rowi do minhère ke maji lema Abraham, Ishak nga Yakob ta do èla pemade, do ta pekèd'i wari ri Deo. Tituwata dèu do muri we do nara ta wie hu nga mejura pa Deo. Hèku kiri pèro teru rowi muu ne lua tada muu to dod'o era lai kèd'i ti d'ara made mada, ad'o do petuu!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua d'èi nga Deo, nga lua d'èi nga dèu rai-wawa<bt>Love the Lord and love people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 22:34-40; Luka 10:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Pa d'ara awe na ène, era he dèu guru agama, do rènge ne lii peb'ale Yesus nga paratei do Saduki he. Pa d'ara pengee noo, ne lii pedai Yesus do pelèka woie. Ta keb'ali ke noo pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Ta keb'ali yaa, mi nahee: ne petèka had'a rai dii, nga lii pereda agama dii, do rihi ae! Ti harièle lii pereda do petèka Musa he, namii ke do kerihi?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there was a religious teacher who had heard Yesus responding to the people from the Saduki party. That religious teacher thought Yesus had answered them fittingly. Then he asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Father! I want to ask like.this: Our-inc tradition's rules, and religion's commands, very many. From all the commands established by Musa, which is/are the most important?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pelèka = cocok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pelèka = cocok</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01744b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Ne lii pereda do kerihi do hure d'o b'uke, mi nahee:<bt>Yesus responded, &lt;&lt;The command that is the most important that has been written and established (in Scripture) is like.this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Harièle dèu pa Isra'el, d'èno nga woie!<bt>&lt;All people in Israel! You-pl hear well!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Ne Deo nee, Noo ke ne Deo Muri dii,<bt>That God, He is our-inc Lord God,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nga Muri Mone dii!<bt>and our-inc King/Sovereign!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">B'ule do ke do wala, ngati Noo!<bt>There is none other, only just Him!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="30" />Hèku, d'èi tèra muu nga Deo Muri muu <span class="Italic">perihe</span> ngati harièle lai.<bt>Consequently, you-pl must really love Lord God |ibeyond/more than|r all things.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ri mi nahère ke, hengee tèra we ne ade-pengee muu nga Muri,<bt>Because of that, you must always remember/think about (word for child yearning for parent) for the *Lord,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="leru = rakus, gemas, rindu, resah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">leru = rakus, gemas, rindu, resah ; pekateme = seluruh ; petone = exclusive focus, hanya itu saja</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">tade kehème we Noo nga woie,<bt>understand Him intimately/close relationship,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kehème = akrab"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kehème = akrab</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nga j'ège petadi ne lua d'èi Noo.&gt;<bt>and work diligently to follow His will.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rui-kelue = segala tenaga (tulang-urat) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rui-kelue = segala tenaga (tulang-urat) ; petadi = tekun ; hèla èni = strive (?) CHECK ; wohe la arui = (idiom) strive, work hard ; tuu ngee = pleased w/s.o., senang karena sso ; banga (hanga?) = senang, rindu</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:29-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 6:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Nga lii pereda ked'ue nee, mi nahee:<bt>And the second command is like.this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;D'èi nga dèu do hewala, mi d'èi nga ngi'u èu miha.&gt;<bt>&lt;You-s must love other people, the same as you love your own self.&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">D'ue nahee ke ne lii pereda do kerihi. B'ule d'oke ne lii pereda do wala, do rihi ngati d'ue lii pereda do na d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>These are the two commands which are the most important. There are no other commands which are more important that these two commands.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kètu Agama nga Lua Petèka Agama 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ta lii rike ne guru agama ne pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Tèra! Ne do lii Papa nee, do petuu. Deo Muri ke ne do Muri Mone ri dii, b'ule d'oke Deo do hewala.<bt>Then, that religion teacher spoke again to Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;True! That which Papa has said, is correct. Lord God is our Sovereign, and there is no other God.</bt><note reference="12:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 4:35</note><v n="33" />D'èi tèra we dii nga Noo perihe ngati harièle lai, j'e hengee petone ne ade-pengee dii nga Noo, tade kehème we Noo nga woie, nga j'ège petadi ne lua d'èi Noo. Nga d'èi dii nga dèu do hewala, mi d'èi nga ngi'u dii miha. Rihi mengèlu d'ara ke Deo, ne j'èga mi nahère, ngata had'èita pedute lua petèka agama he we. Na ène, rihi woie ri ko noo, ngati b'ada tunu menahu, nga wie b'ara do wala pa Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc must love Him more that all, to-point-that we-inc always remember/think about Him (total focus), understand him intimately, and work diligently to follow His will. And we must love other people, same as we love our own body. That, pleases God more than if we only just follow religious regulations. That is better than if we just burn animal sacrifices or, give other thing to God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tunu menahu = korban bakaran ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tunu menahu = korban bakaran ; we = must</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 6:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Pedutu lii b'ale guru agama na ène, pengee ri Yesus do tada woie ke noo. Ta lii ke Yesus pa noo, &lt;&lt;Dae hudi ke èu ta jad'èi dèu Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing the religious teacher answer like that, Yesus thought that he understood well. Then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;You-sg have almost become God's person.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Èla pe na ène, b'ule d'oke he dèu he, do b'ani ta keb'ali nengaa we pa Yesus, ri b'ule d'oke dèu do mèka pa Noo.<bt>After that, there were no other people who dared ask anything of Yesus, because there was no person who could succeed/win.over Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèka = dapat, untung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèka = dapat, untung</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:28-34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 10:25-28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus ti kolo-loro duae Dau, tapulara Noo do jad'èi lema mone pereda pa duae Dau<bt>Kristus, is king Dau's descendant, but He is also king Dau's boss</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 22:41-46; Luka 20:41-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Èla pe na ène, pe ko ma Yesus ta wie lii aj'a pa dèu do pa d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Ta keb'ali ke Noo pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi namii pengee muu? Ne lua aj'a guru agama he, Kristus nee, Noo ke do pej'èu'e ri Deo rai uru he. Pedutu lii roo, Kristus ne kolo-loro duae Dau we. Na ène, ad'o do petuu.<bt>After that, Yesus still taught those people at the *temple. Then he took.issue with them saying, &lt;&lt;According to you-pl thinking, how.is.it? The religion teachers teach about that Kristus, whom God appointed from long.ago. According to them, Kristus is only just king Dau's descendant. That is not true.</bt><v n="36" />Ri do uru, do pake Dau ri Hengaa Megala Deo ta b'uke, mihe ane:<bt>Because before, God's *Holy Spirit used Dau to write, saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Èla ke Deo pelii pa mone pereda pa yaa, mihe ane,<bt>&lt;God has told my boss, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone pereda = penguasa, pemerintahan, atasan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone pereda = penguasa, pemerintahan, atasan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Mai we ma mej'èd'èipa era do rihi d'èia keb'ue pa ai d'anga Yaa.<bt>&lt;&lt;Come to sit in this most.honored place at my right hand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ai g'ana = sabla kanan ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ai g'ana = sabla kanan ; ai keg'ana = tangan kanan ; keb'ue = terhormat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Do ta tao ri Yaa hari-hari ihi muhu Èu, ta pewawa èni pa Èu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>I will make all your enemies, surrender/humble themselves to you.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37a" />Pelai ti mi nahère ke ne toi ri dii, ta duae Dau miha pale Kristus ta &lt;mone pereda&gt; pa noo. Hèku, mi nahère ke kiri lii dèu ta Kristus ne kolo-loro Dau we, keteme ded'o! Rowi Noo miha do jad'èi ita mone pereda pa duae Dau.&gt;&gt;<bt>From that we know that king Dau himself called Kristus, saying &lt;boss&gt;. That.means if people say that Kristus, is only just king Dau's descendant, that is not fully true/not sufficient! Because He is also obviously king Dau's boss.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="we = hanya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">we = hanya</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lii Yesus jaga-meniga ti lua pote-èpi guru agama he<bt>Yesus says be-careful (doublet) with the religion teacher's deceit (doublet)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="penaja = terhadap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">penaja = terhadap</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 23:1-36; Luka 20:45-47)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37b" />Ta pedai Yesus mi nahère, ae dèu do mengèlu d'ara ne d'èno lii pedai Noo.<bt>When Yesus spoke like he just did, then many people liked to hear Him.</bt><v n="38" />Ta pika rike Noo pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Jaga-meniga ie muu pehed'apa nga guru agama he. Roo he do d'èi talèpa nga pake b'aj'u do pera'u pa wurai, la telora dèu lowe, mij'e ta ngèdi roo ri dèu, j'e lii, &lt;Mone kepai he ke j'e nahii!&gt;<bt>Then He told again to them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must be careful with regard to the religious teachers. They like to go.around(outside.home) wearing their long robes that drag on the ground (longer the robe/sarong = higher the social status), among many people, so.that people will see them saying, &lt;Wow! Them there, are really big(important) people!&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="talèpa = jalan-jalan ; pera'u-reka ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">talèpa = jalan-jalan ; pera'u-reka = raroso ; pelangu = tegur ; pehed'apa = berhadapan (broad meaning)</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Kiri maho roo la d'ara èmu heb'aj'a, la era lai tao, kale ri roo ne era mejèd'èido rihi woie, mij'e ta ngèdi ri dèu lowe he.<bt>If they enter a worship house, or they attend a party, they always seek the best sitting place, so.that many people will see them.</bt><v n="40" />Jaga-meniga, oo! Roo he do rihi d'èi la peluu ne mobèni wue he, raba ne èmu-kemali roo harièle. D'ai i'a pewuni roo ne woapa had'a roo, pa namada dèu lowe, nga heb'aj'a titu do rihi tui. Ane roo mij'e ta lii dèu ke ta dèu do mèu ade-pengee. Do ta wie roo ri Deo ne ruwolo do rihi mejèni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But be.careful oo! Cuz they like to/perpetually deceive widows, to steal/rob all their houses-belongings (doublet). But in front of many people, they cover/hide that evil of theirs, and stand praying a long time. They want that people to say they have clean liver-thinking. But later God will give very heavy punishment to them.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ruwolo = hukuman, punishment ; raba"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ruwolo = hukuman, punishment ; raba = rampas ; peluu = menipu ; dèla-ked'oa = telan, kodo ame ; penaja = guard yourself against ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bèni b'alu do kehia do wie kolekte do rihi ae<bt>A poor widow puts in collection money that is the bigger/est</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 21:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Èla pe na ène, ta la mejèd'èike Yesus pehed'apa nga pèti b'ara j'ola pa Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Heleo ri Noo ne dèu-dèu do dèka la pulu doi kolekte la d'ara pèti b'ara j'ola. Ngèdi ri Noo ne do kaja he pulu doi rihi ae.<bt>After that, Yesus went to sit facing the offering box in the *temple. He watched people come put their collection money in that box. He saw rich people also come put large amounts of their money there.</bt><v n="42" />Dèka lema he dèu bèni b'alu do kehia, la heb'aj'a. Pulu noo la d'ara pèti nee, d'ue doi wo naiki.<bt>Then, a poor widow also come to pray/worship. She put 2 smallest money.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pulu = kasi maso"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pulu = kasi maso</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ta kewu'e ke ri Yesus ne ana aj'a Noo, j'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Heleo ko ri muu pe'ie ne bèni b'alu na nii. Ne pulu noo d'ue doi we, tapulara rihi ae ke ne pulu noo ngati pulu harièle dèu.<bt>Then Yesus hand.motioned.to.come His disciples saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl look well at that widow. She has only put in 2 moneys, but she has given more than all people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gape = kewu'e"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gape = kewu'e</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Ne dèu do hewala he harièle, pulu roo kolekte ti doi rihi pake. Tapulara bèni b'alu d'ee, harièle ke ne doi noo ne wie pa Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Those other people all put in collection from their extra/leftover money. But this widow here, she has given all her money to God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Rowi ne b'ara j'ola roo hari-hari,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Rowi ne b'ara j'ola roo hari-hari, dèka ngati muri mada pa d'ara kede'e. Tapulara bèni balu do kehia nee, j'ola ngati d'ara muri mada kehia gahara noo. Harièle muri mada ke noo ne do j'ole nee. (Ne b'ara j'ola do pemaho rowi roo, ègu nga ti do hiha pake roo. Tapulara mobèni do kehia gahara nane, wie ri noo harièle ne do era pa noo, pa Deo).</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ta pika d'ènge Yesus Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo do ta keloli<bt>Yesus *prophesies/foretells the *Temple's destruction</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:1-2; Luka 21:5-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Èla pe na ène, ta pekèd'èike Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo he ti Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Ta d'ai roo ne mèhu èni, ta lii ke he dèu ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama, ee! Heleo ko ri Ama! Ne gaa-kele'e Èmu d'ee. D'ai woie pera'a ne wowadu worena he!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and His disciples were about to leave the *temple. When they were exiting, one of His disciples said, &lt;&lt;Father, ee! Look at this! This Temple (short form) is really beautiful! They really stacked/placed these heavy rocks together really well!&gt;&gt; [Heavy rocks means boulder sized, not pebble sized.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="keloli = jato, rubu ; pera'a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">keloli = jato, rubu ; pera'a = susun, atur ; gaa-kele'e = indah, mulia</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Petuu! D'ai gaa tèra ma ne Èmu na d'ee! Tui d'oke, j'e pekelole ne Èmu d'ee, pemenyèla ne wowadu he.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;True! This House is really beautiful2! But not much longer, they will completely knock down these rocks destroying (the Temple).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pekelole = rubuh, ; pemenyèla ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pekelole = rubuh, ; pemenyèla = ancor abis;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Telia-telia pedèka rai-wawa<bt>Signs of the end of the world</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:3-14; Luka 21:7-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ta kako ke Yesus he la b'ojo Saitun, j'e mejèd'èipa era do pehed'apa nga Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo. Ta dèka ke do èpa dèu ana aj'a Noo la pedai nga Noo miha: Petu, J'ako, Johani, nga Anderia.<bt>And then, Yesus (collective) went to Saitun hill, and sat at a place that faced that *Temple. Then four of His disciples came to talk alone with Him. That.is, Petu, J'ako, Johani, and Anderia.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="telia = tanda"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">telia = tanda</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Ta keb'ali ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Peteleo ri ko ri Ama ne lii pedai do ngine nee. Pèri ke ne jad'èi lai na ène? J'e mi namii ne telia he?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Explain again what You were talking about earlier. When will its time come? And its signs, how.will.they.be?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Had'èita jaga ie muu! B'ole luu muu.<bt>Then Yesus answered them, saying, &lt;&lt;As.long.as you-pl watch out carefully! Don't get decieved.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="luu = tipu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">luu = tipu</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ae hine ne dèu do ta dèka nga tèb'a kodo, j'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;Yaa ke na d'ee, Kristus, do jaje ri Deo rai uru he.&gt; Ae ne dèu do luu ri roo.<bt>Later there will be many people who come beating their chests saying, &lt;I here [am] Kristus, the person who God has promised from before.&gt; And then they will deceive many people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèb'a kodo = pukul dada (sombong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèb'a kodo = pukul dada (sombong, jago)</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Kiri ngèdi muu dèu do pemuhu, ki rèngi lii ped'èii ta do era muhu pa mii-pa mii, b'ole keba'a ne pengee muu. Ne lai do mi nahère do ta jad'èi uru, tapulara d'ai ded'o ne awe pedèka rai-wawa d'ee.<bt>If you see people warring, or you hear stories/rumours saying, there is war in various places, you-pl don't need to be worried. Cuz like that, has to happen first, but the time for the end of the world has not.yet arrived.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="reja = gelisah, kurang harmonis ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">reja = gelisah, kurang harmonis ; keba'a = ragu, bimbang</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Do ta pemuhu kejie dèu nga kejie dèu. Pemuhu hewue rai nga hewue rai. Era d'ai ie pa mii-pa mii. Do ta era ne awe rihi menganga rai pa mii-pa mii. Harièle telia nahère, hela'u mi hedui mi mobèni do ta metana ana.<bt>Later one social group will fight against another social group. One nation/region will fight against another nation. There will be earthquakes all.over.the.place. And hunger season that is extremely severe! These all are signs, like a women who is suffering (generic for labour) about to give birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'ai ie = gempa bumi ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">d'ai ie = gempa bumi ; leru = tidak tenang, sudah dlm proses melahirkan ; menganga rai = famine ; ta = "akan" ; do ta = "akan"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mobèni do leru ta metana ana."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mobèni do leru ta metana ana.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Hèku, jaga ie we muu! Do ta dèka roo ma kèpa muu, j'e nuni muu la hed'apa do hèpo kewèlu agama. Wuhu-d'aba muu ri dèu pa d'ara èmu heb'aj'a he. Uj'u ai muu, j'e ègu la hed'apa do pereda, pelai ti pedute Yaa. Awe tuu muu ta ped'èie j'ara lua Yaa pa roo.<bt>So (consequently) you must watch out carefully! Later they will come capture/arrest you to drag take you to the religion court. And they will repeatedly.beat you in the worship houses. And they will tie your hands, and take you to people who have authority, because you follow Me. That is a time/opportunity for you to tell them about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kewèlu = perkara (legal) ; nuni"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kewèlu = perkara (legal) ; nuni = drag ; do hèpo kewèlu (usually mone hèpo kewèlu) = judge</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Awe do na ène ke, ne"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Awe do na ène ke, ne kehoo pa muu ta ped'ire j'ara lua Yaa pa roo.</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Ne dèu unu Deo he ta la pika uru ko ne Lii Hag'a D'ara j'ara lua Yaa pa hari-hari kejie dèu pa harièle keb'ihu rai-wawa, j'e'itu d'ai lalod'o pedèka rai-wawa.<bt>God's people must first go tell the Good Story to all social groups in the (far) corners of this world, only.then will the days (broad) of the end of the world arrive.</bt><v n="11" />Henge ie, oo! Kiri uj'u ne ai muu j'e pera'u la hed'apa dèu do hèpo kewèlu, b'ole meda'u muu, j'e pengee, &lt;Ta nengaa do ta pedai ri yaa pa nii?&gt; j'e, &lt;Mi namii ke ne lii b'ale yaa?&gt; Kiri d'ai ne awe na ène, palii we muu pedutu nengaa do palii Hengaa Megala Deo pa muu pa awe na ène.<bt>Remember! If they tie your hands and take you before the court, you don't need to be afraid thinking, &lt;What will I say there?&gt; and &lt;How will I answer?&gt; If that time has arrived, you just talk, according to what God's *Holy Spirit tells you at that time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kelau = giring"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kelau = giring</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:9-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:17-20, Luka 12:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Pa d'ara hewue èmu, kiri era dèu do parahaj'a pa Yaa, tuèhu noo miha ta kale ruj'ara ta pemade noo. Kiri ana ne do parahaj'a, ama noo miha do ta pemade noo. Kiri ina-ama noo do parahaj'a pa Yaa, ana roo do ta pemade roo.<bt>In one house, if there is a person who believes in Me, his own kin will seek a way to kill him. If it's a child who believes, his own father will killl him. If it's a parent who believes in Me, his their child will kill them.</bt><v n="13" />Hèku, dèu do ta bubu made nga muu, pelai ti parahaj'a nga Yaa. Tapulara naduu do mèka wènge tade pedèka, do ta wie ne helama pa noo ri Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Thus, people will hate/be veangeful toward you, because you believe in Me. But whoever endures to the end, surely God will give *salvation to him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèka wènge = sabar ; tahan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèka wènge = sabar ; tahan ; bubu made = dendam</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 10:22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jaga-meniga, ri awe pedèka rai-wawa do umu ke!<bt>Watch well (doublet), cuz the end of the world is near!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:15-28; Luka 21:20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta pedai teruu rike Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Do ta dèka he dèu do rihi tao apa. Maho noo la titu pa era do mèu do megala pa d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo, dod'o jèma tuu noo pa ène, ta pera'e ne era na ène. Ri mi nahère ke, ta b'ale kej'unga ke Deo nga era na ène. Kiri nga ngèdi ri muu ne lai do mi nahère, jaga ie muu! (Naduu do aj'e ne lii na d'ee, jaga ie lema). Lai jad'èi do mi nahère he èhi rutada, ne lod'o apa-kerewe nee, pa kelae ke. Kiri ngèdi ne lai do mi nahère, dèu do pee pa propensi Yudea, kèd'èij'e perai la lede la boj'o.<bt>Yesus continued talking saying, &lt;&lt;An extremely evil person will come. He will enter and stand in the place that is taboo/sacred (doublet) in God's *temple, which is not appropriate for him there, and make that place dirty/defiled. That.is.why God will turn his back leaving that place. If you see like.that, be careful! (Whoever reads this, must also be careful!) Those matters are a sign that evil days are just in front of the door. If you see these things, people in Yudea province get up and run to the mountains (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="era do mèu do megala ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">era do mèu do megala = (majemuk) ; kalai (branch) CIE with kelae (door)</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dane 9:27, 11:31, 12:11</note><v n="15" />Mèriai roo ne perai, mij'e ta d'o abu roo ihilaka. Ki era do mèhu èni ti d'ara èmu, b'ole b'ale rii la èba b'ara nengaa we.<bt>And they must run fast, so.that they don't be overcome by misfortune. If there is any who have come.out of their house, don't return home to get any more things.</bt><v n="16" />Dèu do era pa d'oka, b'ole b'ale rii la èmu la èba hij'i. Perai teruu we!<bt>People in the gardens, don't return home to get blankets. Just keep on running!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'aga = ladang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'aga = ladang</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 17:31</note><v n="17" />Ne do rihi hedui, mobèni do tèni ae, nga rena iki ana. Rowi laha d'o roo ne perai.<bt>Those in greatest difficulty are woman who are pregnant, and the mothers with newborns. For they obviously can't run fast. [nursing = explicit &gt; implicit]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tèni ae = hamil, mengandung ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tèni ae = hamil, mengandung ; laha = cepat</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Rihi ie muu ta heb'aj'a, mij'e dod'o jad'èi ne lai na ène pa awe èj'i liru.<bt>So, it's better that you-pl pray to request that those things, don't happen in the rainy season.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rubu èj'i = musim hujan yg"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rubu èj'i = musim hujan yg terus-menerus ; èj'i liru = rainy season</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ri ne awe na ène, d'ai tèra ne hedui! Rai pe'era ri Deo rai-wawa d'ee, tade awe na d'ee ngèdi ded'o dèu ta lake ne lai hedui-herui do mi nahère. Èla pe na ène, b'ule d'o ke ne lai hedui-herui do mi nahère do ta lake wari ri dèu.<bt>Cuz that time will be very extremely difficult. Starting from God created/established this world until now, people have not yet seen trouble-suffering (doublet) like that. And later people will also never see again difficulty like that.</bt><note reference="13:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dane 12:1, Pengède pa Johani 7:14</note><v n="20" />Ki d'o pehe'ète ke ri Deo ne awe hedui do mi nahère, b'ule d'oke he dèu he do nara ta muri mada. Tapulara, pelai ti rihi d'èi Deo nga dèu do èla pepili ri Noo he, ri mi nahère ke ku pehe'ète ri Noo ne lai hedui-herui na ène.<bt>If God does not shorten/make brief that time of suffering, there would not be a single person who can endure living. But, because God loves His people whom He chose, that.is.why He shortens (time) those difficulties (doublet).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pengahe ~ pengaha ; peb'ab'e ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pengahe ~ pengaha ; peb'ab'e ~ peb'ab'a = kasi pendek (things) ; pehe'ète = bekin singkat/pendek (waktu)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ki d'ai la lod'o-lod'o do mi nahère, rèngi ri muu ne lii pedai dèu, mihe ane, &lt;Heleo we! Kristus ne pa d'ee!&gt; Lii had'e, &lt;Kristus nèi pa nii!&gt; B'ole d'èno muu!<bt>If/when those days arrive, you-pl will hear people say, &lt;Look! Kristus is here!&gt; Others will say, &lt;Kristus is yonder!&gt; Don't you-pl listen!</bt><v n="22" />Era dèu do dèka, nga tèba kodo, nga lii, &lt;Yaa ke na d'ee, Kristus!&gt; Era lema do lii, &lt;Yaa ke na d'ee, dèu ub'a ngati Deo.&gt; Ae ne madalae do ta tao ri roo pake kuaha wango ta peluu dèu. La hèku-hèku ri roo ta peluu ne dèu Deo.<bt>There will be people coming and beating their chests saying, &lt;I here, am Kristus!&gt; Another will say, &lt;I here, am God's *prophet.&gt; They will do all sorts of *miracles using the power of evil.spirits to trick people. They try their best so that God's people will also get tricked!</bt><v n="23" />Jaga-meniga ie muu! Uru nga dod'o dèka dae ne awe hedui-herui nee, èla ke muu pe pehewina uru ri Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you must watch (doublet) well! Before those difficult days have arrived, I have reminded you about them beforehand.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehewina = kasi inga, ingatkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehewina = kasi inga, ingatkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua dèka Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu<bt>The coming of the True/Ideal Human</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:29-31; Luka 21:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ta pedai teruu ke Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Kiri moko ne awe hedui-herui nee,<bt>Then Yesus continued speaking to those *disciples of His, saying, &lt;&lt;If/when those difficult days are over,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lore = terus (janggal)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lore = terus (janggal)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Do ta kerèba ne mada lod'o,<bt>&lt;The sun will become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Weo d'oke wèru.<bt>The moon also will no longer shine.</bt><note reference="13:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, Yeskia 32:7, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15, Pengède pa Johani 6:12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Moto he keloro ti liru-bèla,<bt>Stars will fall from the sky,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="moto = bintang ; keloro ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">moto = bintang ; keloro = berjatuhan (Seba) ; keloro = berak (Mehara) ; meloro = berjatuhan (Mehara)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">nga harièle kuaha do era pa liru-bèla, kenyawu-nyela.&gt;<bt>and all powers in the sky will become chaotic (doublet).&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kenyawu-nyela = kaco-balo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kenyawu-nyela = kaco-balo</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:4, Yoel 2:10, Pengède pa Johani 6:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èla pe mi nahère, j'e'itu ngède ri dèu, ta Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu. Do ta puru Yaa pa d'ara merèmu ti liru-bèla. Do ta ngède ri harièle dèu ne kuaha nga mèu-megala Yaa!<bt>After that, only.then will people see me, this Ideal/Prototype Human. I will descend in clauds from the sky/heaven. And all people will see My power and glory/shininess (doublet)!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèu-megala = kemuliaan, bacaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèu-megala = kemuliaan, bacaya</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dane 7:13, Pengède pa Johani 1:7</note><v n="27" />Do ta pereda ri Yaa pa dèu pejuu Deo pa liru-bèla, ta la pekupu harièle dèu do èla pepili ri Yaa, ti èpa keb'ihu rai-wawa.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will order God's *underlings in heaven, to go gather all the people that I have chosen from the four ends/corners of the earth.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lod'o hedui-herui rutada lua dèka Yesus<bt>Difficult days are a sign of Yesus coming</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:32-35; Luka 21:29-33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ta pedai teruu ke Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Èbe ri Yaa ne lii pehèku pa aj'u do muri. Kiri lara ke ne rèu, rutada hedèka ke wèru wadu.<bt>Yesus continued speaking, saying, &lt;&lt;I take a *parable/example/comparison from a living tree. If its young leaves begin turning yellow, that sign says hot season (lit. rock month) is soon to come.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hed'èra = hedèka = suda dekat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hed'èra = hedèka = suda dekat ; pana = hot ; wèru wadu = hot &amp; dry season (lit rock season)</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Mi nahère lema, kiri ngèdi ke ri muu ne lod'o hedui-herui do dèka nee, mii do èla pepika ri Yaa pa muu ngine, rutada ta ne awe dèka Yaa umu ke.<bt>Like.that also, if you-pl see difficult days arrive, like what I just told you, that sign says that I am very soon to come.</bt><v n="30" />D'èno pe woie! Ti harièle dèu do muri mada pa awe na d'ee, era ko dod'o made, pa awe dèka ne lod'o hedui-herui ène.<bt>Listen well! From all people who live now, later there are those who won't yet die, when those difficult days arrive.</bt><v n="31" />Maji liru-bèla nga rai-wawa ta ele ta mèra, tapulara lii pedai Yaa na d'ee, peloro hape la lod'o namii-mii.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even.if the sky (doublet) and earth (doublet) disappear completely, but this talking/message of Mine will endure until forever.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèra = lenyap ; ta ele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèra = lenyap ; ta ele ta mèra = hilang lenyap</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua dèka Yesus toi d'o ri he dèu he<bt>The time of Yesus' coming is not known by a single person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 24:36-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ta pedai rike Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ule d'o he dèu he do toi ne lod'o nga jaa dèka wari Yaa. Dèu-dèu pejuu Deo pa liru-bèla lema, toi d'o. Ri Yaa le miha, toi d'o. Tituwata Ama Yaa we, ne do toi.<bt>Yesus added, saying, &lt;&lt;There is not one person who knows when is the day and hour (assim. loan) of My coming again. God's *angels in heaven, they also don't know. I myself, also don't know. Only just My Father who knows.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jaa = jam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">jaa = jam</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 24:36</note><v n="33" />Ri mi nahère ke, jaga ie muu, ri dod'o toi ri muu pèri ne awe dèka Yaa.<bt>Because of that, you-pl must watch carefully, because you do not know when is the time of My coming.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Tui d'o ke ne awe, j'e lènga Yaa ti telora muu, do ta dèka ri ma Yaa wari. Mii dèu do lènga ti èmu, la rai do j'èu. Pereda ri noo pa dèu pee nga noo, lita pemoke pe'ie ne èmu-kemali noo. Peb'age roo ne j'èga he dèu-he dèu. Tèka lii noo pa mone jaga toka, ta jaga-meniga pe'ie, tade b'ale noo.<bt>Not much longer I will leave you, but then I will come again. Just like a person who goes leaving his house to go to a far country/land/region. He orders the people staying with him (=underlings/ servants/extended household) to take good care of that house-belongings (doublet). And he divides work for each individual. He instructs the watcher-of-the-door to guard well, until he returns.home.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'uri = potong ; lènga ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'uri = potong ; lènga = left, gone, sudah pergi, tinggalkan, lepas, keluar, tidak ada lagi di situ ; lita = omong bilang ; pemoke = mengurus ; toka = pintu pagar ; kelae = pintu ruma</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 12:36-38</note><v n="35" />Jaga muu nimèd'a-nilod'o, ri dod'o toi ri muu pèri ne awe dèka do muri èmu nee. B'ale mèd'a lod'o we, telora mèd'a we, nilod'o we, awe hèu lod'o we, toi d'o ri muu ta pèri ne awe.<bt>You-pl also must watch day-night, because you do not know when the house owner/master returns.home. Returns.home afternoon or, middle of the night or, in the daylight or, when the sun is coming up or, You don't know the time.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nilod'o-nimèd'a ~ nimèd'a-nilod'o (latter preferred, seen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nilod'o-nimèd'a ~ nimèd'a-nilod'o (latter preferred, seen as more natural) = siang-malam ; muri èmu = tuan rumah, ex of muri ; @@ we3 here as 'or' in open disjunction</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Ngita dèka noo nga hewèka, j'e abu muu nga b'èj'i pegoo-koko.<bt>Don't let it be that he comes unexpectedly, and catches you sleeping snoring.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hegoo-koko = manggorok (Dimu) ~ pegoo-koko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hegoo-koko = manggorok (Dimu) ~ pegoo-koko (Seba) ; hewèka = segera</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Hèku, mi namii ne lii pedai Yaa pa muu, do ta pedai lema Yaa nga dèu do hewala he, lii ta, &lt;Jaga pe'ie muu, ta mate ne lod'o dèka Yaa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Thus, what I am telling you, I also tell other people saying, &lt;You-p must watch carefully to await My arrival.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">(Mi nahère we, ne lii pedai Yesus nga ana aj'a Noo pa b'ojo Saitun.)<bt>(This is the end (to that point) of what Yesus talked about with his *disciples on Saitun hill.)</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mone kepai he kale pengee ta kèpe mena'o Yesus<bt>The important people plot to capture Lord Yesus quietly</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:1-5; Luka 22:1-2; Johani 11:45-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1-2" />Èla pe mi nahère, ne mone ketèu pa kètu agama Jahudi he pee nga kale pengee ta kèpe mena'o Yesus. Ne d'èi roo ta pemade ke Noo. Tapulara pelii roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Taha ko! B'ole mèriai dii ne kèpe Noo, ri lod'o nga'a-kewèhu he dèka ke. Ngita kèd'èilila ne dèu lowe he, ta pehala nga dii.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the *chief priests (elder males of the Yahudi priests) still were plotting to capture Yesus quietly. They wanted to kill him. But they spoke to each other, saying, &lt;&lt;Hang on! Let's not capture Him too quickly, because the feast days are near. Don't let it be that the crowds attack and blame us-inc.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kèpe mena'o = tangkap curi (catch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kèpe mena'o = tangkap curi (catch sneakily) ; lod'o nga'a-kewèhu = hari raya ; kèd'i lila = attack spontaneously ; ketèu = katuas ; mone ketèu pa kètu agama Jahudi he = cheif priests ; mena'o = secretly ; kèpe mena'o = culik, kidnap ; lod'o nga'a-kewèhu = holidays ; lod'o nga'a-kewèhu = feast day(s) ; Ngee ta = jang sampe (Dimu) = ngita (Seba)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone ketèu pa kètu agama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone ketèu pa kètu agama</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ne pedai roo mi nahère ri dae d'ue lod'o ke, ne lod'o nga'a-kewèhu unu do Jahudi, do tima ta pale ta &lt;Lod'o Paska&gt; nga &lt;Lai Tao Nga'a Roti Dod'o Pake Ragi&gt;. Pa d'ara lod'o nga'a-kewèhu na ène, pehenge awe do uru he, ama-èpu roo mèhu èni ti ihi rai Masir.<bt>They talked like that, because in two more days, the Yahudi people's feast days, which they called &lt;Paska Day&gt; and &lt;The Feast of Bread without Yeast&gt;. During those feasts, they remembered the earlier times, when their ancestors left the country of Masir.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="muu (2) = mur (kuno) &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">muu (2) = mur (kuno) &gt; bibi &gt; ragi ; pehenge = remember ; bibi = 1) bibit (ragi), 2) tante</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 12:1-27</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Mobèni do pehute èi loko wumèngi do rihi maha pa Yesus<bt>A women pours fragrant liquid which is very expensive onto Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:6-13; Johani 12:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Pa rae Betania, era he dèu ne ngara Himo, do ie ti pèda kusta.<bt>In the village of Betania, there was a person named Himo who was healed from the kusta disease.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehame = kasi minyaki, oles ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehame = kasi minyaki, oles ; pehute = kasi tetes ; maha = mahal ; wumèngi = wangi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Pa awe pèda ne noo, b'ege"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Pa awe pèda ne noo, b'ege d'ara dèu ta pe'umu èni nga noo. Do uru, do b'ege dèu ta pe'umu èni nga noo, ri do pèda kusta. Tapulara do na ène, ie ke noo.<span class="Italic">(3)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Awe do na ène, d'ai ded'o la lod'o nga'a-kewèhu, Yesus he kako la nga'a pa èmu Himo. Pa d'ara nga'a roo, dèka ke he dèu mobèni la pehapo nga Yesus. Dèka noo nga pèru hewue wob'uri do tao ti wowadu. Ne ihi noo, èi loko wumèngi do rihi maha keb'ue.<bt>And so after that, when those feast days had not yet come, Yesus (collective) went and ate at Himo's house. While they were eating, a woman came to meet Yesus. She was holding a small.bottle which was made of stone. Its contents were fragrant liquid which was very expensive. Then, she broke by hitting that bottle's cover. And she poured letting drip slowly that fragrant liquid on Yesus' head, as a sign that she showed respect to Yesus.</bt><note reference="14:3-5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne keb'ue èi loko wumèngi nee, hela'u nga gaji he dèu pa d'ara hewue tèu. Pa d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani, ne keb'ue èi wumèngi ne 300 <span class="Italic">&lt;denari&gt;.</span> Ne ngara èi loko wumèngi ne <span class="Italic">&lt;nardos&gt;, </span>ne tao ri dèu do uru he, ti amo aj'u wumèngi. Pa d'ara Alkitab lii J'awa, ne ngara noo &lt;narwastu&gt;. Ne wob'uri nee, do paha ti wowadu. Ne keb'ue wob'uri ne lema, do maha. Pa d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani, ne wob'uri ne tao ngati wowadu, ne ngara wowadu nee, <span class="Italic">&lt;alabastèro&gt;.</span> Alkitab lii J'awa, ne ngara wowadu ne &lt;batu pualam&gt;. Heleo lema <span class="Italic">Luka</span> 7:37-38.<bt>That fragrant liquid's price/value, equivalent to a person's wage one year. The Yunani language Bible says that fragrant liquid's price is 300 &lt;|idenari|r&gt;. The fragrant liquid's name is &lt;<span class="Italic">nardos</span>&gt;, which people used to make from fragrant tree roots. The Indonesian (lit. J'awa language) Bible says its name is &lt;<span class="Italic">narwastu</span>&gt;. And that bottle, they made from stone that could be carved/chiselled. That bottle's price was also expensive. The Yunani language Bible says that bottle they made it out of a stone with its name &lt;<span class="Italic">alabastros</span>&gt;. The Indonesian Bible says that stone's name is &lt;batu pualam&gt;. Also see in <span class="Italic">Luka</span> 7:37-38.</bt></note>Ta pèko ke ri noo ne lakoko wob'uri nee. J'e pehute ne èi wumèngi ne ri noo la wukolo Yesus, rutada pekeb'ue ri noo Yesus.<Annotation class="General" selectedText="wob'uri = buli-buli (botol kecil) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wob'uri = buli-buli (botol kecil) ; boto = large botol ; pèko = patah ; lakoko = leher ; hegèb'e = po'a ; aj'u mèngi = kayu cendana ; aj'u wumèngi = kayu wangi ; pehute = tetes</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Era lema pa ène do pèri dèu do nga'a hela'u nga roo. Ta ngède ne j'èga mobèni na ène, kura pa d'ara ke roo, j'e pedai lii roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Hmm! Mobèni do mi namii mèra, pehore ele èi loko wumèngi do rihi maha na nii!<bt>There were several other people who also were eating together with them. When they saw that woman do like.that, then they got upset and.so they spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;Hmm! What kind of woman is this, wasting that fragrant liquid that is so expensive!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehore = buang ; pehore ele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehore = buang ; pehore ele = buang percuma ; mèra = ??</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Rihi ie ta pewie we ne èi wumèngi d'ee, j'e pepale ne doi do ae ne pa dèu do kehia-gahara! Rowi ne keb'ue èi wumèngi d'ee, hela'u nga gaji he dèu pa d'ara hewue tèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>It would be better to sell that fragrant liquid, to divide out that big money to the poor people (doublet)! Because that fragrant liquid's price/value, is equivalent to a person's wage for one year.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kehia-gahara = (majemuk = kasian)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kehia-gahara = (majemuk = kasian)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ta lii ke Yesus pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole pehedue ri muu mobèni na d'ee! Hane we noo. Mengèlu d'ara Yaa ne tao noo, ri èla ke ri noo pe pehute ne èi wumèngi d'ee pa ngi'u Yaa.<bt>But Yesus said to them, &lt;&lt;You don't need to make things difficult for this woman! Leave her alone! I am happy with her deed, because she has poured this fragrant liquid on My body.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hane = biarkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hane = biarkan</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Do kehia he, do era loro hela'u nga muu. Hèku, nara muu ta ped'elo ruba d'ara nga roo helod'o-helod'o. Tapulara Yaa, tui d'oke ne era hela'u nga muu.<bt>The poor people will always be with you-pl. So, you can show help/mercy to them from day to day. But I am not much longer, cuz I will not much longer be together with you.</bt><note reference="14:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Ped'ire Wari Ruj'ara Muri Mada 15:11</note><v n="8" />Umu ke Yaa ta made. Èi wumèngi do pehute ri mobèni na d'ee pa ngi'u Yaa, hela'u le ke ta lua pemoke Yaa d'ai ne made, mii pemoko rape ta lebe pa ngi'u Yaa.<bt>I will soon die. With this woman pouring this fragrant liquid, she has prepared Me for death, just.like she is sprinkling death.spices on My body/corpse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rape = rampe ; lebe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rape = rampe ; lebe = siram, sebar, hambur ; lua pedane = penguburan, burial</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Henge pe'ie, oo! Pa mii we ne Lii Hag'a D'ara Deo ne pepeke pa hari hewue rai-wawa d'ee, do ta pedae lema ne woie mobèni na d'ee. Mij'i ta toi ri harièle dèu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember this well! Where ever God's Good Story is told thorughout this world, people will also tell about this woman's goodness. In.order.that all people know about her.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tatu = tentu, pasti (loan)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tatu = tentu, pasti (loan)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Juda pelii ta pewie Yesus<bt>Juda makes an agreement to *sell/betray Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:14-16; Luka 22:3-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Èla pe na ène, era he dèu ti do henguru do d'ue ana aj'a Yesus, ne ngara Juda Iskariot. Ta mèhu èni ke noo la kale ne mone ketèu pa kètu agama Jahudi he, mij'e ta la wie Yesus pa roo. Ta d'ai noo nga roo, ta pika ke ne lua dèka noo.<bt>Then, there was one of those twelve disciples of Yesus, named Juda Iskariot. He went.out to find the *chief priests, to give/hand over Yesus to them. Arriving at them, he told them the reason for his coming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lua kerèwi = siasat, licik ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lua kerèwi = siasat, licik ;</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Rihi mengèlu d'ara roo, ta rènge ri roo ne lii pedai Juda. Ta pejaji ke roo, &lt;&lt;Ki kewie ri èu Yesus pa j'ii, ta ma'e ma ri j'ii pa èu.&gt;&gt; Ta mèhu èni ke Juda, j'e kale uku mi namii ne j'ole Yesus pa roo.<bt>They were extremely happy, when they heard what Juda had to say. And they promised, &lt;&lt;If you hand over Yesus to us-ex, we will pay you.&gt;&gt; Then Juda went.out, and he begain to seek a way(negatively valued) to hand over2 Yesus to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pewie = 1) sell, 2) betray"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pewie = 1) sell, 2) betray ; kewie = serahkan ; wèle = buy ma'i ~ ma'e = pay ; kale uku = kale ruj'ara ; pewie ngara = betray name, doesn't have to have money involved</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus nga'a-kewèhu Paska nga ana aj'a Noo<bt>Yesus eats Paska feast with His *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:17-25; Luka 22:7-14, 21-23; Johani 13:21-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ne lod'o na ène, lèka pa lod'o petari ti lod'o nga'a-kewèhu unu do Jahudi. Hèku, pa lod'o na ène, patima roo ta wob'o roti dod'o pake ragi, nga tèb'u ki'i-j'awa. Ta dèka ke ana aj'a Noo he la keb'ali pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama. Lod'o d'ee, lod'o nga'a-kewèhu Paska. Hèku, ne d'èi Ama, pa mii ke j'ii ne era pemoko ta nga'a-kewèhu Paska tuu dii?&gt;&gt;<bt>That day fell on the first day of the Yahudi people's feast days. So on that day, they usually baked bread that did not use yeast, and they also slaughtered a sheep (foreign-goat). Then, His disciples came asking Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;Father. Today is our Paska feast. So where does Father wish us-ex to prepare the Paska feast for us-inc?&gt;&gt; [CHECK: is /nga'a kewèhu/ known by younger generation?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nga'a-kewèhu = feast of special adat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nga'a-kewèhu = feast of special adat celebration ; tèb'u = horo</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ta pejuu ke ri Yesus do d'ue ana aj'a Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Uru ko muu la d'ara kota. Pa nii, ta pehapo muu nga he dèu momone do nga hape èi pa d'ara guhi wo naiki. Pedute we noo ri muu.<bt>Then Yesus told two of His disciples saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go on.ahead into the city. There, you will meet a male who is shoulder.carrying water in a small clay jug. You just follow him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="guhi = guci, kumbang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">guhi = guci, kumbang</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />La èmu na mii noo ne maho, pedute ri muu. Pika muu pa muri èmu nee, mi nahee: &lt;Ama! Ama Guru unu j'ii ta ami era pa Ama, ta pake ta nga'a-kewèhu Paska nga ana aj'a Noo he.&gt;<bt>What ever house he enters, you go follow him. You tell that house owner/master like this: &lt;Father! Our-ex Teacher is requesting a place from Father, to use for eating the Paska feast with his disciples.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ne lii Ama Guru, pa mi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ne lii Ama Guru, pa mi ne era do ta pemoke tuu Yaa ta nga'a Paska hela'u nga ana aj'a he?&gt; (&lt;Ama e! Ne dèka j'ii pejuu ri Ama Guru, ta ma ami hewue era pa èmu èu, mij'e ta pemoko nga'a Paska hela'u nga ana aj'a Noo he.&gt;)</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Do ta peke ri noo hewue kama do bèla pa d'èia ène. Do èla ke pe pemoke ri noo ne kama ène. Hèku muu d'ue la pemoko nga'a we!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person will show a wide/broad room up above. He has already completely prepared/furnished that room. So you two go prepare the food!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kelaga = dek"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kelaga = dek</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ta pekèd'èi ke roo d'ue la d'ara kota. Pa nii, ta pehapo ke roo nga harièle lai do pedai Yesus. Ta la pemoko ke ri roo harièle, mij'e ta nara Yesus ta nga'a-kewèhu Paska pa ène. Ta la pedoa ke ri roo Yesus he.<bt>Then the two of them went into the city. There they met with all that Yesus had already said to them. And they prepared everything, so.that Yesus could eat the Paska feast there. Then they went and summoned Yesus (coll.).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ta jèna lod'o, ta maho ke Yesus nga do henguru do d'ue ana aj'a Noo la nii.<bt>When the sun was begining to go down, Yesus and his 12 disciples went there.</bt><v n="18" />Mejèd'èi roo ta nga'a hela'u-la'u. Pa d'ara nga'a roo, ta lii ke Yesus, &lt;&lt;D'èno ri muu, ee! He dèu ti telora muu do ta la pewie Yaa pa dèu do hewala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they sat to eat together. While they were eating, Yesus spoke, &lt;&lt;You-pl listen, ee! There's one of you, who will later sell/betray Me to other people.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 41:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ta rènge ne lii na ène, ta hedui pengee ke roo. He dèu-he dèu roo ne keb'ali pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mage ta yaa, ne dèu do ane Ama nee?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, their thoughts were troubled. Then they each.one asked Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;That person that Father was mentioning, is it me?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />B'ale ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Dèu do pehèb'u roti la d'ara mago hela'u nga Yaa, noo ke, ne do ta pewie Yaa.<bt>Yesus answered, &lt;&lt;The person who dipped/s bread in the bowl together with Me, he is the one who will sell/betray Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehèb'u = celup ; mago ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehèb'u = celup ; mago = mangkok</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Henge, ee! Yaa d'ee, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu, do ta made tèra pedutu do hure d'o b'uke. Jaga! Ne dèu do pewie Yaa d'ee, do ta hape ri noo ne hoe ihilaka! Rihi ie noo ta b'ole metana ri ina noo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember! I, Ideal/Prototype Human, will die just like what has been written. Be careful! That person who sells/betrays me, he will shoulder.carry his misfortune! It would be better if his mother didn't give birth to him!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hoe-ha'i = sial ; hoe ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hoe-ha'i = sial ; hoe = sial</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pika Yesus, roti nga èi ago lua pehewe ne Noo<bt>Yesus says the bread and grape liquid are to remember Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:26-30; Luka 22:14-20; 1 Korintu 11:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Pa d'ara nga'a roo, ta d'ede ke ri Yesus ne hewue roti, j'e peha'e lii ie ae pa Deo. J'e pipe ri Noo pemae ne roti nee, j'e j'ole pa ana aj'a Noo he. Ta lii ke Noo, &lt;&lt;Ne roti na d'ee, ngi'u Yaa ke. Hème we, j'e nga'e.&gt;&gt;<bt>While they were still eating, then Yesus picked.up a bread, and.so lifted thanks to God. Then he hand.broke that bread (into little pieces), and extended it to His disciples. And He said, &lt;&lt;This bread, is My body. Receive it and eat it.&gt;&gt; [CHECK if /peha'e lii ie ae/ is known by younger generation]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="b'alo = balok (but not unleavened)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">b'alo = balok (but not unleavened) ; j'ule / j'ula = (Dimu), j'ole / j'ola = (Seba) ; ami terima kasi pa Deo ; peha'e lii ie ae = syukur (TSC) ; j'ole (plural but individuated)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01803b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Èla pe na ène, ta èbe ke ri Noo ne galaa do ihe ri èi ago. Peha'e lema Noo lii ie ae pa Deo. Ta j'ole ri Noo ne galaa ne pa ana aj'a he, ta nginu.<bt>After that, He took a glass that was filled with grape liquid. And he also lifted thanks to God. Then He extended that glass to His disciples in.order.that they drink.</bt><v n="24" />Ta lii ke Noo, &lt;&lt;Èi ago na d'ee, raa Yaa ke. Raa do d'ute ta wie helama pa dèu do ae. Raa na d'ee, jad'èi hakahii ta do tobo ke ne lii jaji Deo. Hème we, j'e ngino.<bt>And He said, &lt;&lt;This grape/wine, is My blood. It will be shed (for a cause) to give *salvation to many people. This blood is a witness /evidence to fulfill/make complete what God has promised. receive it, and drink.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="d'ute = tumpa ; peb'ère ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">d'ute = tumpa ; peb'ère = bekin kuat (s.t. unstable like a pole in ground) = perue = (lebih luas) ; hèle = tanam ; tobo = genap, penuh ; ped'ute</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 24:8, Yermia 31:31-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />D'èno pe'ie ko ri muu! J'ari mèd'a d'ee, ad'o ke Yaa do ta nginu wari èi ago. Hape la awe Ama Yaa mejèd'èita pereda pa liru-bèla, j'e'itu ngino wari Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen well! Starting from this night, I will not drink grape liquid again. Until My Father sits ruling in heaven, only.then will I drink (it) again.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta j'uka ke roo hewue lii lod'o ta pekelode ngara Deo. Ta mèhu èni ke roo mèd'a na ène la b'ojo Saitun.<bt>After that, they sang a song to praise God's name/reputation. Then they went.out at.night to go to Saitun hill.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="j'uka = menyanyi ; lod'o ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">j'uka = menyanyi ; lod'o = menyanyi ; lii lod'o = lagu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Pika uru Yesus, ta Petu do ta pehile Noo<bt>Yesus says ahead of time that Petu will deny (knowing) Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:31-35; Luka 22:31-34; Johani 13:36-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Pa d'ara nga nèru roo, ta lii ke Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mèd'a nèb'o, harièle muu do ta perai j'e hane Yaa. Ri do era ke do hure d'o b'uke, mihe ane,<bt>While they were walking then, Yesus spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;Later on tonight, you all will run away leaving Me. Cuz it is written, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pehile = sangkal ; nèb'o ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pehile = sangkal ; nèb'o = soon</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Do ta pemade ri Deo ne mone b'ata nee,<bt>&lt;God will kill the shepherd,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ne ki'i-j'awa noo menyèla kebali-bali.&gt;<bt>And his sheep will run scattered.all.over.the.place.&gt;</bt><note reference="14:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 13:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Tèra do ta made Yaa. Tapulara do ta muri wari Yaa. Ki muri wari Yaa, do ta uru Yaa nga muu la propensi Galilea.&gt;&gt;<bt>I am really going to die. But I will live again. When I live again, I will go ahead of you-pl to propinsi Galilea.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ta pelawa ke Petu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama! Maji le harièle dèu ta perai, j'e hane Ama, tapulara ad'o yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petu protested, saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Even.if all the other people run leaving Father, but not me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus pa noo, &lt;&lt;Petu! Henge ie, ee! Mèd'a d'e d'ènge, uru nga d'o d'ue awe manu ne tutu'oo, tèlu wari ke èu ne pehile Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus responded to him, &lt;&lt;Petu! Remember! Tonight, before the chicken will not yet crowed two times, three times you-sg will already deny (knowing) Me.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manu = ayam ; tutu'oo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">manu = ayam ; tutu'oo = berkoko; [conventionalised for two time cock (crows)];</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ta perui èni ke Petu, j'e lii noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ad'o, Ama, ee! Ki made Ama, ta made hela'u ke yaa, nga Ama. Perai d'oke yaa ti nga Ama, nga pehile d'o Ama ri yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petu was insistant, and spoke saying, &lt;&lt;No, Father, ee! If Father dies, I also will die together with Father. But I will not flee from Father, and won't deny Father!&gt;&gt; [fleshed out from contex])</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perui = strengthened ; pehile ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">perui = strengthened ; pehile = manyangkal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ihianga Petu he dèu-he dèu palii mi nahère lema.<bt>Petu's other friends also each said like that.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mi nahère lema he dèu-he dèu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Mi nahère lema he dèu-he dèu ti ihianga Petu he ne lii pedai.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus heb'aj'a pa d'oka Getsemani<bt>Yesus prays in the Getsemani garden</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:36-46; Luka 22:39-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Èla pe na ène, ta kako teruu ke Yesus he tade d'ai la hewue d'oka pa b'ojo Saitun, ne ngara &lt;Getsemani&gt;. Ta lii ke Yesus pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mejèd'èiko muu ta mate Yaa pa d'ee. Ta la heb'aj'a pa nii ko Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) continued walking to a garden on Saitun hill, it's name &lt;Getsemani&gt;. And Yesus told them, saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl sit waiting here for Me. I want to go pray over there.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ta pedoa ke, ta penau hela'u nga Noo, Petu, J'ako, nga Johani. J'ari ti awe na ène, noho ne ade-pengee Noo ketèna d'oke.<bt>Then Yesus summoned Petu, J'ako, and Johani, to accompany Him. Starting from that time, then His liver-thinking was not a peace.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ketèna = tenang ; noho ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ketèna = tenang ; noho = menoso ; reja = gelisah</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Ta pedai ke Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;D'ai hedui ne ade Yaa. Mii do ta hèpo hengaa ke. Mejèd'èike muu ta jaga pa d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>He told them saying, &lt;&lt;My liver is extremely troubled! It's like I am going to breathe My last (=die). You-pl sit guarding here.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mii do ta hèpo èle ke."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Mii do ta hèpo èle ke.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01810b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35-36" />Ta nèru ke Noo hudi, j'e lèku rutuu Noo pa wurai, j'e heb'aj'a, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ama tana! Ki do mèd'èihe pa d'ara Ama, b'ole made Yaa nga hape lua hedui-herui do mi nahee. Toi tèra ri Yaa, hari-hari lai do nara ta tao ri Ama. Kiri mèd'èihe pa d'ara Ama hore we pej'èu, ne hedui-herui na d'ee ti Yaa. B'ole jad'èi pedutu nga do d'èi Yaa, jad'èi we pedutu nga lua d'èi Ama.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He went on a little bit more, and He knelt on the ground to pray, saying, &lt;&lt;Dear Father! If it matches/agrees with Father's desires/will, I should not die with this suffering (doublet) like this. I truly know that Father is capable of doing everything. So if matches Father's insides, throw away distancing this suffering from Me. Don't happen according to My will; just happen according to Father's will.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mèd'i = setuju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mèd'i = setuju</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ta èla pe heb'aj'a, ta b'ale ke Noo nga do tèlu dèu ana aj'a Noo he, tapulara era do b'èj'i luu. Ta perei ke ri Noo, j'e lii Noo pa Petu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;He, Petu!<bt>After praying, He returned to those three disciples of His, but they were sleeping soundly. Then He woke them up, and He spoke to Petu, saying, &lt;&lt;He, Petu!</bt><note reference="14:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Era do b'uke pa d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani, &lt;Himo&gt;. Himo nee, ngara do wala ti Petu.<bt>The Greek language Bible writes &lt;Himo&gt; here. Himo is another name for Petu.</bt></note>Do luu ta bèj'i èu? He melila he we Yaa pa nii, taha le d'o ma hudi he muu ta jaga hela'u nga Yaa!<bt>You're sleeping, are you? I'm over yonder just only a little bit, but you-pl can't even watch/guard/stay up with Me even a little bit!</bt><v n="38" />Lure ko peweo ne namada èu. Kèd'èi j'e jaga hela'u nga Yaa! D'èi tèra ne ade muu ta j'ège lai do ie, tapulara rui d'o ne ngi'u muu. Rihi ie muu ta heb'aj'a, ngita j'era d'o muu, ki lèka ri ruhèku.&gt;&gt;<bt>Rub making clear your-sg eyes. Then get up and watch/guard with Me! Your-pl livers truly want to do what is good, but your bodies are not strong. It would be best/better for you to pray, lest you lose/are defeated, if/when you encounter testing (of character).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lure = kucak mata, rub (eyes)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lure = kucak mata, rub (eyes) ; ruhèku = coba'an ; j'era = kalah, tobat ; keloe = lemah ; peweo = clear, bright ; waji = cukup, pas</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ta b'ale rike Yesus la heb'aj'a. Ta ami wari ke Noo pa Deo, ta b'ole hane Noo pehape hedui-herui na ène.<bt>Then Yesus went to pray again. He requested again to God, that He not leave Him to meet that suffering (doublet).</bt><v n="40" />Ta b'ale rike Noo nga ana aj'a Noo do tèlu dèu he. Era ke roo do luu ta bèj'i wari, ri rihi ke roo ne mengètu namada. Ta perei ke ri Noo, i'a d'oke roo ne b'ale lii Yesus.<bt>Then He came again to those three disciples of His. They were sleeping again, cuz their eyes were extremely heavy. Then He woke them up again, but they couldn't respond to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mengètu = mengantuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mengètu = mengantuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ta hani ke roo ri Yesus, j'e b'ale la heb'aj'a ketèlu wari. Èla pe heb'aj'a, ta b'ale ke Noo la perei ne ana aj'a Noo. Ane Noo, &lt;&lt;He do bèj'i ko ma muu! Pengaha we ne b'èj'i. Kèd'èi Ne dèu do ta pewie Yaa, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-petuu, hère ke. Awe na d'ee, ta ma kèpe ke Yaa ri roo, j'e la j'ole pa dèu do tao apa he.<bt>Then Yesus left them and returned to pray a third time. After praying, He returned to wake up His disciples. He said, &lt;&lt;You're sleeping again! Enough sleep! Get.up! The person who wants to sell/betray Me, the Ideal/Prototype Human, is already near. Now, they want to capture Me, to hand over to evil people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hère = sudah mendekat, (mi na"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hère = sudah mendekat, (mi na hère)</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Kèd'èiwe! Heleo muu la nii! Na hii ke ne dèu do ta pewie Yaa. Mai we dii la pehapo nga roo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Get.up! Look yonder! There is the person who wants to sell/betray Me. Let's go meet them!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus ta kèpe<bt>Yesus is captured/arrested</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:47-56; Luka 22:47-53; Johani 18:3-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Pa d'ara pedai lii Yesus, hèra d'ènge Juda nga dèu do rihi ae. Dèka roo nga pèru wela nga tubu, ta la kèpe Yesus. Dèka roo nga mi nahère, pedutu lii pereda mone ketèu pa kètu agama Jahudi he, guru agama he, nga dokepai-dokepai rae he.<bt>While Yesus was talking, just all of a sudden, Juda came with many people. They came carrying short fighting-swords and clubs, to capture Yesus. Their coming like.that, was following the command from the Jahudi *chief priests, the religion teachers, and traditional elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wela = parang ; tubu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wela = parang ; tubu = kayu kudung untuk pukul, club</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Do pika uru ke J'uda pa roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Heleo pe'ie ri muu! Naduu do hengèd'o ri yaa, kèpe ri muu! Noo ke ne dèu do kale ri muu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Juda had previously said to them, &lt;&lt;You-pl look closely. Whomever I kiss, you catch/capture/arrest Him! He is the person whom you-pl seek!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hengèd'o = cium"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hengèd'o = cium</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01812b.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Hengèd'o Yesus ri Juda<bt>Juda kisses Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ta d'ai Juda la ène, mola noo nga Yesus, pelango ri noo, &lt;&lt;Ama Guru!&gt;&gt; Ked'ake ri noo, j'e hengèd'o.<bt>When Juda arrived there, he straight.away went to Yesus, then he greeted, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher!&gt;&gt; Then Juda hugged and kissed (Him).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pelango = tegur, greet ; ked'ake"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pelango = tegur, greet ; ked'ake = peluk</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Ta dèka ke ne dèu do ae he la kèpe Yesus.<bt>Then, the many people came forward, to capture Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />He dèu ti dèu Yesus he ta rèda wela ke, j'e pare pehèpo ne wodilu he dèu. Ne dèu na ène, ènu ri kètu mone ae agama Jahudi.<bt>One of Yesus' people drew.out his machete to slash off a person's ear. That person was a servant/slave of the *high priest (Big Boss of the Yahudi religion).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rèda = cabut ; pare ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rèda = cabut ; pare = potong, slash ; @@ j'e pare, hèpo... = action + result ; pare pehèpo = SVC</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Ta pedai ke Yesus nga dèu do la kèpe Noo he, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi namii? Pengee ri muu, Yaa ne mone b'ani? Ku dèka muu ma kèpe Yaa nga wela nga tubu?<bt>Then Yesus talked with those people who (came) to capture Him, saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? You-pl think I am an evil person? So, you come to capture Me with fighting.swords and clubs?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone b'ani = orang berani di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone b'ani = orang berani di sini = watak jahat</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Helod'o-helod'o era ma Yaa nga muu pa Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo, b'ule d'o he dèu he do dèka la kèpe Yaa. Mai we, ma kèpe Yaa. Na d'ee, do lore do hure d'o b'uke ke.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every day I was with you in God's *Temple, (but) there was not one person sho came capture Me. Come on, capture Me. This has already written beforehand.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lore = memang (fore-)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lore = memang (fore-)</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:49" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 19:47, 21:37</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Made ri meda'u ne ana aj'a Noo he. Ta hane ke Yesus, j'e perai roo.<bt>His disciples were scared to death. Then they fled leaving Yesus [CHECK: should this be pronominalised?].</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Pa ène lema, era he dèu ana do ngèru, do pedute Yesus ti kej'unga. Era nga robo hij'i noo. Ta kèpe ke noo ri dèu he,<bt>There also, there was a young person who followed along behind Yesus. He was wrapped with a blanket/large sarong. Those people also wanted to catch/arrest him,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="robo = bungkus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">robo = bungkus</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />tapulara abo pa hij'i noo we. Pelai ti rihi meda'u, ta perai ke noo nga ihi wue, b'ule d'o nga b'ara pa ihi.<bt>but they could only just grab his blanket. So-then he ran home (stark) naked, cause he was so scared.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ihi wue = badan kosong (halus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ihi wue = badan kosong (halus untuk telanjang, but can be without shirt) ; abu ~ abo = dapat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èbe ri roo Yesus la nga mone hèpo kewèlu agama he<bt>They take Yesus to the religious court judges</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:57-68; Luka 22:54-55, 63-71; Johani 18:13-14, 19-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Èla pe na ène, ta èbe ke Yesus ri roo la èmu Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi. Pa ène, era ke do peteni ne dokepai-dokepai he. Harièle mone ketèu pa kètu agama he, guru agama he, nga dokepai-dokepai rae.<bt>After that, they took Yesus to the house of the *high priest. There, various important people had gathered. That is, the *chief priests, the religion teachers, and the traditional elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="keb'odo = anus ; peteni ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">keb'odo = anus ; peteni = gathered</Message></Annotation><v n="54" />Ta d'ai ne èbe ri roo Yesus, Petu lema do pedutu mena'o ti kej'unga, tade d'ai la èmu Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi. Maho noo hape la d'ara rae nee, la mejèd'èihela'u nga dèu do jaga do menyiru ai pa ène.<bt>When They were bringing Yesus there, Petu also followed hidden/quietly from behind, all the way to the house of the *high priest. He went into the yard, to sit warming at the fire together with guard people who were there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menyiru = berdiam ; menyiru ai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">menyiru = berdiam ; menyiru ai = panaskan diri di api</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper &quot;in all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z" status="Information">hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper "in all probability here the temple guard"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Pa d'ara èmu d'ee, mone ketèu pa kètu agama he pedai lii nga dèu do majèd'èita hèpo kewèlu agama he. Harièle roo kale hakahii ta pehale Yesus, ri d'èi ke roo ta wole pemade Noo. Tapulara nara d'o lai nengaa ta mii hakahii.<bt>In that house, *chief priests were talking with the people who sat to decide the religious court. They all sought evidence/witnesses to accuse Yesus, because they wanted to punish Him with death. But they could not get anything as evidence/witness.</bt><v n="56" />Ta pedoa ke ri roo ne dèu do ae, ta hakahii ta pebue Yesus. Tapulara ne lii lolo roo pe'abu d'o he dèu nga he dèu.<bt>And they summoned many people as witnesses to make Yesus fall. But that talking of theirs, it didn't match up with each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lii lolo = keterangan ; pe'abu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">lii lolo = keterangan ; pe'abu d'o = bertentangan ; lodo = pergi ; hakahii = 1) witness, 2) evidence TSC@@</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Era had'e ne hakahii do kèd'èita titu ta ped'èii pote, mihe ane,<bt>And there were several other witness who stood up to speak lying, saying,</bt><v n="58" />&lt;&lt;Rèngi ri j'ii ne lii pedai dèu na d'ee, mihe ane, &lt;Do ta pekelole ri Yaa ne Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo do j'ège ri ruai dèu rai-wawa. Èla pe tèlu lod'o, do ta pekèd'e wari ri Yaa ne Èmu na ène, nga dod'o pake ruai dèu rai-wawa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;We-ex have heard this person talk saying, &lt;I will knock down the Temple that people have build with human hands. Then after three days, I will rebuild that House again, without using human hands.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:58" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Johani 2:19</note><v n="59" />Tapulara pe'abu d'o ne lii lolo roo he dèu nga he dèu.<bt>But that talking of theirs, didn't match.up with each other.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Ta titu ke Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi nee, pa hed'apa harièle dèu do mejèd'èipa ène. J'e keb'ali pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ae ke dèu do kelaa pehed'apa nga Èu. Ta ngaa Èu ku pehèngo èni we?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that *high priest, stood up facing all the people who sat there. And he asked Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;Many people are accusing You-sg. Why are you just quiet?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kelaa = kalak, gugat, tuduh ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kelaa = kalak, gugat, tuduh ; pehèngo èni = diam</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />B'ale d'o ri Yesus he ub'a he. Ta keb'ali rike ne Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi pa Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Hèku ko Èu ta pika mola! Èu tèra ke na d'ee Kristus, Ana Deo do jaje rai uru ne?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus didn't even talk a little bit (lit. not one mouth). Then the *high priest asked again to Him, saying, &lt;&lt;You should talk straight/openly/honestly! Are You here really the Kristus, the Child of God whom He promised from long ago?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Do petuu! Yaa ke na d'ee. Do ta ngède ri muu harièle ta Yaa, Dèu Rai-wawa do Petuu-Petuu, do mejèd'èipa liru-bèla pa ked'anga Deo. Rihi mone ae ne kuaha Noo! Do ta pèru pereda Yaa hela'u nga Noo. Èla pe na ène, do ta puru Yaa ti liru-bèla nga merèmu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;It's true! That's Me here. You-pl will later all see Me, Ideal/Prototype Human here, sitting in heaven at God's right (side). He's that one whose power/authority is greatest! Later I and Him will hold rule together! After that, I will come down again from heaven, with a cloud.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:62" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Dane 7:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Ta rènge ne lii b'ale Yesus do mi nahère, made ri bubu d'ara ne Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi ène, tade hio ke ri noo ne b'aj'u do womerai do pake ri noo. Ta pekaa ke noo pika pa dèu lowe do mejèd'èipa ène, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Teo d'oke dii ta pake hakahii wari!<bt>Hearing Yesus' response like that, then the *high priest was furious, to-point-that he forcefully.ripped.up the long robe he was wearing. Then he yelled telling all the people who sat there, saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc don't need any more witnesses/evidence!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teo d'oke = tidak usa ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">teo d'oke = tidak usa ; nahii &gt; na d'ee &gt; nahère</Message></Annotation><v n="64" />Rèngi ke ri wodilu muu miha, Noo ma do pika wari èni mi nahère. Èla ke Noo pepai èni ta Ana ri Deo. Lii Noo d'ee, ta pe'ape ngara Deo! Pedutu petèka agama dii, ki era dèu do pale wari èni ta hela'u nga Deo, dèu na ène ta pemade! Ku, mi namii ne lai hèpo muu?&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl have heard with your own ears, He himself that spoke like.that. He has raised him to become God's Child. This that He has said is blasphemy (defiles the name/reputation of God)! According to our-inc religious regulations, if a person makes himself to be the same as God, that person must die! So now, how is your-pl decisions?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hèpo ri roo hari-hari, &lt;&lt;Hala tèra ke dèu na d'ee! Hèku, ta wole made!&gt;&gt;<bt>They all decided, &lt;&lt;This person is really wrong! Thus, punish (Him) with death!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pai èni = anggap diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pai èni = anggap diri</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:64" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kètu Agama nga Lua Petèka Agama 24:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="65" />Èla pe mi nahère, ta kèd'èike do pèri dèu la hebue Yesus ri ilu. Wute ne namada Noo, j'e merèho. J'e lii roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Kiri Èu tèra ke mone ub'a Deo, hèku ko Èu ta pale ne ngara dèu do kud'e Èu!&gt;&gt; Ta pereda ke roo pa dèu do jaga Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo, ta ma èbe Yesus. Ta èbe ke ri roo, j'e tèb'e b'ale-b'ale.<bt>After that, several people came.forward to spit at Yesus. They covered His eyes, and (repeatedly) beat (Him). Then they ordered, saying, &lt;&lt;If you are God's spokesman You try to tell the name of the person who socked You (with fist)!&gt;&gt; Then they ordered people who guard the Temple to come take Yesus. They took Him, and they slapped him around.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hebue = sumbur ; kud'e ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hebue = sumbur ; kud'e = falungku ; wute = cover ; tutup ; merèho = beat (repeatedly) ; pali ~ pale ; tèb'e = tampeleng</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petu tèlu wari ne lii ta d'o tade Yesus<bt>Petu says three times, that he does not know Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 26:69-75; Luka 22:56-62; Johani 18:15-18, 25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66-67" />Pa awe do na ène, Petu do mejèd'èita menyiru ai pa d'ara rae ène. Ta dèka ke he dèu mobèni, ènu ri Kètu Mone Ae Agama Jahudi, ngède noo ta menyiru ai. Pehod'e ri mobèni na ène, ne worèwu Petu, j'e kab'ali noo, &lt;&lt;Ngine d'ee, èu era hela'u-la'u nga Yesus, do Nasare ène, we ad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Petu was still sitting in the yard warming (himself) over the fire. Then a female servant of the *high priest came seeing him warming by the fire. The woman looked closely at Petu's face, then she asked, &lt;&lt;Earlier, you-sg were together with Yesus, that Nasare person, weren't you?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="menyiru ai = panggang di api"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">menyiru ai = panggang di api ; pehod'e = maloi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="68" />Ta b'ale ke ri Petu, &lt;&lt;Ad'o! Ta ngaa èu ku lii mi nahère! Tade d'o Noo ri yaa.&gt;&gt; Èla pe na ène, ta kako ke Petu la titu pa toka rae nee. Pa d'ara awe na ène, ta tutu'oo ke ne manu.<bt>Petu answered, &lt;&lt;No! Why are you-sg talking like.that! I don't know Him.&gt;&gt; Then, Petu went to stand by the (fence)gate. At that time/moment, a chicken crowed.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tutu'oo = kokore'o ; toka rae"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tutu'oo = kokore'o ; toka rae = pintu pagar, pintu gerbang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="69" />Ta ngède rike Petu ri mobèni na ène. Ta pika ke noo pa harièle dèu do era pa ène, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Noo ke he dèu ti kejie Yesus!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then, that woman saw Petu again. Then she told all the people there saying, &lt;&lt;He is one of Yesus' (social) group!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Ta pehihi èni ke Petu, j'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ad'o èu ta wuj'u! Tade d'o ri yaa dèu na nii!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petu distanced himself, and spoke, saying, &lt;&lt;You're probably crazy! I don't know that person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pelawa = oppose, protest ; pehihi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pelawa = oppose, protest ; pehihi èni = menyangkal, menjauhkan diri ; @@ ad'o = barangkali, probably maga = lest</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tui d'o, era ri he dèu do hewala pa ène, lii la Petu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ole pote èu ta ad'o do hela'u nga dèu na nii! Muu he, do Galilea, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long again, another person who was there spoke to Petu, saying, &lt;&lt;Don't lie saying you weren't together with that person! All of you-pl, are Galilea people, right?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="71" />Ta pelawa rike Petu, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;B'ani yaa ta hupa! Tade d'o ri yaa dèu na nii!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petu opposed again saying, &lt;&lt;I dare to swear! I don't know that person!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="72" />Tatuu ne lii pedai noo, ta tutu'oo ke ne manu ta d'ue awe. Ta henge ke ri Petu ne lii pedai Yesus ngine, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Uru nga d'o d'ue awe manu ne tutu'oo, tèlu wari ke èu ne pehile Yaa.&gt;&gt;<bt>As he finished speaking, then a chicken crowed two times/for the second time. And Petu remembered Yesus' words earlier, saying, &lt;&lt;The chicken won't yet have crowed two times, you-sg will have denied (knowing) Me three times!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tatuu = habis (bicara)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tatuu = habis (bicara)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mèd'a d'e d'ènge, uru nga d'o"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Mèd'a d'e d'ènge, uru nga d'o d'ue awe manu ne tutu'oo, tèlu wari ke èu ne pehile Yaa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">D'ai ne henge ri noo ne lai na ène, ta tangi oga-oga ke Petu.<bt>Upon remembering that matter, then Petu cried deeply/loudly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tangi oga-oga = menangis keras"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">tangi oga-oga = menangis keras</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Èbe ri roo Yesus la hed'apa Gubernur Pilatus<bt>They take Yesus to face Gubernur Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:1-2, 11-14; Luka 23:1-5; Johani 18:28-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Rai j'ami ae, harièle roo do era pa era hèpo kewèlu hela'u lii ta pemade Yesus. Ta uj'e ke ne ai Noo, j'e èbe la nga Gubernur Pilatus.<bt>Early in the morning, all the people in that court, agreed to kill Yesus. Then they tied His hands and took Him to Gubernor Pilatus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gubernur ~ gurunoo (kuno, jarang)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gubernur ~ gurunoo (kuno, jarang)</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Ta d'ai nga gubernur, ta keb'ali ke pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Mi namii? Petuu tèra ke Èu ta duae do Jahudi?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived at the gubernor, he asked Yesus, saying, &lt;&lt;How.is.it? Is it true that You are the king of the Jahudi people?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta b'ale ke ri Yesus, &lt;&lt;Tèra. Petuu ke ne lii pali Ama Gubernur.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied, &lt;&lt;True. Father Gubernor is speaking correctly.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ta pedae ke ri mone ketèu pa kètu agama he nga gubernur, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ad'o ke ta hudi we ne hala dèu na d'ee!&gt;&gt; Ta nèj'i ke ri roo harièle ne hala Yesus.<bt>Then the *chief priests talked with the gubernor, saying, &lt;&lt;This person has made wrongs/sins which are not few [understatement=many]!&gt;&gt; And they detailed Yesus' wrongs, one by one.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nèj'i = uraikan, daftar terperinci, list"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">nèj'i = uraikan, daftar terperinci, list one by one</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ta keb'ali wari ke gubernur pa Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Rènge d'o ri Èu ne lii pedai roo? Ae ke ne hala Èu, ne pika roo. B'ale ko ri Èu ta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked Yesus again saying, &lt;&lt;Don't you-sg hear that talking of theirs? They are making many accusations against You. You should respond!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rènge = individuated"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">rènge = individuated</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />B'ale d'o ri Yesus he ub'a he, tade madalae gubernur.<bt>But Yesus did not respond one mouth, to-point-that. that gubernor was amazed/confused. [CHECK: I don't think /ked'ii/ is right lexical choice here]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hengodo ; ked'ii = bingung (Seba)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hengodo ; ked'ii = bingung (Seba)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hèpo ri Pilatus ta pemade Yesus<bt>Pilatus decides death for Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:15-26; Luka 23:13-25; Johani 18:39-19:16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Pa tima hewue tèu-hewue tèu, pa lod'o nga'a-kewèhu Paska Jahudi, dèu lowe ami pa gubernur ta gole he dèu ti d'ara èmu b'èdo, pedutu lii ami roo.<bt>Normally from year to year, at the time of the Jahudi Paska feast, many people asked the gubernor to free one jail person, according to their request.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gole = lepas, bebaskan (tunggal) ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gole = lepas, bebaskan (tunggal) ~ golo (jamak)</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Pa awe do na ène, era he dèu do b'èdo, ne ngara Barabas. Ne kèpe noo do uru he, pelai ta pelawa nga do pereda Roma, nga pemade dèu.<bt>At that time, there was a jail person, named Barabas. Before, they captured him, because he opposed the Roma govt, and he killed person/s.</bt><v n="8" />Ri umu ke ne lod'o nga'a-kewèhu Paska, ku ae ke ne dèu do kako nga gubernur, la pekaa, ane roo, &lt;&lt;Ama gubernor! D'ai ke pa lod'o kewèhu Paska. Ki ie he, gole wie j'ii he dèu ti d'ara b'èdo, pedutu tima.&gt;&gt;<bt>Because2 the Paska feast was near, that.is.why many people went to the gubernor to yell out, saying, &lt;&lt;Father gubernor! The Paska feast is here! If possible, please free tu us-exc a jail person according to the custom/normal!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ta keb'ali ke gubernur, &lt;&lt;Naduu ke do ta gole ri yaa? Mi namii ki gole ri yaa ne duae do Jahudi d'ee? Hèmi muu, we ad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked, &lt;&lt;Whom should I free? How.about I free this king of the Jahudi people? You-pl accept, don't you?&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="10" />Pedai gubernur mi nahère, ne petuu he, do toi tèra ke ri noo, ta mone ketèu pa kètu agama he ne èbe Yesus nga noo, pelai ti rihi bubu d'ara nga Yesus.<bt>The gubernor spoke like.that, however he really already knew that the *chief priests had brought Yesus to him, because they hated Yesus very much.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ri mone ketèu pa kètu agama he, ubu made ne dèu lowe he, lii ta ami pa gubernur, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wae d'o j'ii nga Noo! Gole we Barabas!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because those *chief priests persuaded/cajoled those many people, they all request the gubernor, saying, &lt;&lt;We-exc don't want Him! Just free Barabas!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ubu made = bujuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ubu made = bujuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ta keb'ali rike gubernur, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Ki mi nahère, ta tao mi namii ke ri yaa pa Yesus, do pale ta &lt;duae do Jahudi&gt; na d'ee?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked again saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, what must I do with Yesus, whom they call, &lt;king of the Jahudi people&gt;?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ta pekaa ke roo hari-hari, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Pemade we Noo! Raje Noo pa aj'u ketoe!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all yelled, saying, &lt;&lt;Just kill him! Nail him on a *cross (hanging tree/pole/wood--conventionalised in Hawu)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="raje = pakukan ; raja (jamak)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">raje = pakukan ; raja (jamak) ; woruu = paku (n) ; ketoe = gantung ; aj'u ketoe = cross (umum dipakai) ; aj'u lèba = 1) kayu palang, 2) roadblock ; lèba = penghalang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ta keb'ali ke gubernur, &lt;&lt;Nengaa ke ne hala Noo? Pereha ri yaa, b'ule d'o Noo nga hala!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked, &lt;&lt;What is His wrong? I have examined Him, but He has no wrongs!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Juu mèdu ne lii pekaa roo, &lt;&lt;Pemade we Noo! Raje Noo pa aj'u ketoe!&gt;&gt;<bt>They all yelled even louder, &lt;&lt;Kill Him! Nail Him on a cross (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Mij'i mengèlu d'ara dèu lowe, ta gole ke Barabas ri gubernur, pedutu lai d'èi roo. Ta pereda ke ri noo pa dèu jaga he, ta la wèbe Yesus ri gui.<bt>In order to please the crowd, the gubernor freed Barabas, following their will. Then he ordered his guard people, to beat/whip Yesus with a cane/(any)instrument for official punishment.</bt><note reference="15:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Horod'ad'u Roma he do pake gui do èpe ti kuri b'ada. Patima èpi heo. J'e èke ri rui do meriu, kiad'o ti temèru do meriu pa huu dari nee. Ki wèbe loro-loro ri gui nee, tala ne kuri dèu.<bt>The Roma soldiers used a cane/punishing instrument that was made from strands of leather. Normally there were nine cords. Then they tied sharp bones or sharp lead on the ends of the cords. If/when whipped over and over using that cane/punishing instr, people's skins can peal.off.</bt></note>Ta èla pewèbe, ta èbe ke Yesus ri horod'ad'u, ta la raje mij'e ta made pa aj'u ketoe.<bt>Finishing the beating, then the soldiers took Yesus in.order.to nail Him dead on a cross.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gui = rotan, alat pemukul (bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">gui = rotan, alat pemukul (bisa cambuk) ; meriu = tajam ; temèru = tima ; huu = ujung ; tala = terkupas ; terpisah</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus wuhe d'abe, j'e mare-d'ole ri horod'ad'u<bt>Yesus is beaten around and mocked by soldiers</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:27-31; Johani 19:2-3)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Pa awe do na ène, ta nune ke Yesus ri horod'ad'u he la keb'èla kato roo.<bt>After that, the soldiers yanked/dragged Yesus to the broad field of their complex/office ['office' can have barracks, training facilities, admin, etc. whereas 'house' can be the private residence of a single soldier].</bt><note reference="15:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ne era pee horod'ad'u he, patima ne pale pa d'ara lii Latin, ne ngara noo, <span class="Italic">praetorium.</span> Ne benteng roo pa d'ara rae gubernur. Pedutu Alkitab lii Yunani, ne horod'ad'u do pekupu he, he <span class="Italic">speira, </span>era do èna ngahu dèu he, hela'u nga he batalion.<bt>That place of the soldiers, they called in the Latin language by its name |ipraetorium.|r It is the army's own place in the gubernor's complex. According to the Yunani language Bible, the soldiers that gathered were one |ispeira|r, around 600 people, or about the same as one batalion.</bt></note>Ta pedoa ke ne ihianga roo he batalion.<bt>Then they called their companions from one batalion (+/- 750 people).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wuhe d'abe = dipukul ulang-ulang, pukul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wuhe d'abe = dipukul ulang-ulang, pukul sembarang ; ta mare ta d'ole = diejekkan ; diolok-olokkan ; kato = kantor, but implies whole complex including dorms or barracks, whereas èmu can simply mean residential house</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ta pepake ke ri roo Yesus hewue b'aj'u merai do wo kelere mea, do tima ta pake ri duae he. J'e ènyo ri roo ne tèd'u ngati kelai aj'u do dudu. Petèd'o, j'e ènye peb'ère pa kètu Yesus. Ne tao roo mi nahère, ta mare-d'ole Yesus, ta mii d'ede he dèu duae do wiu, pepake tèd'u duae.<bt>Then they made Yesus wear [can also be &lt;dressed him in&gt;] a long purple robe, like kings often wear. Then, they took a thorn tree/bush small branches to braid/twist to make a hat. Then they mashed.down that thorn hat on Yesus' head. They did that to mock (doublet) Yesus, as if they were raising/installing a new king using a king's hat.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="wo kelere = ungu (muda) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">wo kelere = ungu (muda) ; wo kelere mea = purple ; ènyo = anyam ; tèd'u = topi ; kelai = ranting ; dudu = duri ; petèd'o = put hat on ; ènye = tekan ; peb'ère = bekin kuat &lt; b'èra = kokoh ; mare = (VT) mock, laugh at ; pemange = dipermainkan (literal play)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00321C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around:horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ta mare-d'ole rike Yesus ri roo, ta petab'e nga Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Helama pereda, Muri Mone, duae Jahudi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they mocked Him again, and pretended to greet/honour Him, saying, &lt;&lt;Happy governing, great Jahudi king!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="medi-melatu = selamat, umur panjang (kuno)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">medi-melatu = selamat, umur panjang (kuno)</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Hengaja roo ta peru'u èni pa hed'apa Yesus. J'e hebue-hebue ri ilu roo pa tanga mada Yesus. J'e wuhe d'abe ri aj'u pa kètu Yesus ri roo.<bt>And they teasingly knelt before Yesus. Then they spat over.and.over at His face. Then they beat.him.on.head over.and.over with wood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hengaja = sengaja ; keliu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hengaja = sengaja ; keliu = sunyi ; peru'u = tunduk</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ta b'enya roo ne tao pa Noo, ta boke ke ne b'aj'u do womerai nee. J'e pepake wari ri roo ne b'ara pake Noo. Ta èbe ke Noo ri roo la tele kota Yerusalem, mij'e ta la raje ketoe Noo tade made.<bt>They finished doing [term used when a child is abusing another] Him, then they took.off that long robe. And they made Him wear again His clothes. And then, they took Him outside Yerusalem city, to go nail hanging Him until dead.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Raje peb'arèpa ri roo Yesus pa aj'u ketoe<bt>They nail Yesus spread-eagled on the cross</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:32-44; Luka 23:26-43; Johani 19:17-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Pa telora ruj'ara ti Yerusalem, pehapo roo nga he dèu do dèka ngati kota Kirene. Ne ngara noo, Himo, ama ri Aleksander nga Rufus. Ta maho kowe noo la kota Yerusalem, moko ta kèpe ri horod'ad'u he, j'e pehèhe noo ta pehape ne aj'u ketoe Yesus.<bt>On the way/journey from Yerusalem, they met a person who was just coming from Kirene city. His name was Himo, the father of Aleksander and Rufus. He was just entering Yerusalem city, when the soldiers grabbed him, to force him to shoulder.carry Yesus' cross.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peb'arèpa = tertalentang (malentang) dgn tanga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peb'arèpa = tertalentang (malentang) dgn tanga terbuka, terulur ke samping ; itu = baru ; pehèhe = dipaksakan ; pehape = dipikulkan</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 16:13</note><v n="22" />Ta nune-hèpe ke ri roo Yesus, tade d'ai la hewue era, ne ngara Golgota, ne hela'u mi &lt;era rui kètu&gt;.<bt>They pulled (doublet) Yesus until arriving at a place, named Golgota, which is equivalent to &lt;place of piling up head bones/skulls&gt;.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hèpe = tarik ; b'odo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hèpe = tarik ; b'odo = tumpukan ; rui kètu = skull, tengkorak ; kab'ue = harga, nilai ; era b'odo kètu = a (mythical) place in Dimu where they would keep the trophy heads taken in battle</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ne keb'ue ngara nee, &lt;era b'odo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Ne keb'ue ngara nee, &lt;era b'odo rui kètu.&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Pa nii, do ta pengino ri roo nèb'o èi ago do menyilu do pehiwe ri ruaj'u, mij'e ta d'o rihi noho pèda. Tapulara wae d'o Yesus ta ngino.<bt>There they were going to give Yesus sour grape/wine that was mixed with medicine, so.that He could stand the pain. But Yesus did not want to drink it.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pengino = kasi minum ; menyilu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pengino = kasi minum ; menyilu = asam ; ruaj'u = 1) daun, 2) obat ; noho = menoso, pain</Message></Annotation><v n="24-25" />Ta èla pe mi nahère, ta raje ke Yesus peb'arèpa pa aj'u ketoe ri roo. J'e petito ri roo ne aj'u ketoe nee, era wèba heo j'ami ae he. Ta pepili ode ke ne horod'ad'u he, mij'e ta toi ta nara naduu ne b'ara pake Yesus.<bt>Then they nailed Yesus belly-up/spread-eagled on the cross. Then they made that cross stand up, approximately nine o'clock in the morning. Then the soldiers drew lots in.order.to know who would get Yesus' clothes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="petito = kasi badiri (tunggal) ~"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">petito = kasi badiri (tunggal) ~ petitu (jamak) ; j'ami ae = pagi ; pepili ode = buang undi</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 22:19</note><v n="26" />Ta b'uke ke roo pa bèla papa, j'e raje pa huu aj'u ketoe, pemira wukolo Yesus, mihe ane:<bt>Then they wrote on a board, and.so nailed it at the tip of the cross right above Yesus' head, saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mira = tepat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mira = tepat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line Centered" usfm="qc">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Na d'ee ke, Duae do Jahudi&gt;&gt;</span>
      <bt>|i&lt;&lt;This here is the King of the Jahudi people&gt;&gt;|r</bt>
    </p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Na ène ke ne kepue hala ta wole Yesus.<bt>They used that as the reason to punish Yesus.</bt><v n="27" />Pa ène lema, ketoe pemade ri roo do d'ue mone tao kenya'u nga apa-kerewe. He dèu pa heb'èka ked'anga, nga he dèu pa heb'èka keriu Yesus.<bt>There also, they nailed to death two men who were trouble-makers and evil-doers (doublet). One on Yesus' right side; one on His left side.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peraba = perampas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peraba = perampas</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />[Nahère, do lore do hure do b'uke ke, &lt;&lt;Ne tao roo pa Noo, mii pa dèu do tao apa-kerewe.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[With that they followed what was previously established in writing, &lt;&lt;They made/treated Him, like an evil person (doublet).&gt;&gt;]</bt><note reference="15:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara Alkitab lii Yunani do rai uru j'ara, ad'o do era ne ayat 28 na d'ee.<bt>In the oldest Bahasa Yunani writings, there is not this verse.</bt></note><note reference="15:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:12</note></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01836b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Harièle dèu do lake j'ara ène, ngède Yesus do ketoe. Ta piku-piku kètu ke roo, j'e mare pemekae d'ara Noo ri roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Eeh! Ad'o Èu ke do lii, ta b'age pemenyèle ri Èu Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo, j'e pekèd'e wari pa d'ara tèlu lod'o, we ad'o?<bt>All the people who passed by there, saw Yesus hanging. And they shook their heads to make Yesus embarrassed/ashamed, saying, &lt;&lt;Eeh! Didn't You-sg say You can destroy God's Temple, then make it stand again in three days, or not?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="piku = goyang (kepala) ; menihe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">piku = goyang (kepala) ; menihe = fitnah,</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 22:8, 109:25, Ma'u 14:58, Johani 2:19</note><v n="30" />Hèku ko Èu ta puru ti kolo aj'u ketoe nee, mij'e bèla kètu Èu. Ki mi nahère, j'e'itu parahaj'a j'ii ta Èu tèra ke ne Ana Deo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Try to get down from on that cross, to free yourself (idiom). If its like.that, only.then we-ex will really believe You-sg are God's Child.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mij'e bèla kètu Èu = supaya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mij'e bèla kètu Èu = supaya kamu bebas</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Mi nahère lema, ne mone ketèu pa kètu agama he nga guru agama he, ne mare-d'ole Yesus, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Pehelama ri Noo dèu do hewala, tapulara nara d'o ta pehelama ne ngi'u Noo miha!<bt>The same way, the *chief priests and religious teachers also mocked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;He has saved other people, but he can't save His own self!</bt><v n="32" />Do pika wari èni Noo, ta Noo ke ne &lt;Kristus&gt;, dèu do jaje ri Deo rai uru. Lii dèu do hewala, Noo ne Duae do Isra'el. Ki do petuu ke mi nahère, hèku ko Noo ta puru ti aj'u ketoe d'ee, mij'e ngède ri dii. Ki mi nahère, parahaj'a ke dii nga Noo.&gt;&gt;<bt>He called Himself &lt;Kristus&gt;, that.is the person whom God has promised from long ago. Others say, He here is the King of the Isra'el people. If it's really like that, let Him get.down from that cross so.that we-inc can see. If (He does) that, we will believe in Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hib'u = tebus, selamatkan ; mone"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hib'u = tebus, selamatkan ; mone hib'u = penyelamat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Hari do d'ue dèu do ketoe hela'u nga Yesus he, pedutu lema ta mare-d'ole Noo.<bt>Those two people that were hanging together with Yesus, also followed mocking Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua made Yesus<bt>The death of Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:45-56; Luka 23:44-49; Johani 19:28-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Pa awe do na ène, ta kerèba guru rai ke ne era na ène, rai nètu lod'o tade wèba tèlu mako lod'o.<bt>At that time, deep darkness covered that place, from mid day to 3 o'clock in the afternoon.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kerèba = gelap ; kerèba guru"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kerèba = gelap ; kerèba guru rai = gelap gulita ; mako lod'o = Mid afternoon, sun leaning toward the west</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Pa d'ara wèba tèlu, ta pekaa ke Yesus pa d'ara lii Aram, mihe ane, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eloi! Eloi! Lama sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (Ki peb'ale pa d'ara lii rai dii, &lt;&lt;Wo Muri Yaa! Deo Yaa! Ta ngaa ke Ama ku naja kej'unga, j'e hane Yaa mi nahee?&gt;&gt;)<bt>At three o'clock, then Yesus shouted in their Aram language saying, &lt;&lt;|iEloi! Eloi! Lama sabaktani?|r&gt;&gt; (It's meaning in our-inc language is, &lt;&lt;Wo My Lord! My God! Why is Father turning his back abandoning Me like this?&gt;&gt;)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="naja = pasang ; naja kej'unga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">naja = pasang ; naja kej'unga = bale belakang (tolak, mebiarkan)</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 22:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Era do pèri dèu do umu pa ène, do rènge ne lii pekaa Yesus. Ta lii ke roo, &lt;&lt;Weh! D'èno ko ri muu. Nèi ke ri Noo ta pedoe Elia, mone ub'a ngati Deo do uru ne!&gt;&gt;<bt>There were several people close by there hearing that shout of Yesus'. Then they said, &lt;&lt;Weh! You-pl listen! He's summoning Elia, that *prophet of God's from before!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="36" />Mèri-mèriai he dèu la èba boroo la pehèb'o pa èi ago do menyilu. Tèb'o ri kèji ne boroo nee, j'e pej'ole la kuri ub'a Yesus, mij'e ta hemuhe ri Noo, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Mata ko! Heleo ko ri dii! Ngita dèka tèra Elia ma pepure Noo ti aj'u ketoe d'ee.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then one person hurried to get sea-sponge to dip it in sour grape/wine. Then he speared that sponge on the end of a walking.stick, and extended it to Yesus' lips so.that He could suck. There were those who spoke, &lt;&lt;Wait! Let's see! Perhaps Elia will come to get him down from that cross.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="boro'o = busa yg di laut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">boro'o = busa yg di laut (Dimu) boroo (Seba) = sea sponge ; tèb'o =</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lii Wue-Waje 69:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Moko ta pekaa wari ke Yesus, j'e made.<bt>After that Yesus shouted again, then died.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Pa d'ara Èmu Kepue Heb'aj'a pa Deo, era ne b'èla do perète ta pewate Kama do Mèu do Megala. Pa awe hèpo hengaa Yesus, ne b'èla mehèri ped'ue rai ti d'èia, hape la d'a'i.<bt>In the *Temple, there was a big curtain hanging to block the Holy (doublet) Room. Exactly when Yesus died (ceased breathing), then that cloth ripped into two, from the top to the bottom.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="perète = tagantung ; pewate ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">perète = tagantung ; pewate = pele, batasi ; ped'ue ; b'èla do bèla = kain yg lebar @@CIE</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Do Isra'el Mèhu èni ti Masir 26:31-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Pa Golgota, era he dèu kètu horod'ad'u do jaga, do titu pe'umu nga aj'u ketoe Yesus. Ta ngède ri noo ne lua made Yesus, ta keb'èdi ke noo. J'e lii, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Wii! Tèra-tèra, Dèu na d'ee, Ana Deo!&gt;&gt;<bt>At Golgota, there was a head soldier guarding who stood near Yesus' cross. When he saw Yesus' death (process), he was amazed/startled [CHECK: should it be /madalae/?]. Then he said, &lt;&lt;Wii! This Person here, really truly is God's Child!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40-41" />Pa ène, era lema do pèri dèu mobèni, do titu ti j'èu, do ngède ne lua made Yesus. Mobèni nahère, do tima ta pemoke Yesus he pa Galilea. Ne ngara mobèni he, Salome, Maria ti rae Magdala, nga Maria do wala (ri ina ri J'ako do ngèru, nga Yoses),<bt>And there were several women there, standing a little far, who watched Yesus' death. Those women were ones who had served Yesus mob in Galilea. The names of the women were, Salome, Maria from the village of Magdala, and another Maria (that.is the mother of young J'ako and Yoses),</bt><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Pa d'ara do b'uke pa lii Yunani, era had'e do b'uke ta &lt;ina ri Yoses&gt;, era lema do b'uke ta &lt;ina ri Yosef&gt;.<bt>Some Yunani writings say &lt;Yoses' mother&gt;, others say &lt;Yosef's mother.&gt;</bt></note>nga era ri ko mobèni do wala, do dèka pedutu Yesus hape la Yerusalem.<bt>and there were other women who followed Yesus coming to Yerusalem.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="henata = menyambut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">henata = menyambut</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Luka 8:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Lua pedane Yesus<bt>The burial of Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 27:57-61; Luka 23:50-56; Johani 19:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Èla pe na ène, era he dèu do kale pengee ta d'èi ta pepure ngi'u Yesus ti aj'u ketoe. Ne ngara noo Yusuf, ti rae Arimatea. Noo lema he dèu ti telora mone hèpo kewèlu pa d'ara agama Jahudi. Noo he dèu, mone mola ngee. Noo lema pa d'ara ta mata ne dèka lua pereda Deo.<bt>After that, there was a person who sought a way wanting to take down Yesus' body/corpse from the cross. That person's name was Yusuf, from Arimatea village. And he also among (=one of) the judges of the Jahudi religious court. He was a person of good character (lit. straight/pure thinking). And he had been waiting the coming of God's rule.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mone hèpo kewèlu pa d'ara agama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">mone hèpo kewèlu pa d'ara agama Jahudi = correct form (CHECK ALL)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Do woie ne ade-pengee noo."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Do woie ne ade-pengee noo.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Made Yesus, lèka pa hari lèmi. B'èli rai nee, lod'o heb'aj'a do Jahudi. Ri harièle mii ke, ku d'èi ke Yusuf ta la pepure mèriai ne ngi'u Yesus. Ta peb'ani d'èlu ke noo, ta la ame ne ngi'u Yesus pa gubernur Pilatus.<bt>Yesus' death was on Friday (day five). The next day would be the Jahudi people's worship day. That.is.why Yusuf wanted to quickly take down Yesus' body. So he made brave his abdomen, in.order.to go request Yesus' body at gubernor Pilatus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pab'ani ngungu = (Dimu) = peb'ani"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pab'ani ngungu = (Dimu) = peb'ani d'èlu (Seba, Dimu) beranikan diri</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Ta rènge ne lii ami Yusuf mi nahère, ta hengodo ke noo, j'e lii, &lt;&lt;Weh! Made d'ènge ke Noo? Ne pengee ri yaa, ad'o mi nahère.&gt;&gt;<bt>When the gubernor heard Yusuf's request like.that, then he was amazed/surprised. Then he said, &lt;&lt;Weh! He has already died? In my thinking I didn't think was like.that.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta pejuu ke ri noo dèu la pedoe ne kètu horod'ad'u do jaga. J'e keb'ali noo, &lt;&lt;Mi namii we? Do made tèra ke Yesus, we ad'o?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he sent someone to go summon that *commander (head of the soldiers) guarding. Then he asked him, &lt;&lt;How.is.it? Has Yesus really already dead or not?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ta b'ale ke ri kètu horod'ad'u nee, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Made rai ngine heke, Ama, ee.&gt;&gt; Ta rèngi ri gubernur ta do mi nahère, ta lii ke noo pa Yusuf, ta la èbe ne ngi'u Yesus.<bt>That *commander replied saying, &lt;&lt;He died since earlier, Father, ee.&gt;&gt; Hearing that, the gubernor spoke to Yusuf to go take Yesus' body.</bt></p>
    <fig path="c:\graphics\cook\cnt\cn01847b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Èbe ne ngi'u Yesus la pedane<bt>(They) take Yesus' body to bury</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ta pekèd'e ke Yusuf la Golgota. La pepure ri noo ne ng'iu Yesus ti aj'u ketoe. Ta wute ke ri noo ne ngi'u Yesus pe wo'ie-ie, ri b'èla do wiu, do maha keb'ue. Pa awe do na ène, ta èla kowe roo, pe kei hewue ro'a naba ta tuu rae dare pa b'ojo wowadu. Ta hero'e ke ri roo ne ngi'u Yesus la d'ara ro'a ène. J'e riho ri roo hewue ne wowadu keb'èla do worena, la henèb'e ne ub'a ro'a ène. Ta b'ale ke Yusuf he.<bt>Then Yusuf went to Golgota. And he took down Yesus' body from the cross. He wrapped carefully Yesus' body with new cloth which was expensive. At that time, they had just finished digging a horizontal hole for a grave into a rock hill/mound. Then they carried entering Yesus' body into that (grave) hole. Then, they rolled a heavy round (&amp; flat) rock, to close the mouth of that hole/grave. Then Yusuf mob went home.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kee penabe = gali bekin goa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">kee penabe = gali bekin goa, gali masuk ; keb'ila = batu pipi, plat, ceper (Dimu) ~ keb'èla (Seba) ; henèb'e = tutup ; kee ~ kei ; naba = horizontal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itu ta moko kowe ri roo,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">itu ta moko kowe ri roo, ne kee penabe hewue ro'a pa b'ojo wowadu. Èla pe mi nahère, ta hero'e</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Pa awe na ène lema, Maria ti rae Magdala, nga Maria do wala (do ina ri Yoses ne), do pedutu hape la nii. Do toi woie ke ri roo d'ue, ne era peb'èj'e Yesus.<bt>At that time also, Maria from Magdala village, and the other Maria (that.is Yoses' mother), were following to there. The two of them noted carefully that place where they laid Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peb'èj'e = dibaringkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">peb'èj'e = dibaringkan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus do muri wari!<bt>Yesus lives again!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 28:1-8; Luka 24:1-12; Johani 20:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Bèli rai, hari èna, lod'o heb'aj'a do Jahudi. Ta èla pejèna lod'o, ta pekèd'èike Maria ti rae Magdala, Maria do wala (do ina ri J'ako), nga Salome, la wèli èi loko wumèngi, do ta èbe roo bèli rai, la pihe ngi'u Yesus, pedutu had'a Jahudi.<bt>The next day was Saturday (day six), the Yahudi people's day of worship/prayer. After the sun had already set, Maria from Magdala village, that other Maria (that.is J'ako's mother), and Salome, went to buy fragrant liquid, in.order.that tomorrow they could take it to go sprinkle it on Yesus' body/corpse, following the Jahudi tradition.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pihe = percik"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pihe = percik</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Rai j'ami ae lod'o Migu, ta pekèd'èike roo tèlu la rai dare Yesus.<bt>Then early Sunday morning, then the three of them went to Yesus' grave.</bt><v n="3-4" />Pa telora ruj'ara, ta pedai ke roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Weh! Naduu ke do ta ami ri dii, ta riho ne wowadu worena do henèb'e ub'a ro'a nee? Mèka d'o dii tèlu, ta riho ne wowadu ène!&gt;&gt;<bt>On the way/journey, they talked, saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! Who will we ask to roll that heavy rock that is covering the mouth of the grave? Surely we-inc three can't move rock!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ta d'ai roo la nii, ngède ri roo ne wowadu ne èla ke periho.<bt>When they arrived there, then they saw that rock was already rolled/moved.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="periho = geser , pindah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">periho = geser , pindah</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ta maho ke roo la d'ara ro'a ène. Ta keb'èd'èiane ke roo, ri ngède ri roo he dèu do ngèru do mejèd'èipa heb'èka ked'anga roo, nga pake b'ara wo pudi kewa'a.<bt>Then they entered into that hole/grave. They were startled, because they saw a young person sitting to their right side, and wearing shiny white clothes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="keb'èd'i hala / ane = Idiom,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">keb'èd'i hala / ane = Idiom, tiba-tiba terkejut ; wo pudi kewa'a = puti mengkilat, puti barisi</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ta lii ke ne do ngèru na ène pa roo, &lt;&lt;B'ole meda'u muu! Toi ri yaa, ta muu he ma kale Yesus ti Nasare, do èla pe pemade ri roo pa aj'u ketoe. Pe'ee d'o pa d'ee, èla ke Noo pemuri wari. Mai ma heleo miha ri muu, ne era peb'èj'e ngi'u Noo. Pe'ee d'oke.<bt>Then that young person told them, &lt;&lt;Don't be afraid! I know you are coming to look for Yesus from Nasare, whom they killed on the cross. He is no longer here, (because) he is already alive again. Come, so.that you can see for yourselves that place where His body was laid. He's not there any more.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'ee d'o = tidak ada lagi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pe'ee d'o = tidak ada lagi</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />B'ale we muu mèriai! La pika pa Petu he, ta èla ke Yesus pemuri wari. Nèi ke Noo do uru la Galilea. Do ta pehapo muu nga Yesus pa nii, mi namii ne lii pika uru Noo pa muu. Naa, b'ale we muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl go.home quickly (imperative)! Go tell Petu (collective) that Yesus is already alive again. He is going on ahead to Galilea. Later you-pl will meet Yesus there (remote), same.as what He told you-pl previously. Naa, you-pl go.home (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="16:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateo 26:32, Ma'u 14:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ta d'ai ne ngède ri mobèni he, ta d'o pe'ee tèra ke ne ngi'u Yesus, ta hengodo ke roo. Ta perai ke roo la tele. B'ale roo mèri-mèriai. Pedai d'o roo pa naduu-naduu pa ruj'ara, ri rihi meda'u roo.<bt>When those women saw that Yesus' body was really not there anymore, they were startled/confused. Then they ran outside. They went.home quickly. They didn't tell anyone on the road, because they were so scared.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pehapo nga Maria ti Magdala<bt>Yesus meets with Maria from Magdala</bt><note reference="16:9-20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii do b'uke pa d'ara buku lii Yunani do rihi uru, nga do rihi ie, pedèka pa ayat 8. Lii Ped'èii Ma'u, henèb'e nga d'ue kera'a ruj'ara: he èhi do merai (Markus 16:9-20), nga he èhi ri do b'ab'a (Markus 16:9-10). Pedutu lii do mèu d'ara, do toi woie ne lii ped'èii Ma'u na d'ee, hari d'ue kera'a ruj'ara nahee, b'uke leto we. Tao ne lai henèb'i na ènetèke (b'uke) pa era do pedèka rai. Hari d'ue lii ped'èii j'ara lua muri wari Yesus ti made mada, nga lai do ta j'èga ri dèu do parahaj'a pa Yesus.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Ma'u's Story closes in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to knowledgable people who know Ma'u's story very well (=expert), these two closings were written afterward. Both of them tell of the resurrection of Yesus from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 28:9-10; Johani 20:11-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Rai j'ami ae lod'o Migu, Yesus pengèdi èni pa Maria ti Magdala, do ngèdi ta hud'èiti d'ara noo ri Yesus, pidu ngi'u wango.<bt>Early that Sunday morning, Yesus revealed himself to Maria from Magdala, whom previously Yesus had expelled seven evil spirits from inside her.</bt><v n="10" />Ta èla noo pe pengèdi nga Yesus, ta b'ale ke noo la pika pa harièle dèu do ngèdi ta pedute Yesus. Do pee ko roo pa d'ara pekupu, nga hedui pengee he, nga pewewi èi namada ta henge ne lua made Yesus.<bt>After she saw Yesus, then she went.home to tell all the people who previously had followed Yesus. They were still gathered with sadness and their tears were falling remembering the death of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pewewi = alir terus"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pewewi = alir terus</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ta lii ke Maria pa roo, &lt;&lt;Ta ngaa muu ku pee ko nga hedui? B'ole hedui ri ne pengee, èla ke Yesus pemuri wari! Do na d'ee kowe, pehapo ko nga yaa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Maria told them, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl still (in.a.state.of) difficulty/distress? Don't be troubled in your thinking, cuz Yesus is alive again! Just now, (He) met with me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tapulara b'ale ri roo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Weh! B'ole peluu j'ii ri èu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they responded, saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! You-sg are lying/deceiving!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pengèdi èni rii pa do d'ue dèu<bt>Yesus reveals himself to two more people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 24:13-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Èla pe na ène, era do d'ue ana aj'a Yesus do kako la hewue rae. Pa telora ruj'ara, ta dèka ke Yesus la pengèdi èni pa roo d'ue. Rowi do wala ke ne hia Noo, hèku ue ta tui hudi ne tade ri roo.<bt>After that, there were two of Yesus' disciples who were walking to a village. On the way/journey, Yesus came and revealed himself to the two of them. Because His appearance was different, it was after a little (while), before they recognised (Him).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hia = gaya, bentuk, (seluruh) ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">hia = gaya, bentuk, (seluruh) ; pengèdi èni = penampakan, wujud ; ue = agak</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tapulara, do wala ke ne hia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">Tapulara, do wala ke ne hia Noo. Tui d'o, j'e tade d'ènge Noo.</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ta b'ale ke roo d'ue, la pika pa ihianga roo, &lt;&lt;Weh! D'èno ko ri muu! Ngine d'ee, pehapo Yesus nga j'ii pa ruj'ara!&gt;&gt;<bt>They the two of them went.home to tell their friends saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! You-pl listen! Just now, we-ex met Yesus on the road!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Tapulara ne lii ihianga roo harièle, &lt;&lt;Weh! B'ole peluu j'ii ri muu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But their friends all said, &lt;&lt;Weh! You-pl don't lie!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus pengèdi èni pa harièle ana aj'a Noo<bt>Yesus reveals himself to all his disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateo 28:16-20; Luka 24:36-49; Johani 20:19-23; Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu Yesu 1:6-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Èla pe na ène, pengèdi èni rike Yesus pa do henguru he dèu ana aj'a Noo, pa d'ara mejèd'èita nga'a roo. Ta b'ani ke ri Noo, mihe ane, &lt;&lt;Weh! Rihi kètu wowadu muu! Dèu ta pika pa muu, ta do ngède ke Yaa ri namada roo miha, parahaj'a d'o muu! Ane muu, ta peluu muu. Na d'ee, ne ke Yaa ma hed'apa muu. Èla tèra ke Yaa pemade, tapulara do na d'ee, ne ke Yaa do muri wari! Naa, heleo ri namada muu miha.<bt>After that, Yesus revealed himself again to His eleven disciples while they were eating. He scolded them, saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! You-pl are very stubborn (idiom)! People have told you that they have seen Me with their very own eyes, but you don't believe! You say, they're lying! Now, I myself am facing you. I really died, but now, I live again! Naa, you just see with your own eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pelango = greet, welcome (but not"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">pelango = greet, welcome (but not scold)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Hèku, na d'ee, kako we muu la èpa keb'ihu rai-wawa d'ee, la pepeke pa harièle dèu ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Yaa.<bt>Thus, now you must go to the four corners of this earth, to tell all people, this Good Story of Mine.</bt><note reference="16:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu Yesu 1:8</note><v n="16" />Naduu do parahaj'a nga Yaa, j'e do herani ke, do ta wie ri Deo ne helama pa noo, mij'e nara noo ta muri loro hela'u nga Deo pa liru-bèla. Tapulara naduu dod'o parahaj'a, do ta nara ruwolo noo, ta hane loro noo ri Deo pa tele.<bt>Whoever believes in Me, and gets *baptised, God will give him/her *salvation, so that he can live continually with God in heaven (doublet). But whoever doesn't believe, he will get punished, and God will abandon him/her continually on the outside (heaven).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ruwolo = hukuman"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">ruwolo = hukuman</Message></Annotation><v n="17" />Ne dèu do parahaj'a pa Yaa, do ta tao ri roo, ae kera'a rutada madalae, mij'e ta toi ri harièle dèu, ta kuaha do era pa roo dèka ngati Deo. Unupala he roo, do ta nara roo ta hud'èiwango nga ngara Yaa. Do ta wie ri Deo, ta i'a pedai lii pedai do wala, dod'o toi ri roo.<bt>And the people who believe in Me, they will do *miracles of all sorts, so.that all people know that their power/authority, comes from God. For example, they will be able to expel *evil spirits with My name. Later God will make them able to speak in other languages that they don't know.</bt><v n="18" />Kiri ta hib'i ri dob'oho do nga raho, kiad'o lèka ta nginu raho roo, ihilaka d'o roo. Ki tèka roo wolaèba pa wukolo dèu do pèda, ta ie ma ne dèu ène.&gt;&gt;<bt>If they hold poisonous snake, or else they are affected by drinking poison, they will not experience misfortune. If they put hands on top of sick people's heads, those people will become well/healed.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dob'oho = ular (generic) ; raho"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-02 21:19:42Z">dob'oho = ular (generic) ; raho = racun</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yesus ta d'ede la liru-bèla<bt>Yesus is taken up to heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Luka 24:50-53; Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu Yesu 1:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ta èla Yesus pepedai lii nga ana aj'a Noo he, ta d'ede ke Noo ri Deo la liru-bèla. Pa nii, jad'èi Noo ta ai d'anga Deo, mejèd'èi Roo hela'u ta pereda.<bt>After Yesus spoke with those disciples of His, then God lifted Yesus up to heaven. There (remote) He is God's right hand (= #2 man), so the two of them sit ruling together.</bt><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Muri Mada Dèu Pejuu Yesu 1:9-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ta èla pe mi nahère, ana aj'a Noo he, pedute ne lii pereda Noo. Pekèd'èiroo la harièle keb'ihu rai la pepika Lii Hag'a D'ara ngati Yesus pa harièle dèu. Ta wie ke ri Deo pa roo, ne kuaha ta tao ae kera'a rutada madalae do èla pewie ri Yesus. Ae tèra ne dèu do parahaj'a pa Yesus, ri ne Lii Haga D'ara na d'ee, do petuu.<bt>After that, His disciples followed His command(s). They went to all the corners (of the earth) to tell all people Yesus' Good Story. And God gave them power/authority so.that they could do all those miracles that Yesus had told them. Then a great many people believed in Yesus, cuz they knew that that Good Story, is really true.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">LUA HENÈB'E LII PED'IRI MA'U, PEDUTU DO HURE DO B'UKE DO WALA<bt>THE END OF MARKUS' STORY, FOLLOWING ANOTHER WRITING</bt><note reference="16:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Lii do b'uke pa d'ara buku lii Yunani do rihi uru, nga do rihi ie, pedèka pa ayat 8. Lii Ped'èii Ma'u, henèb'e nga d'ue kera'a ruj'ara: he èhi do merai (Markus 16:9-20), nga he èhi ri do b'ab'a (Markus 16:9-10). Pedutu lii do mèu d'ara, do toi woie ne lii ped'èii Ma'u na d'ee, hari d'ue kera'a ruj'ara nahee, b'uke leto we. Tao ne lai henèb'i na ènetèke (b'uke) pa era do pedèka rai. Hari d'ue lii ped'èii j'ara lua muri wari Yesus ti made mada, nga lai do ta j'èga ri dèu do parahaj'a pa Yesus.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Markus' Story closes in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to knowledgable people who know Markus' story well (=expert), these two closings were written afterward. Both of them tell of the resurrection of Yesus from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ta d'ai ne do tèlu mobèni he ta pe'abu nga Petu he, ta ped'èii ke roo harièle j'ara lua do ngèru do pedai lii nga roo pa rai dare ne ngine.<bt>When those three women arrived at Petu mob, they told everyone about that young person who had spoken with them in/at the grave earlier.</bt><v n="10" />Moko ke Yesus miha pereda pa ana aj'a Noo he, lita kako la pepeke ne Lii Hag'a D'ara ti Noo la hari-hari era, hape la èpa keb'ihu rai-wawa. Lii Hag'a D'ara na d'ee, do pika ruj'ara ta Deo do ta wie helama pa harièle dèu ti hala-ludu roo, mij'e ta nara roo ta muri mada peloro nga Noo.<bt>And then, Yesus himself commanded His disciples, that they go tell this Good Story of His to all places, to the four corners of the world. This Good Story tells the way for God to save all people from their wrongs (doublet), so.that they can live continually with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Lii Hag'a D'ara na d'ee, do petuu tèra. Ri do mi nahère ke, ku pee noo ta era loro, hape la lod'o na mii-mii.<bt>This Good Story, is really true. That.is.why it endures continually, until forever.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <fig path="maps\bible\palestin.bmp" rtfFormat="width:10.5cm" />
  </book>
</bible>